title: spicy chicken bake
directions: Optional:
Dip seasoned chicken in barbecue sauce before baking.

title: cornflake drop cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugars until creamy, (fluffy). Beat in eggs and vanilla. Stir in dry ingredients. Stir in raisins and corn flakes. Drop by teaspoons on greased baking sheet. Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes. Makes 6 dozen cookies.

title: pork chops and apple slices
directions: In skillet, brown pork chops quickly.
Drain well.
Arrange a layer of sliced apples in crock-pot, then a layer of pork chops; repeat.
Dot with butter; sprinkle with nutmeg and salt and and pepper.
Cover and cook on low setting for 7 to 9 hours.
Makes 4 servings (about 2 1/2 quarts).

title: chocolate covered cherry cake
directions: Mix and bake at 350° in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Frost with Chocolate Icing.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix all ingredients in large bowl, using hands to mix well. When mixed, pinch off bits of mixture, about the size of marbles and roll in balls.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: banana split
directions: Combine 1/2 cup margarine and graham cracker crumbs.
Press into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Beat eggs 4 minutes at high speed. Add sugar, 3/4 cup softened margarine and vanilla.
Beat 5 minutes. Spread over crumb mixture.
Chill 30 minutes.
Spread pineapple and add bananas.
Cover with Cool Whip.
Sprinkle with pecans.
Can garnish with maraschino cherries.

title: oatmeal fudge
directions: Beat until firm enough to hold shape.
Drop by spoonful on wax paper.
Easy to make.
My children loved them.

title: toll house pie
directions: In a large bowl, beat eggs until foamy.
Add flour and sugar and beat until well blended.
Blend in melted margarine.
Stir in chocolate chips.
Pour in pie shell and bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Line bottom of a 9 x 13-inch baking dish with ground beef that has already been browned.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Cover meat with slices of American cheese.
Spoon cream of mushroom soup over cheese.
Top with Tater Tots placed in rows to cover area. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: shrimp and crabmeat casserole
directions: Place soup in a 2-quart casserole and stir in sherry, mushrooms and almonds.
Fold in seafood gently.
Cover with layer of cheese.
Sprinkle paprika on top.
Can refrigerate until ready to bake at 300° for 1 hour.
Serve over rice.
Serves 6.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Combine cooked chicken (cold), celery, onion, almonds and mayonnaise.
Spread into a baking dish. Add cheese evenly over mixture, then top with potato chips.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes in a 400° oven.
Check occasionally.
Do not let potato chips get too brown.

title: cool cake
directions: Bake cake.
Let cool upside-down.
After cake is cool, poke your fingers in it for holes.
Pour your thawed strawberries and syrup over cake.
Spoon vanilla pudding over strawberries.
Cover entire cake with Cool Whip like you would do icing.
Refrigerate. Enjoy.

title: german potato salad
directions: Fry bacon until crisp; crumble.
Add to potatoes, onion, celery and seasonings.
Add vinegar to hot bacon drippings; simmer 5 minutes.
Stir in flour to thicken.
Pour over potato mixture. Cover; let stand in a warm place for 3 hours.
Serve warm.
Makes 15 servings.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients except 1 cup of cheese.
Pour into a 9 x 12-inch casserole dish.
Top with remaining cheese.
Heat in oven until cheese melts and casserole is hot throughout.
Bake at 350°.

title: overnight french toast
directions: In a saucepan, over low heat, combine corn syrup, butter and brown sugar.
Cook just until it is syrup.
Put this mixture in the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Cover the syrup completely with the apple slices.
Place the bread slices on top of the apples.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Mix sugar, corn syrup, salt and milk together in a deep saucepan.
Cook over high heat, stirring a few times until a drop tested in cold water forms a soft ball.
Let cool down some.
Then add peanut butter and vanilla and beat vigorously until candy loses its shine and starts to thicken.
Pour into buttered pie pan and let stand until firm.
Cut in squares.

title: potato casserole
directions: Heat butter with soup.
Blend sour cream, onion and cheese into soup.
Stir until smooth.
Stir in potatoes.
Place in buttered casserole dish.
Sprinkle corn flake crumbs on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Yields 10 to 20 servings.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour, vanilla, milk and margarine.
Add eggs to mixture and then pecans; stir.
Bake in cold oven at 300° until firm and lightly browned.
Makes 2 pies.

title: deep dish spinach pie
directions: Combine flour and sugar; with 2 knives cut in butter until flour resembles coarse crumbs.
Add egg and water, mixing until dough forms a ball.
Wrap and chill.

title: tropical coconut chicken
directions: Place chicken between two pieces of wax paper and gently pound to 1/4-inch thickness. In small bowl, place egg, water, salt and pepper; stir to mix well. In shallow dish, place coconut. Dredge chicken, first in egg mixture, then in coconut, pressing to coat well. In large non-stick fry pan, place olive oil and butter over medium heat. Add chicken and cook until done.

title: apricot nectar cake
directions: Mix all ingredients, except powdered sugar and lemon juice. Bake, then dissolve 1 cup powdered sugar in 2 tablespoons lemon juice and put on cake while still hot.

title: rhubarb cake
directions: Butter bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Put in rhubarb.
Sprinkle over the top the dry jello, sugar and marshmallows.
Prepare cake mix as on package and pour over all in pan.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: italian cream cake icing
directions: Beat with mixer and spread over cake.

title: cooked cabbage
directions: Cook bacon.
Remove bacon, reserving fat.
Add chopped cabbage.
Add salt, pepper or spices to taste.
Mix well, then add a little water.
Cover and steam until done.

title: baked beans
directions: Taste to see if you have enough stuff to taste.
Fry bacon crisp.
Add a few drippings to beans.
Crunch bacon over top.

title: german chocolate refrigerator cake
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch pan, bake cake mix per package directions. While cake is warm, punch holes in top.
Pour Eagle Brand milk over top.
Spoon caramel sauce on top.
When cake is completely cool, spread with Cool Whip and sprinkle with nuts.
Refrigerate.

title: banana cake
directions: Cream sugar and Crisco.
Add eggs, beating well.
Add milk and vanilla, then dry ingredients.
Add mashed bananas, beating well. Bake until done at 350°.

title: oriental slaw
directions: Saute sesame seeds in margarine. Break up Ramen noodles. Combine all together, except for onion and last 3 ingredients. Blend together the last 3 ingredients; pour over the noodle mixture the day before. Add onion (chopped) just before serving.

title: sweet sour baked beans
directions: Cook onions, sugar, garlic powder, mustard, salt and vinegar in covered skillet for 20 minutes.
Add to beans and crumbled bacon. Mix.
Pour into 3-quart pan or casserole.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: mama's corn pudding
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients.
Beat together remaining ingredients and add to corn mixture.
Pour into greased (buttered) shallow casserole.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes, and 350° for 20 minutes or until custard is set.
Sprinkle with 1/3 cup bread crumbs.

title: fake thanksgiving turkey
directions: Mix all ingredients well and pour into greased bread pan and sprinkle top lightly with Kellogg's poultry seasoning.

title: goldie thomas' spiced peach congeal
directions: Dissolve 1 package of gelatine in 1/2 cup cold water.
Follow jello package instructions to dissolve jello.
Add gelatine mixture and dissolved jello to peach syrup.
Cool until it begins to thicken.
Stir in peaches, celery and nuts.
Refrigerate until firm.

title: five can casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and put in casserole pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Sprinkle top with cereal or potato chips (I use potato chips).

title: pecan pie(a not so sweet version)
directions: Cream butter to soften.
Add sugar gradually and cream until fluffy.
Add syrup and salt; beat well.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating thoroughly after each one.
Stir in pecans.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake in a moderate 350° oven for 50 minutes.

title: vegetable salad
directions: Drain all vegetables and mix together in a large bowl.
In pan, mix the sugar, vinegar and oil.
Boil and pour over vegetables. Toss and cover.
Marinate overnight. Serve chilled.

title: date pudding
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients together.
Boil for 5 minutes. Cool.

title: divinity fudge
directions: Place sugar, syrup and water in pan over slow flame.
Stir only until sugar is dissolved.
Then cook until a soft ball forms (236°).
Beat egg whites at #8 speed until stiff.
Continue beating.
Pour 1/2 of the syrup slowly over beaten egg whites. Cook rest of syrup until it forms a hard ball when dropped in a cup of cold water, until it cracks when hit against the side of a cup (280°).
Add syrup gradually to the syrup and egg mixture.
Add vanilla and keep heating until candy is thick enough to drop from spoon.
Place the spoonfuls in buttered platters.
Makes 35 to 40 pieces.
Nuts may be added, if desired, just before candy is ready to spoon.

title: homemade hot chocolate mix
directions: Use 2 scoops to one cup of boiling water.

title: beef and broccoli
directions: Slice beef across the grain into thin strips.
In skillet, add oil.
Cook beef until browned, stirring often.
Remove from pan. In skillet, cook broccoli and onion.
Add garlic, stirring often until tender.
Add soup, water and soy sauce.
Heat to boiling. Return beef to skillet.
Heat through, stirring occasionally.

title: pull candy
directions: Boil slowly until 256°; do not stir at all when it starts to boil.
Let boil slowly until it reaches 256°.
Pour on well buttered slab of marble (cool).
Let mixture cool until you can handle.
Butter hands and pull until it loses its gloss.
Pull into strips and cut into pieces.
Store in airtight container.
I use a heavy 8-quart pan.
Good luck!

title: strawberry congealed salad
directions: Mix strawberry jello, boiling water and crushed pineapple with juice.
Add strawberries.
If you like, add bananas to this.
Mix and congeal.

title: millionaires pie
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Pour into pie shells.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: potato souffle
directions: Mix together first 7 ingredients and put in baking dish.
Make topping of brown sugar, pecans, flour and melted margarine.
Mix together and put on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: lemon lush
directions: Use Waverly crackers by Nabisco only.

title: george's cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Spread on greased 17 x 11 x 1-inch cookie sheet pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
(Will not look done). Cut while warm into 1 1/2-inch cookies.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash; drain and mash.
Add other ingredients, except butter and cracker crumbs.
Put in 2-quart casserole.
Top with cracker crumbs mixed with melted butter.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes in 350° oven.

title: flank steak
directions: Shake well or stir to blend all ingredients.
Pour over a flank steak in glass dish.
Marinate for 12 hours (approximately), turning meat.
Store in refrigerator.
Pour off marinade and save.
Grill steak approximately 10 minutes.
Slice thin.
Serve with green salad and scalloped potatoes.

title: somebody else's fruit salad
directions: Drain canned fruit, reserve juice.
Add small portion of reserved juice to the mix; stir, then add remaining juice.
Pour over combined fruit.
Chill.
Salad is more flavorful if prepared several hours before serving.

title: hot and sour soup
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients and cook until hot.
Stir cornstarch mixture into the hot soup to thicken.
Sprinkle with green onions to serve.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix flour and baking soda.
Combine butter, sugar and pudding in large mixing bowl until creamy.
Beat eggs and add.
Gradually add flour and baking soda mixture, then stir in oats and raisins. (Batter will be stiff.)
Drop by rounded teaspoon onto slightly greased baking sheet, about 2 inches apart.
Bake at 325° for 10 to 12 mintues.
Cool on rack.
Makes about 5 dozen.

title: spiced nuts
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Spread nuts in a pan.
Bake 6 minutes. Melt butter in skillet, stir in remaining ingredients.
Add heated nuts and toss to coat.
Return to pan and bake 5 minutes.

title: crescent roll appetizers
directions: Roll crescent rolls out and press on a large cookie sheet. Bake 10 minutes at 350°.
Let cool.
Blend cream cheese, Ranch dressing mix and milk; spread like icing on cooled crescents.

title: pretty party punch
directions: In a large pitcher or a punch bowl, mix together the juices and seltzer or club soda.
Stir in strawberries.
Add 2 handfuls of ice cream.

title: pumpkin cake roll
directions: In a mixing bowl, beat eggs on high speed for 5 minutes. Gradually beat in granulated sugar.
Stir in pumpkin and lemon juice.
In a small bowl, stir together flour, cinnamon, baking powder, ginger, salt and nutmeg.
Fold into pumpkin mixture.

title: velveeta fudge
directions: In a heavy saucepan, heat cheese, chocolate and corn syrup together over medium to low heat.
Stir constantly until mixture becomes very hot and all is melted and well blended.
Remove from heat and use electric mixer to gradually add powdered sugar. After all sugar is added, continue to beat until smooth.
Add nuts and vanilla.
Pour mixture into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Smooth surface with spatula.
Cover and refrigerate until serving.
Cut into small squares.
Very rich and delicious.

title: ham loaf
directions: Mix and mold into loaf.
Bake 1 hour at 375°.
Remove from oven and pour drained, crushed pineapple over loaf.
Return to oven and bake 1 hour longer.
Baste with the pineapple juice.

title: wonton appetizers
directions: Brown sausage and onion and drain. In paper towel, remove as much grease as you can from meat.

title: simply super strawberry jello
directions: Mix up dry jello in a large bowl using hot water and the 5 ice cubes, stirring until ice is dissolved.
Spoon entire carton of sour cream into jello and whip it in with an electric mixer until smooth.
Jello will be a pink and white speckled color.
Pour mixture into 8-inch square or round pan, then chill.
Wash and hull the berries and slice in half.
When jello is completely firm, place berries, cut side down, on top and serve.

title: christmas present fudge
directions: Combine
sugar,
margarine
and milk in pan; bring to a rolling
boil, stirring constantly. Boil 5 minutes over medium heat, stirring constantly. Remove from heat, stir in chocolate bits
until
melted.
Add Marshmallow Creme, nuts and vanilla; stir
until
well blended.	Pour into greased 13 x 9-inch pan. Cool.

title: pistachio cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together until thick (I do 2 minutes). Bake in greased tube pan at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes.

title: meatballs(michael's favorite)
directions: In large bowl mix together hamburger, eggs, salt, pepper, onion and garlic salts, bells seasoning and chopped onion.
Use 1 package (roll) of Ritz crackers, broken up fine.
Mix with bread crumbs.
Melt margarine in small pan on top of stove and mix all together.
Cook in crock-pot on low for 3 to 4 hours, depending on amount you're making.
After 1 1/2 hours add sauce of your choice.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Beat together and mold into small patties. Fry until brown on each side.

title: easy chicken and dressing
directions: Remove bones from chicken.
Melt butter in broth while it's hot.
Crumble cornbread in large bowl and mix all ingredients together.
Press into baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: pumpkin cookies
directions: Combine flour, oats, baking soda, cinnamon and salt; set aside.
Cream butter.
Add sugar.
Beat light; add eggs and vanilla.
Mix.
Chill dough.
Drop on baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: buttered carrots
directions: Bring water, sugar and salt to boil.
Add raisins and carrots. Cover and cook until tender.
Stir in butter.
Makes 4 servings.

title: orange sunbeams(no sugar)
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and salt into mixing bowl.
Cut in butter until particles are fine. Stir in raisins.
Blend egg, orange rind, orange juice and liquid sweetener.
Sprinkle over mixture while stirring with fork until dough holds together. Shape dough into balls using a teaspoonful for each.
Place on cookie sheets. Flatten to about 1/4-inch with fork dipped in flour. Bake in moderate oven at 375° for about 12 to 15 minutes. Makes about 2 1/2 dozen cookies.
Each cookie contains 55 calories.

title: diabetic bar
directions: Boil prunes and raisins in 1 cup water for 5 minutes.
Cream rest of ingredients together.
Add fruit; mix together well. Grease and flour a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: dilly ryes
directions: Combine cream cheese and dry Ranch mix with mixer until well blended.
Spread a small amount of cheese mixture on slices of party rye.
Top each slice of spread bread with a thin slice of unpeeled cucumber.
Sprinkle each slice of cucumber with a small amount of dill weed.

title: dill dip
directions: Mix all ingredients; chill and serve.

title: herman cake
directions: Mix above and pour over top of dough.
Use a fork to swirl batter.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: beef or venison jerky(dehydrator method)
directions: Mix ingredients in glass or ceramic bowl.
Cut approximately 4 pounds of meat into 1/8-inch to 1/4-inch thick strips.
Place meat into marinade solution.
Cover with plastic wrap and refrigerate for 10 hours.
Remove and follow manufacturer's instructions for dehydration.

title: hamburger curry
directions: Saute the onion and garlic in butter in a skillet.
Add the ground beef; brown well.
Stir in the remaining ingredients. Cover and simmer for 25 minutes.
Serve with rice.

title: layered brunch salad
directions: In a small bowl, mix sour cream and mayonnaise until well blended.
Set aside.

title: rich onion soup
directions: In large kettle, cook onions with butter and oil over low heat for 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add sugar and mustard. Cook 30 minutes longer.
Blend in flour.
Stir in broth and wine. Cook 30 minutes more.
Season to taste.

title: zucchini patties
directions: Press all liquid from zucchini.
Mix all ingredients in order. Fry in oil until brown and cheese melts.

title: spiced coffee
directions: Heat water, brown sugar, cinnamon, orange peel and allspice to boiling; strain.
Pour liquid over coffee in heatproof container and stir until coffee is dissolved.
Makes 6 servings of 1/3 cup each.

title: peanut crispies
directions: Measure 1/2 cup sugar and 1/2 cup Karo syrup.
Stir and bring to boil over medium heat.
Add peanut butter and chow mein noodles.
Take pan off stove and stir.
Drop by spoon on wax paper.
Cool.
Share with a friend.

title: catfish cakes
directions: Poach or bake catfish fillets.
Drain and refrigerate.
Flake cooled fish into large mixing bowl.
Add eggs, potato, onion, parsley, hot pepper sauce, garlic, salt, pepper and basil and mix well.
Shape into 8 patties.
Coat with cracker crumbs.
Heat small amount of oil in a large skillet.
Cook patties, a few at a time, until browned and heated through.
Serve with tartar sauce, if desired.

title: adam's pudding cones
directions: Prepare pudding according to directions. When pudding is thick, place in cone. Top with Cool Whip. Serve cone inside a cup but take cone out to eat.

title: spanish rice
directions: Brown together hamburger, rice and onion.
Drain grease.
Add tomato sauce and water.
Bring to a boil.
Turn down to low and cook for five minutes.
Remove from heat and let set for five more minutes.
Ready to eat.
This recipe will serve 5 people.

title: swedish meat balls
directions: Combine all ingredients except the soup, sour cream and salt and pepper and blend well.
Cover bowl and store in refrigerator for about 1 hour.
Shape into small balls about the size of a quarter.
Use bacon grease to fry meat balls. When all meat balls are browned, return meat balls to skillet.
Turn heat down low and add the soup and sour cream. Season with salt and pepper.
Cook until mixture is heated through.
Serve in chafing dish.

title: oven cube steak
directions: Mix soup and 1 can of water in large baking pan. Season cube steak with tenderizer and flour (put flour in a zip lock bag and shake). Place cube steak in pan. Bake at 400° for about 1 hour. Cook rice separate. Great over rice.

title: ida cook's hot milk cake
directions: Melt butter in whole milk.
While it's melting cream together eggs, sugar and vanilla.
Add to milk and butter mixture.
Beat well.
Add flour and baking powder.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.
Can be cupcakes, tube cake or layers.

title: icicles
directions: Take an ice tray and fill it with any type of juice.
Freeze for about 1 1/2 hours.
Take out and serve.

title: orange julius
directions: Blend ingredients in blender until frothy.

title: aunt rosa's hamburger soup
directions: Brown meat and onions until onions are tender.
Add remaining ingredients; bring to a boil, then simmer for 1 hour.

title: reuben loaf
directions: On half of each crescent roll, spread dressing.
Layer corned beef, Swiss cheese and sauerkraut.
Fold top over and pinch closed. Bake at 350° to 400° until golden brown, 10 to 15 minutes.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: fresh fruit pie
directions: Dissolve gelatin in warm water.
Stir in lemon extract, lemon peel and sugar.
Set aside.
Butter a 9-inch pie pan plate. Sprinkle graham cracker crumbs over bottom and sides of plate. Layer sliced peaches in the pie plate.
Top with 1/3 of gelatin mixture, then strawberries and blueberries.
Cover with remaining gelatin.
Refrigerate 2 to 4 hours or until set.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix thoroughly.
Put into loaf pan.
Cover with strip of bacon.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: peach jello dessert
directions: Combine crumbs, 1/4 cup sugar and butter.
Press firmly into bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan.
Chill 15 minutes.
Beat cream cheese and 1/4 cup sugar.
Gradually beat in milk.
Fold in whipped topping and spread evenly over crumb crust.
Top with peaches; chill.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Heat applesauce, margarine and soda.
Remove from stove and pour into large bowl.
Add sugar, spices and flour.
Beat with mixer at medium speed, gradually adding flour.
Stir in raisins and nuts.
Pour into greased and floured Bundt pan.
Bake 2 hours at 300°.
Cool in pan 20 minutes, remove and place on rack to finish cooling.

title: cashew chicken
directions: Sprinkle cornstarch over chicken; add soy sauce and let marinate for 15 minutes.
Heat 1 1/2 teaspoons oil; brown chicken and remove from skillet.
In same skillet, heat remaining oil; add onion and cashews and stir-fry until onion is tender.
Add mushrooms and garlic; stir-fry for 1 minute.
Return chicken to skillet; add water chestnuts and reserved liquid.
Cover and cook until heated through, one to two minutes.
Serve sprinkled with green onion.

title: light and fruity pie
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add ice cubes.
Stir until jello is thickened.
Remove any unmelted ice cubes.
Blend in Cool Whip.
Whip until smooth.
Chill if necessary until mixture will mold.
Pour in pie crust.
Chill 3 hours.

title: mexican dip(salsa)
directions: Carefully mix first 5 ingredients.
Mix olive oil and vinegar. Pour over vegetable mixture.
Refrigerate.
Needs to marinate several hours or overnight.
Drain off most of marinade before serving.
Will keep a week or so in the refrigerator.
Makes approximately 4 cups.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: frozen salad
directions: Mix together the pineapple and marshmallows.
Let sit.
Add the remaining ingredients.
Freeze and serve.

title: italian vegetable soup
directions: Brown beef in large heavy kettle; drain.
Add all ingredients, except cabbage and macaroni.
Bring to boil; lower heat and simmer 20 minutes.
Add cabbage and macaroni.
Bring to boil and simmer until vegetables are tender.
This dish is low in fat, sugar and salt.

title: banana and peanut butter salad
directions: Slice banana lengthwise and place on lettuce leaf.
Mix peanut butter and mayonnaise.
Spread over banana.

title: orange glazed sweet potatoes
directions: Mix sugars with cornstarch.
Add juice and cook until thickened, stirring constantly.
Add oleo.
Pour over potatoes in a casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: peanut butter brownies
directions: Melt chocolate and butter over boiling water.
Cool.
Add vanilla, sugar, eggs and peanut butter; mix, then add flour and baking powder.
Pour into greased 8 x 8-inch pan.
Bake 30 minutes at 375°.

title: crazy ass pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt stick of butter in an 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
In a bowl, mix 1/2 cup of sugar, flour, baking powder and salt (sift).
Pour milk over dry ingredients; stir.
Pour batter over melted butter.
Do not stir!
In another bowl, mix fruit and 1/2 cup of sugar.
Pour this over batter; do not stir. Bake until golden brown.

title: broccoli-rice casserole
directions: In skillet, brown rice, onion, pepper and celery.
Add remaining ingredients; pour into casserole dish and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix all of the above ingredients together.
Use either to brush on meat or add meat to the sauce.

title: chocolate ice cream
directions: Mix Eagle Brand milk with Cool Whip.
Add chocolate milk to fill freezer to desired depth.
Add vanilla.
Freeze as desired.

title: chicken and dressing casserole
directions: Place chicken in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix soup and cream together and pour over chicken.
Spread dressing on top.
Pour broth over dressing.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 minutes or until dressing is slightly brown.

title: citrus honey peas
directions: Drain peas.
Mix rind, juice, honey and butter powder.
Add peas; bring to a simmer.
Add pimento; simmer 3 minutes more. Serves 4.

title: fayetteville pizza
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Spread on party rye and broil until cheese is bubbling.

title: turtle cake
directions: Mix cake according to package directions.
Pour 1/2 of mixture on greased (Pam) 10 x 14-inch cake pan.
Bake 1/2 mixture at package heat for 10 minutes.

title: sweet and sour chicken
directions: Beat egg and add chicken.
Toss until coated.
Sprinkle with 1/4 cup cornstarch and toss until chicken is covered.

title: oyster dressing
directions: Grease a 8 inch x 8 inch or 9 inch x 9 inch pan.
Take one package of saltines and crush them into the bottom.
Cut oysters into small pieces and put them every 1 - 2 inches apart.
Cut small dabs of butter and put them every 1 - 2 inches apart opposite oysters.
Shake on some salt and pepper.
Pour on milk until this layer is saturated and mushy.
Repeat layers until you run out of oysters.
Pour oyster juice on top layer and really saturate the whole casserole with milk.
Put in 350 degree oven and bake for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Pull it out when the top is brown and puffy.
Serve immediately.

title: baked acorn with apples
directions: Cut squash in half; scoop out seeds.
Fill center with apples. Place in baking dish containing 1/4 cup water.
Cover and bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until partially done.
Remove from oven and sprinkle with salt, sugar and nutmeg.
Dot with butter.
Bake, uncovered, 45 minutes longer or until squash and apples are tender.
Yields 4 servings.

title: sweet pickle
directions: Note:
You will need one large container.

title: easy cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients well. Drop by spoonfuls on greased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes. Add chocolate chips or nuts to batter for variations.

title: tasty tuna casserole
directions: Turn on oven and set at 350°.
Crush potato chips in a plastic bag to make 3/4 cup.
Butter the inside of a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
In a small bowl, mix mushroom soup, salt and milk.
Drain tuna and arrange in bottom of a casserole dish.
Pour soup mixture over tuna.
Sprinkle crushed potato chips over soup.
If desired, also sprinkle grated Cheddar cheese over top.
Bake for 25 minutes.

title: family favorite potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes in skin, drain, cool and peel.
Boil eggs, cool and peel.
Chop onion, pickles, eggs and potatoes.	Add salt and pepper to taste.
Mix all ingredients with mayonnaise.
You can boil potatoes and eggs a day ahead, refrigerate, peel and chop later.
Serves 8-10.

title: molasses stack cake
directions: Beat shortening and sugar together until light.
Beat eggs in one at a time.
Add vanilla and molasses and mix well.
Sift flour with cinnamon, ginger, cloves and nutmeg.
Add to shortening mixture alternately with buttermilk.
Mix thoroughly; the dough should not be sticky.
Add more flour, if needed.

title: chicken bake
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients together.
Put chicken pieces in baking dish and pour mixture over top. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: strawberry trifle
directions: Bake cake as directed in 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Prepare pudding as directed.
When cake is cool, cut in half, then eighths.
Lay half of cake (8 pieces) in 2-quart serving bowl.
Layer half of thawed strawberries, half pudding, then repeat.
Chill 8 hours.

title: sugar-free cookies(diabetic)
directions: Mix flour and baking powder; cream butter and gelatin, beating well.
Beat in egg and vanilla.
Gradually add flour mixture. Roll out dough and cut into shapes.
Bake at 400° for about 8 minutes.
Yields 5 dozen.

title: heart of palm lettuce
directions: Combine and toss lightly with:

title: stuffed cherry tomatoes
directions: Prepare by washing, removing the tops and scooping out the insides of tomatoes.
Stuff with Curry Cheese Spread or the cheese mixture for Stuffed Brussels Sprouts.

title: cream of crab soup
directions: Pick crab meat.
Melt butter in pot.
Remove from heat and blend in flour, salt, pepper and mustard.
Add milk and return to heat.
Heat until thickened, stirring constantly.
Add onion and crab meat.
Heat on low 15 to 20 minutes.

title: kraut salad
directions: Boi sugar, vinegar and let cool.
Mix all the ingredients. Store in refrigerator.
Stir a couple of times a day.
Best second day to eat.

title: nutty honey whole wheat bread
directions: Set aside 1 cup flour.
In large bowl, mix remaining flour, walnuts and yeast.
Heat milk, water, honey and margarine until hot (125° to 130°).
Stir into dry mixture, stir in only enough reserved flour to make soft dough.
On lightly floured surface, knead until smooth and elastic, about 8 to 10 minutes.

title: potato soup
directions: Put potatoes, celery, onions and margarine in large pot. Adjust enough water to come to surface of mixture.
Cook until tender (approximately 30 minutes).
Add margarine, half and half and cubed Velveeta (reduce heat).
Do not boil mixture after adding cheese and cream.
If soup is thinner than desired, add a few instant potato flakes to thicken.

title: jello vegetable salad
directions: Drain pineapple.
The juice can be used as part of the cold water if desired.
Just reduce cold water by the amount of pineapple juice.
Make jello.
Chill until partially set.
Add pineapple and vegetables.
Chill until firmly set.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Dice up artichokes and mix well with other ingredients. Refrigerate well before serving.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Mix sugar and flour thoroughly.
Place pineapple and juice in saucepan, stir in sugar and flour and cook on medium heat until thick, stirring almost constantly.
Grease and flour 9x9 pan and turn pineapple mixture into pan.
Melt butter and mix with crushed crackers and grated cheese.
Pour evenly over the pineapple and heat in a 350 degree oven for 20-25 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: trash - party mix(microwave)
directions: Combine and melt peanut butter, butter and chocolate chips on High for 3 minutes, then blend in with Chex in a large bowl until Chex are covered. Pour 1/2 cup of powdered sugar in the bottom of a trash bag.
Pour in cereal and add remaining powdered sugar. Toss around until Chex are coated.

title: fruit smoothy and frozen pop
directions: Blend all ingredients in blender or food processor until smooth.
Drink as is, or freeze in popsicle molds or paper cups. Yields about 3 cups or 10 to 11 pops.

title: finger jello
directions: In a large bowl, mix gelatin and Jell-O.
Add boiling water and stir until dissolved.
Pour into cake pan and chill until firm.
Cut into shapes or squares.

title: dakota buffalo pie
directions: Season the meat cubes with salt, pepper and sage; dredge in 1/4 cup of flour.
Heat oil in a large skillet; brown the meat on all sides.
Using a slotted spoon, transfer meat to a heavy Dutch oven.
In the remaining oil in the skillet, saute onion, carrot, celery and potato until lightly browned.
Add vegetables to meat in Dutch oven.
Sprinkle remaining flour over drippings in skillet and cook, stirring, until lightly browned.
Stir in the broth, tomato puree, water, garlic, bay leaf, parsley, clove and thyme. Pour over meat and vegetables.

title: braised pork chops
directions: Fry pork chops in oil.
Brown on both sides.
Add onion, garlic powder, seasoning and enough water to cover bottom of pan to 1/2-inch.
Cover and simmer slowly for 10 minutes.
Add carrots and potatoes.
Simmer until done, adding more water, if needed.
Add barbecue sauce and simmer 5 more minutes.

title: turkey stuffing
directions: Pour melted butter over torn bread.
Mix greens, onions, boiling water and seasoning together.
Then add eggs.
Stir all ingredients and pour over bread.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: tortilla roll-ups
directions: In a food processor, chop green onions, jalapenos, black olives and Cheddar cheese.
Mix in cream cheese and sour cream. Spread mixture thinly and evenly over flour tortilla.
Roll tortilla up.
Wrap Tortilla Roll-Ups in damp paper towel and refrigerate until chilled.

title: she crab soup
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Add crabmeat and sherry last.
Bring to a boil.

title: taco dip
directions: Mix together cream cheese and taco seasoning.
Spread on bottom of pan or dish.
Then top with lettuce, tomatoes and Cheddar cheese.
Add any other salad toppings you like.
Dip with nacho chips.

title: pineapple pudding
directions: Mix together and boil until thick.
Let set until cool.
Add pineapple and Cool Whip; then refrigerate.

title: hot german potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes; peel and slice. Chop onion and saute in oil and butter. Place potatoes in baking dish. Place sauteed onions, cup of water, vinegar, sugar, flour, salt and pepper in a bowl; mix. Pour over potatoes and bake in 325° oven for 1 hour.

title: baked egg
directions: Cut foil into 12 x 18-inch pieces.
Double fold foil into 9 x 12-inch pieces.
Place egg in center of foil and twist excess foil, sealing in the egg.
Place in coals.
Turn frequently, about every minute.
Test after 5 minutes.
If it is too soft, reseal and put back on coals for another minute or two.
If egg is too hard, your fire is too hot.
Try again, but cut time down to 3 or 4 minutes.

title: cherry cream pie
directions: Mix cream cheese, sugar and Cool Whip together with mixer. Mix well. Put mixture into pie crust. Spread to fill crust. Put 1 cup cherry filling on top. Let set for about 3 hours in the refrigerator.

title: cajun sausage and rice
directions: Bring 3 1/2 c. water to boil in a large saucepan.
Add rice mix; reduce heat, cover and simmer 10 minutes.
Meanwhile, heat oil in a large nonstick skillet.
Add peppers; saute over high heat 5 minutes.
Add sausage; saute 3 minutes until lightly browned.
Place mixture on rice (don't stir), cover and simmer 10 minutes until rice is tender.
Stir to mix; sprinkle with scallions.

title: thank you apple pie filling
directions: Cook all this together and add to apples.
Mix.
Put in jars, not too full and
seal.
Let pressure rise to 10 pounds. Turn off burner and let set
to 15 minutes or cold pack 15 minutes.

title: quick cottage cheese salad
directions: Mix jello and cottage cheese together. Add fruit and mix well. Add cool whip and mix again. Stir before serving. Best served when chilled.

title: mexican string beans
directions: Saute onion in oil. Add remaining ingredients. Simmer for about 10 minutes.

title: grilled ginger chicken breasts
directions: Arrange chicken breasts in a shallow 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Combine remaining ingredients in a small bowl. Mix well and pour over chicken. Cover and chill for 4 hours, turning every hour. Place chicken on rack and grill over hot coals for 5 minutes per side, basting twice with the marinade mixture. Transfer chicken to a warm platter and garnish. Garnish with cherry tomatoes and parsley.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: tamale pie
directions: Place tamales in casserole.
Sprinkle onion, corn chips, cheese and top with chili.
Layer in same order except cheese. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Top with cheese; let melt.

title: mushroom bake
directions: Saute mushrooms in butter.
Mix flour and soup mix with sour cream (will be thick) and add to mushrooms.
Mix well and heat through.

title: rice con queso(from "diet for a small planet")
directions: Combine rice, beans, garlic, onion and chilies.
In a casserole, repeat layers of rice, bean mix, Ricotta cheese and Monterey Jack cheese, ending with rice and beans.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Sprinkle grated Cheddar cheese over the top.

title: german caramel bars
directions: Combine cake mix, 1/2 cup evaporated milk and oil.
Blend well and spread 1/2 in lightly greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 6 minutes in a preheated 350° oven.

title: kentucky pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into pie shell.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.
Top should be hard and crunchy.
Serve warm.

title: banana pickles
directions: Peel pickles and
slice
lengthwise.
Make
a
brine of listed ingredients and bring
to a boil.
Pour over pickles in cans. Makes 5 quarts.
Cold pack 10 minutes.

title: cheese-topped pork chop casserole
directions: Brown pork chops on both sides in skillet.
Cook potatoes in 1 cup boiling water for 15 minutes, then drain well.
Spoon potatoes into lightly greased 13 x 9 x 1 1/2-inch baking dish.
Add half the onion and season with salt and pepper.
Arrange pork chops over potatoes, then sprinkle with remaining onion.
Spread soup evenly over top.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 30 minutes. Sprinkle cheese over top and bake for 30 minutes longer or until chops are tender.

title: easy caramel rolls
directions: Slightly thaw bread dough.
Cut into pieces and place in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix the other ingredients and heat until margarine melts, stirring until smooth.
Pour over bread dough.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
In morning, take out and let stand for 15 to 30 minutes.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Turn out on wax paper.

title: halloween pumpkin dip
directions: Combine softened cream cheese, pumpkin and sugar.
Blend until creamy.
Add nutmeg and ginger to taste and chill.

title: apple cake
directions: Cream shortening, add sugar and beaten eggs.
Add soda to applesauce, then alternate with flour, cocoa, and spices, sifted together.
Dredge raisins and nuts in flour, and fold in.
Bake in 350° for 45-50 minutes.

title: chicken pasta salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together thoroughly and chill.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix and stir in 1/2 cup mushroom soup and 1/2 cup milk.
Stir in 1/2 cup Pepperidge Farm Herb stuffing and sprinkle stuffing on top.
Dot with butter.
Bake at 400° for 20 or 25 minutes.

title: lemon pie
directions: Combine ingredients and cook over medium heat until thick and bubbly.
Pour into baked pie shell and cool.

title: avocado bread supreme
directions: Beat shortening and sugar together.
Add eggs, avocado, lime or lemon juice, flour, baking powder,
salt
and
pecans; blend. Pour into greased loaf pan and bake in 375° oven for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: tofu enchiladas or lasagna filling
directions: Place all ingredients in food processor and blend until smooth.
Stuff enchiladas.
Cover with sauce and bake or use as a lasagna filling in place of Ricotta cheese or stuff large shell noodles, cover with sauce and bake.

title: oatmeal pancakes
directions: Mix oatmeal and buttermilk together.
Beat in rest of ingredients.
Fry on hot griddle.
Makes about 12 4 inch pancakes. Can substitute powdered buttermilk for liquid buttermilk.
Mix the powder to equal 2 cups buttermilk into oatmeal.
Then add 2 Cups hot tap water and let it soak.

title: merk's coffee cake
directions: Grease two 8-inch pans or one 13 x 9-inch pan.
Pour dough into pan.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Preheat oven to 375°; bake bottom pie shell.
Cook chicken, soup and Veg-All.
Pour into baked pie shell; cover with second pie shell and poke holes in the top shell.
Bake until top shell is golden brown.
Serve.
This recipe will serve 5 people.

title: easy broccoli salad
directions: Break broccoli and cauliflower into flowerets and chop into bite size pieces.
Chop tomatoes and onion.
Pour any dressing over mixture.
Italian is best.
Let marinate several hours or overnight.
Keeps well for several days in refrigerator.

title: cherry topped cheese cake
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Measure one cup dry cake mix; set aside.
In large bowl, stir remaining cake mix, one egg and oil. Mixture will be crumbly.
Press mixture evenly into 9 x 13-inch greased pan.

title: pepper steak
directions: Pound flour into meat.
Brown meat in shortening.
Pour off fat.
Add soup and ketchup.
Cover and simmer one hour.
Stir and add green pepper.
Cook 20 minutes longer or until peppers are tender.
I also add 1 cup of instant rice when I add pepper.

title: cream cheese cookies
directions: Cream together oleo and cream cheese; add flour.
Form into small balls by hand.
Flatten and add small amount of jelly in center.
Pinch up cookies toward the center.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes on ungreased cookie sheet.
Remove from oven.
Place on cookie rack (with wax paper underneath) and sprinkle on powdered sugar, through a sieve.

title: presbyterian punch
directions: Boil sugar and water for 10 minutes.
Add the pineapple and lemon juice.
Just before serving, add the ginger ale.
Use finely crushed ice.
This serves 25 to 30.

title: slaw
directions: Mix dressing together; simmer for 15 minutes.
Put a tablespoon of salt on the chopped cabbage and let stand for 1 hour.
Squeeze juice out of cabbage.
Add chopped celery and mango.
Pour lukewarm dressing over cabbage, mango and celery.

title: ma's cole slaw
directions: Shred cabbage.
Dice tomato, cucumber and onion.
Add Miracle Whip, salt and pepper.
Mix well.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix dry ingredients together for stuffing.

Tear or cut chicken into small pieces and put on bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan. Add your stuffing on top of chicken. Mix soups together with broth and pour over stuffing, making sure it is evenly moist. Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: yum-yum casserole
directions: Brown hamburg and onion.
Add soups, rice, celery, water and soy sauce.
Turn into a buttered casserole.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serve over noodles.

title: zucchini corn muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Coat inside of 16 medium size muffin cups with nonstick cooking spray.
Shred zucchini.
Place in colander over bowl.
Sprinkle with salt.
Set aside.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Combine gelatin and boiling water.
Add bananas and remaining ingredients.
Mold and refrigerate.
Serves 8 to 10 people.

title: snicker's salad
directions: Cut up Snickers bars and apples in bite size pieces.
Mix together.
Add marshmallow cream and Cool Whip.
Mix all ingredients well.
Chill before serving.

title: lemonade pie
directions: Blend and spoon carefully into pie crusts.
Chill.
Keeps 1 week in refrigerator.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Refrigerate 2 hours.
Hollow out pumpernickel bread.
Place dip in center.
Place extra pieces around sides for dipping.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Layer in a casserole in order given and bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour.
Serves 4 to 6 people.

title: posse stew
directions: In a skillet, brown ground beef and onion; drain.
Stir in tomatoes, beans, chilies, hominy and corn.
Season with salt and pepper.
For a thicker stew, combine cornstarch and water, then stir into stew.
Cook and stir until thickened.

title: new york cheese cake
directions: To cream cheese, add sugar gradually while beating.
Add eggs and beat until smooth.
Stir in lemon, vanilla, flour and cornstarch.
Add butter and mix until smooth.
Blend in sour cream.

title: strawberry pie glaze
directions: Cook mixture at medium heat until thickened.
Pour over strawberries in pie shell.
Chill.

title: fried wild turkey
directions: Slice turkey breast
in 1/4-inch thick slices or thicker, if desired.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Soak turkey slices in buttermilk for 2
or
minutes.
While turkey is soaking, heat vegetable oil in frying pan.
Roll turkey in flour.
Drop in heated
oil
and
fry until golden brown.
(Do not overcook.) Drain on paper towel.

title: corn sticks
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Combine eggs, water, sugar and salt. Mix cornmeal, flour and baking powder.
Add shortening.
(Bacon drippings are best for shortening.) Pour into corn stick molds and bake for 20 minutes.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Combine apples and sugar in a large mixing bowl.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Sift flour.
Add soda, salt, cinnamon, nutmeg and allspice; set aside.
Blend oil and egg into apple sugar mixture. Add dry ingredients, stirring just until blended.
Fold in raisins and nuts.
Spread evenly in greased 8-inch square pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: hickory hill spoon bread
directions: Pour boiling water over meal and shortening.
Let cool.
Add milk and beaten eggs.
Then add salt and baking powder last.
Pour into a greased pan and bake at 400° for 1/2 hour.

title: versatile refrigerator cookies
directions: Mix the shortening, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Stir in the dry ingredients.
Divide dough in half and roll in a roll.
Wrap in wax paper.
Put in refrigerator and bake whenever you want. Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: willey's stew
directions: Do not dilute soup.
Mix all ingredients together and place in casserole dish.
Cover and bake at 300° for 2 1/2 to 3 hours. Serve over rice or noodles.

title: pistachio cake
directions: Blend the above ingredients for 2 minutes.
Grease and flour Bundt pan.
Pour batter into pan and bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes, or until done.
Frost with Pistachio Frosting (see recipe).

title: aunt melba's deluxe tortellini soup
directions: Remove casing from sausage and brown; add onions and garlic and saute.
Add beef broth, water, tomatoes, celery, basil, parsley, oregano, green pepper and soup.
Simmer for 40 minutes. Add tortellini and zucchini and boil for another 30 minutes. Serve with Parmesan cheese and breadsticks.

title: tuna croquettes
directions: Mix tuna, soup, bread crumbs, onions, egg and lemon juice. Shape into croquettes.
Makes 8.
Brown in skillet.

title: dill dip for vegetables
directions: Mix all ingredients until well blended.
Tastes best if you let stand, covered, in refrigerator overnight.
Makes 2 cups of dip.

title: cabbage soup
directions: Put cut up cabbage in large pan.
Cover with water.
Boil until cabbage starts to get tender.
Add potatoes, onion and green pepper.
Also add corn, stewed tomatoes, green beans, tomato soup and hamburg.
Cook until potatoes are tender.

title: caramel pie
directions: Beat egg whites and cream of tartar until stiff.
Combine sugar and vanilla; beat until stiff.
Spread over pie.
Bake at 275° until lightly browned.

title: caramel corn
directions: Boil sugar, margarine and molasses for 4 minutes.
Remove from heat and stir in 1/2 teaspoon soda.
Pour over popped corn and mix well.
Bake at 200° for 1 hour in large shallow pans.
Stir every 15 minutes.

title: scones
directions: Mix together flour, sugar, baking powder, soda and a dash of salt.
Cut in margarine until mixture resembles coarse crumbs. Make a well in the center.
In a separate bowl, mix sour cream, raisins and egg yolk.
Add all at once to flour mixture.
Mix together with a fork.
Knead quickly 10 to 12 strokes.
Pat into a 7-inch circle.
Cut into 12 wedges.
Arrange on a cookie sheet 1-inch apart.
Brush with slightly beaten egg white.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes until light brown.

title: pimento cheese salad
directions: Mix
Jell-O,
salt,
hot water, mayonnaise, cold water, vinegar
and pimento cheese, beating well.
Cool.
Add celery, onion and
green
pepper.
To make a nice luncheon dish, add 1 can shrimp.

title: corn pudding
directions: Combine flour and margarine, stirring to make a smooth paste. Add milk gradually.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: ground beef-rice casserole pie
directions: Add to the meat pie crust.
Cover with aluminum foil and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Check every 30 minutes.
Do not stir. Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: no bake cookies
directions: In large saucepan combine sugar, oleo, milk and cocoa.
Heat, stirring frequently, until mixture comes to a boil.
Boil 2 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Let cool one minute.
Stir in peanut butter, vanilla and salt; mix well.
Add oatmeal, nuts and coconut.
Drop by spoonfuls onto wax paper and let cool until hardened.
Makes 3 to 4 dozen.

title: rhubarb jam
directions: Mix together rhubarb and sugar; let sit overnight.
Bring to a boil until tender (5 minutes).
Remove from heat and add Jell-O and stir until dissolved.
Put in jars and seal with wax or lid.

title: corn muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Place 1/2 teaspoon oil in each cup or muffin tin.
Place in oven until hot.
Combine corn meal and sugar.
Combine milk and egg; add to dry ingredients; stir until smooth.
Pour batter into hot pan.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes.
Makes 12 large muffins or corn sticks.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mash potatoes and combine ingredients.
Put in a 2-quart casserole.

title: ritzy chicken
directions: Combine chicken, sour cream and soup in a 3-quart casserole dish.
Top with cracker crumbs combined with butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Cream sugar and oil.
Add eggs; beat well.
Combine dry ingredients and add to creamed mixture.
Fold in apple and nuts. Dough is very thick.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: garlic and herb pasta
directions: Cook pasta according to package directions; set aside.
In large skillet, over medium-high heat, cook garlic cloves in oil about 5 minutes until golden brown.
Reduce heat to low and add 1/2 can broth.
Cover and cook 10 minutes until garlic is tender. Using the back of a spoon, mash half of the garlic cloves.
Add remaining 1/2 can broth and rest of the seasonings and bring to a boil.
Add drained pasta; toss until well combined.
Season with salt and pepper to taste.
Serves 4.

title: seasoned salt
directions: Mix and store airtight.

title: chocolate covered cherries
directions: Mix together sugar, butter, salt, milk and vanilla.
Chill for 2 hours.
Drain cherries on paper towels.
Put small amount of mixture around cherries and chill.
Put chocolate chips in double boiler.
Melt chips and dip covered cherries.

title: chocolate angel food cake
directions: Slice off one-half inch of the top of cake and set aside.
Whip the cream, gradually adding sugar, then cocoa.
Hollow out cake, leaving an inch on sides and bottom.
Fill cavity with cream mixture.
Place piece back on top of cake and ice with the remaining cream.
Pecan meats may be added to the part in the cavity filling.

title: chess cake
directions: Mix all the above ingredients together and pour in a greased baking pan.

title: speedy spinach pie
directions: Combine eggs, sour cream, cheese and salt with a mixer.
Fold in onion rings and tuna.
Pour into pie shell and bake in a 350° oven for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: green bean almondine
directions: Drain juice from 3 cans of green beans and place in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Add last can, juice and all.
Add chopped onions, bacon and almonds.
Toss lightly.
Pour over vinegar and sugar mixture.
Place in refrigerator, covered, overnight.
Marinate for 18 to 24 hours.
Uncover and cook at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: lamb and string beans
directions: Saute chops in butter.
Add onions and garlic.
Add plum tomatoes and season; cook for 1/2 hour.
Then add potatoes and cook for another 15 minutes.
Then add string beans.
Cook until done (15 minutes or so).
Serve with Italian bread and a green salad.

title: honey mustard dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put in covered
Tupperware dish.
Let set in refrigerator for 2 hours.

title: granny decoster's green tomato mincemeat pie filling
directions: Wash, cut up green tomatoes and put through food chopper. Rinse in cold water and drain in colander.
Cook slowly in a large kettle for 2 hours in the vinegar and water.

title: twinkie surprise
directions: Cut Twinkies into halves lengthwise. Arrange, cream side up, in a 9 x 13-inch dish. Combine milk and pudding mix in a large bowl and beat until thick. Spread over Twinkies. Top with whipped topping and chopped candy. Chill for at least 1 hour.

title: fruit punch cake
directions: Beat eggs and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add rest of ingredients and pour into large, greased cake pan.
Bake at 350°.

title: banana cake
directions: Cream together sugar, butter and nutmeg until fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Stir in bananas and vanilla.
Combine flour, baking powder, soda and salt; beat into creamed mixture, alternating with buttermilk.
Stir in nuts.
Bake in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes, or until toothpick comes out clean.
Cool and frost with Cream Cheese Frosting.

title: cranberry wassail
directions: You will also need a spice bag. (Use coffee filter tied with twist tie.)

title: lazy lasagna
directions: Meat Sauce: Brown ground beef; drain. Add next 6 ingredients. Simmer 1 hour.

title: bourbon hot dogs
directions: Combine all ingredients in a crock-pot.
Simmer about 6 hours.

title: no-beat popovers
directions: Beat eggs into bowl; add milk, flour and salt.
Mix well with spoon (disregard lumps).
Fill very well-greased muffin pans 3/4 full.
Put in cold oven.
Set control to 450°.
Turn on heat.
Bake 30 minutes.
Makes 11 good-size popovers.
Don't peek!
(The secret is starting with a cold oven and not opening the oven for a full 30 minutes.)

title: mexicana tamale pie
directions: In large skillet, brown ground beef; drain.
Stir in taco seasoning, corn, tomatoes, peppers and 1 can onions; pour mixture into 2 quart casserole.
Prepare corn muffin mix according to package.
Spoon batter around edge of beef mixture.
Bake, uncovered, at 400° for 20 minutes or until corn bread is done.
Top corn bread with cheese and remaining onions; bake, uncovered, 1 minute until onions are golden brown.

title: diana's brownies
directions: Cook pudding.
Put cake mix in big bowl.
Pour pudding in mix. Use big spoon and stir in until moist and lumps out.
Add semi-sweet morsels.
Put in 9 x 13-inch greased and floured pan. Sprinkle with chips.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: shortcut lasagna
directions: Brown meat; drain off fat.
Cook noodles in boiling salted water; drain.
Combine egg, Parmesan, cottage cheese and meat.
In a 10 x 6 x 2-inch pan, layer half the noodles, meat mixture, Mozzarella and spaghetti sauce.
Repeat layers.
Bake, uncovered, at 375° for 50 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: pecan millionaires
directions: Melt caramels and milk in top of double boiler.
Stir in pecans.
Drop by teaspoonful onto cookie sheet which has been sprayed with Pam.
Freeze 1 hour.

title: one bowl chocolate cake
directions: Put all these dry ingredients together in mixing bowl and blend well.
Add cup of buttermilk and cup of oil.
Beat slowly and add eggs.
Beat well and add 1 cup boiling water.
The batter will be thin.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake in a 350°
oven for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: brunswick stew
directions: Brown the ground beef and sausage meat together.
Pour off excess fat.
Add all other ingredients and simmer.
Be sure to stir well while simmering because it will scorch easily.
Can eat when you are ready to eat it.

title: oven beef stew
directions: Cut beef and vegetables into 1-inch cubes.
Place all ingredients into a bean pot. Cover and cook at 300° for 3 hours.

title: baby ruth bars
directions: Bring sugar and syrup to a boil. Remove from heat.
Mix in peanut butter and cereal.
Press into buttered pan.
Melt chocolate and butterscotch bits in a double boiler.
Spread over first mixture. Cut into bars when hard.

title: pork roast
directions: Flour roast and brown in oil in pan.
Drain sauerkraut.
Wash in colander.
Press to dry.

title: sugar-free peach pie
directions: Slice peaches and mix with remaining ingredients.
Pour into 9-inch or 10-inch unbaked pie shell.
Cover and slit top crust. Cook about 1 hour at 425° until bubbly.

title: orange salad
directions: Dissolve jello in 1 cup boiling water.
Add orange sherbet. Stir until sherbet dissolves and jello thickens.
Add all the rest of the ingredients.
Stir and let congeal.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix first six ingredients, cover and chill for 2 hours. Hollow out bread and reserve bread chunks for dipping.
Serve dip in hollowed bread.

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: Melt margarine and cocoa together.
Remove from heat and stir in sugar and eggs.
Mix well.
Add flour, salt, nuts and vanilla. Mix well.
Spoon batter into a well-greased pan (13 x 9 x 2-inch). Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.
Sprinkle marshmallows on top of warm cake.
Frost with a chocolate frosting.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Drain green beans and mushrooms.
Place in a greased 9 x 13-inch dish.
Stir in cream of mushroom soup.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Top with onions and bake 15 minutes more.

title: cook-out potatoes
directions: Fry bacon until crisp; drain and crumble.
Peel and slice potatoes thin and sprinkle with salt and pepper to taste.
Put potatoes on large piece of foil.
Slice onion thin and put on potatoes.
Sprinkle with crumbled bacon.
Cut cheese in small cubes and dot over potato mixture.
Dot potatoes with butter.
Wrap tightly in foil and seal edges.
Cover over hot coals for 1 hour. Turn several times during cooking.

title: hot cranberry punch
directions: Mix cranberry, pineapple and lemonade.
Heat until very hot. Add ginger ale and serve.

title: judson casserole
directions: Grease casserole dish.
Slightly brown hamburger in skillet. Layer sliced potatoes and onions in casserole dish.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Sprinkle hamburger over layers of potatoes and onions. Salt and pepper meat to taste.
Spread cream of mushroom soup over hamburger.
Bake at 350 degrees for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
(Time varies...cook until desired tenderness.)

title: cheese ball
directions: Shape into ball and roll in paprika.
Serve with crackers such as Wheat Thins.

title: mandarin orange cake
directions: Mix ingredients together lightly.
Do not beat.
Bake in 4 layers at 325° in 8 or 9-inch layer cake pans for 15 minutes.
Let completely cool.

title: joe's chili
directions: Brown meat and saute onion.
Drain excess grease; add other ingredients and cook until done (about 1 1/2 hours).
(Joe cooks his all day in slow cooker.)
Chili meat may take longer to cook than hamburger meat...so just be sure your meat is done.

title: yeast rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Pour boiling water over butter, sugar, cold water, egg and yeast.
Stir.
Add flour and salt. Knead and place in greased bowl.
Let rise until double in bulk. Knead and shape into rolls or loaf.
Let rise again and bake for 20 minutes at 350°.
Brush with butter after removing from oven.

title: ham loaf
directions: Mix and bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: surprisingly good oriental veal and sprouts(6 servings)
directions: Brown meat in 2 tablespoons hot oil.
Add onions and garlic; saute about 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Sprinkle flour over mixture, stirring until blended.
Add soy sauce.
Cover and cook about 15 minutes.
While meat cooks, stir-fry bean sprouts in 1 tablespoon oil to heat.
Serve meat with sauce on bed of sprouts.

title: eveready bran muffins
directions: Mix together dry ingredients, including cereal and set aside. Beat eggs and add oil and buttermilk. Add liquid mixture to dry mixture until just moistened. Refrigerate overnight.

title: grandma's tea cakes
directions: Mix ingredients, except flour.
Add enough flour for stiff dough.
Put in refrigerator overnight.
Roll thin (cut out) and leave plain.
Bake at 325° until light brown.

title: grossmommy's oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream sugar
and
lard;
add eggs, vanilla and coconut. Add flour,
oatmeal,
baking
soda and baking powder.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes or until done.

title: peanut butter candy
directions: Make dough out of ingredients.
Roll out and spread with peanut butter.
Roll up, slice and refrigerate.

title: squash casserole 2
directions: Mix soup, sour cream, onion and cooked squash.
Melt margarine in a baking pan.
Layer the squash mixture into buttered pan. Place 1 layer of stuffing on top.
Bake at 325° for 20 minutes.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Wipe mushrooms with damp cloth.
Remove stems from caps.
Chop up stems very fine.
Saute onion and garlic in oil and butter for 1 minute.
Add chopped stems and parsley, then salt and pepper. Add bread crumbs and toss lightly; set aside.
Brown mushroom caps 1 minute in butter.
Stuff caps.
Place in baking dish.
Dot with butter and broil for 5 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: gooseberry salad
directions: Heat water.
Add jello, juice, sugar and gooseberries.
Cool. When slightly congealed, add celery and nuts.
Mold.

title: 5 cup salad
directions: Just mix the ingredients all together, chill and serve with cookies or a nut bread.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix
onion,
beaten
eggs and seasonings together.
Add squash,
boiled
for 5 minutes or until tender.
Grease casserole dish
with oleo; mix oleo and crackers in separate bowl. Sprinkle buttered
crumbs
on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes until brown.

title: marinated mushrooms
directions: In a small saucepan, combine all ingredients.
Bring to a boil for 5 to 6 minutes.
Cool; chill for several hours.
Serve with favorite meat or as a relish garnish.

title: mother's fruit salad
directions: Combine ingredients and mix with cooked dressing.

title: mexican pinwheel appetizers
directions: Put the salsa in a strainer and set aside to drain for 10 minutes.
Transfer drained salsa to a blender.
Add cream cheese, Cheddar cheese, onion and hot pepper sauce.
Mix until smooth. Spread mixture over tortillas and roll into cylinders.
Wrap in plastic wrap.
Refrigerate at least 2 hours.
Cut into thin slices.
Makes 4 dozen bite-size pieces.

title: carrot copper pennies
directions: Cook carrots until tender.
Add soup, green pepper, onion, vinegar, salad oil, sugar, mustard, Worcestershire sauce, salt and pepper to taste.
Chill.

title: cucumber sandwiches
directions: Cream together cream cheese, sour cream and dressing mix. Spread on bread.
Peel and slice cucumbers.
Put slice on bread and sprinkle with dill weed.

title: eggplant roll-ups
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Peel eggplants and slice lengthwise into approximately 8 (1/4-inch thick) slices.
In a large frying pan, heat oil and brown slices on both sides.
Add more oil as needed. To make eggplant rolls, fold slices of ham in half lengthwise and place one on each slice of browned eggplant.
In small bowl, mix Ricotta, garlic and parsley.
Spoon the cheese mixture on top of ham; spread evenly to the edges.
Top with slice of Mozzarella. Roll eggplant and place, seam side down, in baking dish.
Makes approximately 16 rolls.
Spoon tomato sauce over rolls and sprinkle with cheese.
Bake 30 minutes.

title: raisin spread
directions: Break eggs in a thick pan; beat eggs and sugars.
Add lemon juice.
Cook until thick.
Mix nuts and raisins; then stir in mayonnaise.
Pour mixture over.
Keep in refrigerator.
Spread over crackers, bread, etc.
Good for a quick snack.

title: busy day cobbler
directions: Melt margarine in a 2-quart baking dish.
Sift and mix flour and sugar together.
Add milk to the bowl and mix.
Pour into middle of melted butter.
Top with one can of pie filling.
Your choice.
Sprinkle 1/2 cup sugar on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: salted eye of round
directions: Tear off a piece of waxed paper, large enough to completely wrap the roast.
Use two sheets if necessary.
Place wax paper on countertop.
Place roast in center and pour the kosher salt over the meat.
Use your hands to spread the salt evenly over both sides of the meat until it's completely covered and white.
Don't be afraid of too much salt.
Wrap meat as completely as you can so that all the salt stays inside the wrapper.
Be careful. Place the wax papered meat directly on hot coals.
Stand back!
The wax paper will immediately flame up and burn away.
Leave the grill cover off.
Let the meat cook for 35 to 40 minutes on one side, then flip the meat over and cook for 30 to 35 minutes more on the second side.
Do not cover grill.

title: macaroni pizza style
directions: Brown beef and onion.
Stir in cooked macaroni.
Mix water, tomato sauce and seasonings.
Mix all together and pour into 13 x 9-inch pan.
Top with cheese, then pepperoni.
Pour pizza sauce on and spread.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: dean barnes' pralines
directions: All at one time boil over low heat for 15 minutes or until forms soft ball in cool water.
Drop on wax paper.

title: sour cream coconut cake
directions: Cook yellow cake mix as directed in round cake pans.
When cool, split layers in half.
Mix sugar with sour cream; add coconut to desired consistency.
Spread in between all layers. (Refrigerate.)

title: pineapple pie
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients in saucepan; add pineapple.
Cook until clear and thick on very low heat, 6 to 8 minutes, stir occasionally.
Mix a little pineapple at a time to egg yolks very slowly, cook 1 minute.
Cool slightly and add lemon juice.
Pour in baked pie shell and top with meringue; seal well.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Mix as listed. Pour in pie plate (ungreased). Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes, until golden brown. Will be congealed when cooled.

title: shove in the oven tuna dish
directions: Drain peas, reserve liquid.
Cook potatoes, carrots and onion in this liquid for 8 to 10 minutes.
Drain and save liquid.
Melt butter in saucepan; stir in flour to make a smooth paste.
Add milk to vegetable liquid to make 2 cups.
Add to butter mixture; cook over low heat; stir until mixture thickens.
Add seasonings. Combine veggies and tuna in buttered 2 quart casserole.
Pour sauce over all.
May be refrigerated overnight.
To serve, bake covered in slow oven at 325° for 1 hour.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: zucchini and tomato
directions: Melt butter and saute green peppers and onions.
Add zucchini, bread crumbs, Parmesan cheese, salt and pepper.
Turn into 1 1/2-quart covered casserole.
Bake at 375 degrees for 20 minutes.
Add tomatoes and bake 10 minutes more.
Melt Cheddar cheese on top and serve.

title: pecan pie bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix flour and 2 tablespoons brown sugar in bowl with hands.
Work in 1/2 cup butter until dough holds together.
Pat into 9-inch pan.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes.

title: barbecue
directions: Simmer all ingredients except ground beef for 15 minutes.
Add ground beef and simmer until beef is done.

title: sliced zucchini pickles
directions: Bring vinegar, sugar, salt and spices to a boil; pour over zucchini and onions and let stand one hour.
Bring to a boil; cook three minutes.
Pack in hot jars; adjust lids.
Process in boiling water, 212°, for 5 minutes.
Remove jars and complete seals. Makes 6 to 7 pints.

title: pretzel strawberry salad
directions: Mix together the crushed pretzels, melted margarine and 3 tablespoons sugar.
Pat into a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Mix together the cream cheese, 1 cup sugar and whipped topping; spread this mixture over pretzels.
Mix gelatin into boiling water; add frozen berries.
Stir until dissolved; set aside to thicken.
Spoon over cream cheese mixture; garnish with strawberries.

title: dill pickles
directions: Heat the first 4 ingredients to boiling.
In the bottom of each jar, put 1 clove of garlic and 1 teaspoon of dill seed.
Pour water and vinegar mixture over pickles and seal.
Use hot water bath for a few minutes.
Let sit for 4 weeks before using.

title: needhams
directions: Add salt to mashed potatoes.
Place margarine in top of double boiler, over boiling water until melted.
Add mashed potatoes, confectioners sugar, coconut and vanilla.
Mix well.
Turn onto greased cookie sheet and spread evenly.
Place in cool place to harden.
Cut into small squares.
Dip in Chocolate Dip Mixture.

title: potato chip cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together, adding potato chips last.
Roll dough into balls, then roll balls into sugar.
Flatten with a fork.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: porcupine meat balls
directions: Wash rice.
Combine with meat, rice, salt, pepper, onion and green pepper.
Shape into small balls (1 to 1 1/4-inch across). Heat tomato soup and water.
Add Worcestershire sauce in cooker. Drop meat balls into soup mixture.
Cover pressure cooker and place pressure regulator on vent and cook 10 minutes, if pressure cooking.
Let rock slowly and drop on own accord.
If using a boiler, cook, covered, for about 45 minutes or bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour or until done.

title: baked oatmeal
directions: Mix sugar, eggs and oil.
Add rest of ingredients.
Mix well. Serve with cinnamon, milk or butter.
Can add raisins or coconut. (May use less sugar.)
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes in an 8 x 8-inch or 7 x 9-inch pan.
One and one-half recipe fills a 9 x 12-inch pan.
Keeps well in refrigerator and reheat in microwave.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients, except chicken.
Pour over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/4 hours, uncovered.
Serve with rice.

title: rum walnut torte
directions: Beat egg yolks until light and lemon colored.
Add sugar and beat well about 15 minutes.
Beat egg whites until stiff peaks form.
Fold in egg yolks gently.
Fold in nuts and crumbs alternately, a tablespoon at a time, gently.
Bake in 3 greased and floured 9-inch spring-form pans for 45 minutes to 1 hour at 350°. Cool.

title: mozzarella chicken
directions: Soak chicken in milk; dip in egg and bread crumbs.
Brown in hot margarine.
Cut into bite-size pieces.
Layer in large casserole dish with mushrooms, Mozzarella and scallions.
End with Mozzarella on top.
Pour chicken broth over all.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 50 minutes.
Good with rice pilaf or other seasoned rice.
Serves 6.

title: caramel-nut wedges
directions: Heat oven to 450°. Line a 9-inch round cake pan with foil, letting ends extend about 2-inches above pan. Unfold pie crust in pan. Press into pan and fold edges down slightly to make a 1-inch high lip. Press edges gently with a fork, then prick crust with fork. Press a sheet of foil slightly and snugly onto crust. Bake 12 minutes; remove foil off top and bake 6 minutes more until lightly browned. Reduce heat to 350°.

title: pig picken cake
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together.
Pour into 4 (8in.) cake pans.
Bake at 325 degrees for 15 minutes.
Allow to cool completely.
Frost and refrigerate.

title: ricotta cream
directions: Mix ingredients together in blender or food processor until smooth.
Serve with Fruit Salsa.

title: glass candy
directions: Heat in large pan the first 3 ingredients to 300°. Add drops of food coloring. Add cinnamon. Pour this mixture on cookie sheet. Sprinkle with powdered sugar. Let cool and break in pieces.

title: crock-pot meatball stew
directions: In small bowl combine first 7 ingredients.
Form meat mixture into 1-inch meatballs.
Mix together potatoes and carrots.
Layer meatballs and vegetables in crock-pot.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour over layers.
Cover and cook on low for 8 to 10 hours or overnight.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Combine rice, water and cream of mushroom soup.
Spread in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle a small amount of the dry soup mix over the rice mixture.
Arrange pork chops over the rice mixture.
Sprinkle remaining onion soup mix over the top.
Cover tightly with foil. Bake at 350° for approximately 1 1/2 hours.

title: scalloped pineapple
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat eggs and sugar until fluffy.
Add remaining ingredients.
Place in a 2-quart casserole dish that has been buttered.
Bake for 40 to 45 minutes, until set and brown on top.

title: ham and scalloped potatoes for crock-pot
directions: Put half of ham, potatoes and onions in crock-pot.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper, then half of cheese.
Repeat with remaining half.
Pour soup over top.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Cover and cook on low, 8 to 10 hours or high for 4 hours.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in water.
Mix flour and other dry ingredients together and cut in shortening.
Add yeast and buttermilk. Lightly flour board and knead slightly.
Cut biscuits and fold. Let rise at room temperature.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes.
Brush with melted butter.
(Can be kept in refrigerator to bake later.)

title: earthquake cake
directions: Mix coconut and nuts together.
Spread in bottom of a 9 x 12-inch cake pan (spray with Pam).
Mix cake mix as directed on box.
Pour this over the coconut and nuts.

title: chicken salad burritos
directions: Mix first five ingredients.
Mix next three together and add to first mixture.
Spoon down the center of tortilla and roll up and fasten with toothpick.
Warm in 350° oven for 20 minutes. Leave uncovered for a crisper tortilla.
Wrap securely for a soft tortilla.

title: oven french fries(low calorie)
directions: Scrub potatoes and cut into long strips, about 1/2 inch wide. Drop into ice water, cover and chill 1 to 2 hours.
Remove strips from water and dry thoroughly.
Place strips and oil in a deep bowl and toss until all potatoes have a light coating of oil.
Preheat oven to 475°.
Spread fries in a single layer in a shallow baking pan.
Place in oven for 30 to 35 minutes.
Stir fries occasionally to brown on all sides.
Yields 8 servings.

title: simple, sinful cheesecake
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Combine butter, crumbs and sugar; pat firmly into 9-inch springform pan.
In large mixer bowl, beat cheese until fluffy.
Beat in remaining ingredients.
Pour into prepared pan.
Bake 50 to 55 minutes or until center springs back. Cool to room temperature and chill.

title: franks and corn bread
directions: Combine first five ingredients; mix well.
Transfer to greased 9-inch square baking dish.
Prepare corn bread batter according to package directions; stir in cheese.
Drop by spoonfuls into bean mixture.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes or until heated through.

title: cajun barbecued ribs
directions: In a medium bowl, combine first 8 ingredients; set aside. Moisten ribs with water and sprinkle on all sides with tenderizer.

title: french vanilla cappuccino mix
directions: You will need 1/2 cup sugar to each 1 cup of grapes. Place 1 cup grapes in quart jar. Add 1/2 cup sugar. Fill with boiling water; seal and process 20 minutes.

title: sticky popcorn
directions: Melt marshmallows, oleo and brown sugar over low heat. Mix into popcorn.

title: strawberry jello
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Add frozen strawberries, stirring occasionally until thawed.
Add pineapple with juice, bananas and nuts.
Mix well.
Pour 1/2 mixture in mold or pan. This mixture should be about 1/2 inch deep.
Put in refrigerator until set.
(Leave other 1/2 out of refrigerator.)
Spread thin layer of sour cream over set Jell-O.
Pour rest of Jell-O mixture over sour cream.
Refrigerate until firmly set.
Serves 10 to 12 (or keeps for several days).

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix pudding, milk, sour cream and Cool Whip together.
Place layers of pudding, layer of vanilla wafers and layer of bananas until all are used.

title: banana bread
directions: Blend all ingredients in large bowl, pour into greased loaf pan and bake 1 hour in slow oven (300°).

title: corn casserole
directions: Melt margarine in ovenproof dish; set aside.
Whisk together flour and whipping cream.
Add Shoe Peg corn.
Pour all ingredients over melted margarine.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes until slightly brown.
Do not overbake.

title: dogs in a blanket
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Split each wiener but not completely through.
Slice cheese to fit in middle of wiener.
Flatten each biscuit; place one wiener on each of the flattened biscuits.
Roll biscuit around wieners; secure biscuit around wiener with toothpick.
Place on cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes or until biscuits are browned.
Yield: 10 servings.

title: santa fe chicken heroes
directions: Pound chicken to flatten evenly. Brush both sides with oil. Combine seasonings; sprinkle on both sides of chicken.
Grill over medium-hot coals for 6 to 8 minutes.
Turn and grill 4 to 6 minutes more or until chicken is tender and no longer pink. Top with cheese.
Allow to melt, about 2 minutes. Brush rolls with butter. Grill until toasted.
Place lettuce, tomato and chicken on rolls. Top with salsa, if desired.

title: southern hoe cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients, then add water and mix well.
Put cooking oil in small fryer or skillet (about 6-inches in diameter).
Heat until it will cause batter to fry.
Pour batter into hot fryer. Reduce heat to medium-high and brown. When brown, turn with an egg turner and let other side brown. Take up and serve hot.

title: strawberry jello saladlubbock, texas
directions: Mix fruit into thickened jello.

title: lo-cal dish
directions: Place cabbage in greased baking dish.
Brown hamburger with onion.
Stir in uncooked rice.
Place meat and rice mixture on cabbage, then cover with soup and water.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
This dish is low calorie, yet filling.

title: potato soup
directions: Boil potatoes and onion in a small amount of water until soft. Add milk, salt and pepper; then reheat.
Brown flour in the butter and blend it slowly into the potato mixture.
Add a little water to the beaten egg and stir into the soup.
Let it cook for a few minutes and serve with a sprinkling of chopped parsley.

title: miss margaret's cinnamon rolls
directions: Mix flour, yeast and sugar.
Cut in shortening.
Add water and mix.
Roll dough in 12 x 14-inch rectangle pan or dish.
Brush butter on.
Mix 3 tablespoons sugar and cinnamon; sprinkle over top.
Roll up and cut in about 15 slices, 3/4-inch thick.
Put in buttered pan and let rise 2 hours.
Bake at 425° for 10 minutes or until golden brown.
Glaze while hot with powdered sugar and 4 teaspoons water.

title: cheese loaf
directions: Put all ingredients in a chopper or cut fine with knife.
Mix well.
Roll into ball and chill.
Serve with crackers.

title: grampa crosby's sloppy joes
directions: Cook onion and hamburger together; drain.
Add remaining ingredients; simmer about 15 minutes.
Salt and pepper to taste. Spread over hamburger buns and serve.

title: chocolate eggnog pie
