directions: Combine crumbs, sugar, and butter, mixing until well combined. Press onto bottom and sides of 9 inch pie plate. Bake at 350° for 5 minutes. Soften gelatin in water. Combine sugar and cornstarch in small saucepan, gradually add eggnog. Bring to
boil over medium heat, stirring constantly. Add softened gelatin, stir until dissolved. Stir in
Extract. Cool. Fold in whipped cream, pour over crust. Chill several hours until set.
Spread with Cool Whip.
Garnish with chocolate curls.
Makes 8 servings.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Boil broccoli in small amount of water for 5 minutes.
Drain well.
Mix with other ingredients.
Bake for 30 minutes at 325°.

title: ribbon finger jello
directions: Dissolve 1 package jello and 1 envelope unflavored gelatin in 1 cup hot water.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan, which has been lightly Pammed.
Chill until almost firm, approximately 20 minutes.
If too firm, next layer will tend to slide off.
Soften 2 envelopes unflavored gelatin in 1/4 cup cold water; add 3/4 cup hot water. In separate bowl, mix condensed milk with 1 cup boiling water. Combine both mixtures.
Pour 1 cup milk mixture over first layer and 1 cup between each subsequent layer.
Repeat each gelatin procedure, alternating with milk mixture and ending with gelatin mixture.
While each layer is chilling, mix next layer.
Jelling times will vary according to temperature of mixture.
If mixture becomes too thick, set in hot water or microwave.
When completely firm, cut into desired size.
Crinkly cutter makes an attractive finish.

title: broccoli-cheese casserole
directions: Saute onions in 1/2 cup oleo until tender.
Combine onion, soup, mushrooms, cheese, parsley, salt, pepper, almonds and broccoli.
Mix well.
Spoon into two lightly greased 2-quart casseroles.
Combine stuffing mix and 1/2 cup oleo; spoon over broccoli mixture.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Yield:
12 to 14 servings.

title: savory cheese biscuits
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In food processor, pulse together with on-and-off motion flour, butter, Jarlsberg, Parmesan, rosemary, thyme, garlic salt, nutmeg and cayenne pepper until combined and mixture resembles small peas.
Add egg yolk and water.
Pulse until ball forms.
If mixture is too dry, add 1 tsp. water and pulse until dough comes together.
Turn out onto lightly floured work surface; knead a few times to blend, if necessary.
Divide dough in half.
On a floured surface, roll out each half of dough to 1/4-inch thickness.
Cut into star shapes using 2 1/2-inch star cookie cutter, flouring cutters well to avoid dough sticking to cutter.
Place stars on ungreased baking sheet.
Gather scraps together, roll out again and cut out more stars for a total of 48. Sprinkle tops with coarse salt.
Bake in 350° oven for 18 minutes or until firm and lightly browned around edges.
Let biscuits cool on baking sheets on wire racks for 2 minutes.
Transfer biscuits to racks; let cool completely.
Lightly sprinkle
paprika over biscuits, if desired.
Store in airtight container at room temperature for up to 1 week.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mash sweet potatoes with mixer.
Melt butter and add to potatoes with mixer.
Then add sugars and beaten eggs.
Next add milk and flour.
Last add salt, vanilla, pineapple, nutmeg and cinnamon.
Pour into a greased casserole dish.

title: ragu surprise
directions: Cut eggplant into bite size cubes.
Combine all ingredients in saucepan and heat through for about 10 minutes.

title: apricot salad
directions: Heat pineapple to boiling and then add Jell-O (no water); let cool.
Mix Cool Whip and buttermilk together, then stir into Jell-O mixture.
You will need to stir a long time before it's thoroughly mixed.
Pour into a 9 x 9-inch dish and refrigerate.

title: apple juice frosty
directions: Combine ice cream and apple juice.
Beat until frothy.
Pour into glasses.
Top with cinnamon, if desired.

title: pink fluff
directions: Combine yogurt, pudding mix and whipped topping; mix well. Fold into pie crust.
May top with nuts, if desired.
Chill until served.

title: barbara's blue cheese dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together, refrigerate until using as a dip for fresh vegetables.
Best if made ahead.
Can also be used as a salad dressing.

title: chocolate coffee
directions: Melt chocolate on stove and add milk, sugar, coffee and cinnamon.
Heat, but do not boil. Pour into cups and top with Cool Whip.
Sprinkle on nutmeg and serve.

title: ham strada
directions: Cut crusts from bread and slice in thin strips.
Line a buttered 13 x 9-inch
pan
with bread.
Place cheese, broccoli and ham in layers.
Combine
eggs, milk, mustard and salt; mix well. Pour over top
of
casserole.
Refrigerate
hours or overnight. Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Let set 8 to 10 minutes. Serves 12.

title: crab and shrimp dip
directions: Drain crabmeat.
Mix all ingredients and heat in chafing dish.
Serve on crackers.
Yields 4 cups.

title: pistachio dessert
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Melt butter; stir in flour and nuts. Put into bottom of 9 x 13-inch Pyrex pan.
Bake 20 minutes and let cool.
(If you use tin pan, preheat oven to 350°).
Soften ice cream.
Mix pudding with 1 1/2 cups milk.
Mix until it starts to thicken, then stir in with ice cream.
Spread over cooled crust and freeze.
About 3 hours before serving, top with Cool Whip and Heath bars.

title: 45 second pie crust(makes 2 crusts)
directions: Mix with a mixer, 30 seconds, shortening, flour and salt.
Add water, all at once.
Mix for 15 seconds on low.
Shape into a ball.
Kids can roll out and sprinkle with cinnamon and sugar. Bake at 400° for 3 to 5 minutes.

title: gram's double decker cookies
directions: Cream oleo, sugar and vanilla; add eggs.
Beat well.
Add flour and salt.
Divide batter in half.
Add melted chocolate to 1/2.
Add nuts to rest.
Spread walnut batter in 8 x 8-inch pan (greased).
Spread chocolate batter over top.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes in 350° oven.
Cool in pan.
Cut in squares.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Combine broccoli, bacon, sunflower kernels and onion.
To make dressing, mix mayonnaise, sugar, and white vinegar.
Pour dressing over broccoli just before serving.
Mix well.

title: string bean casserole
directions: Put beans in 1 1/2-quart casserole after draining off the water.
Pour soup to which milk has been added over beans. Sprinkle bread crumbs on top and cover.

title: pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325.

title: cabbage soup
directions: Bring all the ingredients except cabbage to a boil, then add the cabbage.
Boil until cabbage is done.
Can be frozen.

title: texas hash
directions: Saute onions and pepper in shortening or oil.
Add ground beef and fry until mixture falls apart.
Stir in tomatoes, rice, chili powder, salt and pepper.
Pour into greased 2-quart baking dish. Cover and bake for 1 hour at 350°.
Remover cover during last 15 minutes of baking time.
Yields 6 servings.

title: slow cooked peach cobbler
directions: Spray inside of a slow cooker with non-stick spray. Place peaches in bottom of cooker and sprinkle with corn starch. Mix well. Drizzle with vanilla and sprinkle with brown sugar over the top; cover and cook on high for 30 minutes. In a large bowl mix remaining ingredients. Spoon onto the hot pie filling. Cover and cook for 2 to 3 hours. Serve with vanilla ice cream if desired.

title: rice casserole
directions: Saute onion, celery and almonds in margarine for 3 minutes. Add mushrooms, then rice and bouillon; cook for 1 minute.
Pour mixture in casserole dish.
Cover; bake for 1 hour, or until all liquid is absorbed, at 300°.

title: crisco pound cake
directions: Beat Crisco and sugar.
Add eggs one at a time, beating after each egg.
Stir in vanilla.
Add flour and beat for 3 minutes. Bake in greased tube pan for 1 hour at 350°.
This cake has a very crusty top and does not need frosting.

title: pineapple scalloped
directions: Dissolve sugar in pineapple juice.
Add remaining ingredients. Mix in bowl; let absorb.
Place mixture in lightly buttered dish. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
This can be eaten hot or cold; also good reheated.

title: tomato pudding
directions: In a saucepan, bring the tomatoes, sugar and butter to a boil. Break the bread into pieces and add to the tomato mixture.
Add extra bread until all of the liquid is absorbed.

title: pineapple delight
directions: Beat Eagle Brand milk and lemon juice a little.
Drain pineapple and fold into mixture.
Add Cool Whip.
Chop cherries and pecans and add to mixture.
Put in refrigerator to cool.

title: lemon tenderloin and vegetables
directions: * Vidalias if in season.

title: potato soup
directions: In 2 quarts water in a large pan, crumble in raw hamburger. Add celery and onions; bring to simmer.
Peel and cube potatoes. Add to the pot.
Cook until potatoes are tender.
Add margarine and milk; cook 10 minutes.
Stir in instant potatoes.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: perfect baked potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Scrub potatoes well under cold, running water.
Dry thoroughly with paper towels.
With fork, prick skins over entire surface.
(Brush potatoes with salad oil if you like skins soft after baking.)
Place potatoes right on oven rack and bake for 50 to 60 minutes, or until they are easily pierced with fork or feel soft.
Slash an X in top of each potato.
Then, holding potato with pot holders, squeeze ends so steam can escape and potato puffs up.
Add a pat of butter to each; sprinkle with salt, pepper and paprika.
Or top with sour cream and crumbled bacon or chopped green onions.
Serves 4.

title: mostaccioli
directions: Cook noodles as directed on package.
Brown sausage and cut in small pieces.
Mix sausage, sauce, noodles, mushrooms and 1/4 cup cheese together in a 9 x 12-inch baking pan.
Top with remaining Mozzarella cheese and cover with aluminum foil.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1/2 hour.

title: fruited cheese ball or wheel
directions: Mix all ingredients. Form and chill. May "ice" with softened cream cheese. Good with Ritz crackers and gingersnaps. Best made the day before serving. Makes 2 balls.

title: mushroom soup
directions: Soak dried mushrooms in 1 can of chicken broth for a few hours if you decide to use them.
Later simmer this combination with half of the fresh whole mushrooms for 10 minutes.
Pour into blender or food processor and puree with the cheese.
Set aside.
Slice remaining mushrooms and simmer 10 minutes in the saucepan.
Pour blender mixture in.
Stir and heat gently and serve.

title: overnight fruit salad
directions: Beat eggs; add sugar, flour, pineapple juice and butter.
Cook in double boiler until thick, then let cool.
Add crushed pineapple, marshmallows, nuts and pint of cream to the first mixture and put in box overnight.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Melt margarine. Cut chicken into small pieces.
Slice eggs and onion.
Mix milk and soup. Pour over mixture.
Mix stuffing with chicken broth and put over top. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: caldo gallego(spanish vegetable bean soup)
directions: Wash beans and soak overnight in 8 cups water.
Drain and add 12 to 16 cups water.
Add turnips, ham, saffron, soup base, pepper and bay leaf.
Bring to boil; cook, uncovered, about 2 hours. Stir occasionally.
Then add rest of vegetables and vinegar.
Cook additional 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Serve hot.
Salt to taste.
Add a squeeze of lime juice, if desired.
This is a delicious vegetable soup from Spain.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Thaw berries.
Dissolve jello in hot water.
Add strawberries and pineapple.
Pour half of mixture into 9-inch square dish.
Set in refrigerator until firm.
Keep remaining jello mixture at room temperature.
Mix together sour cream and cream cheese.
Spread over jello when set.
Cover with remaining jello mixture.

title: 3 bean barbecue baked beans
directions: Bake at 325° for 35 to 45 minutes or cover and cook at low heat overnight in slow cooker.

title: saucy meat muffins
directions: Separate dough into 10 biscuits; flatten each and press into bottom and up sides of a greased muffin cup.
Set aside.

title: corn muffins, corn sticks or fried cornmeal cakes
directions: Mix meal, flour and sugar.

Add egg and add milk gradually until you get the right consistency (not too thick, not too thin). Add melted shortening last, stirring only enough to mix completely. Fill preheated and greased corn stick tins or muffin tins and bake at 450° for 20 to 30 minutes or until golden brown and done.
If frying, melt about 3 tablespoons shortening in skillet and fry with medium-low heat until brown and done.
About 2 tablespoons of mixture to each corn cake.

title: simmering potpourri(spice scent)
directions: Simmer on stove in open pan.

title: cajun spice
directions: Take a cup of kindness,

title: caramel popcorn
directions: In saucepan, mix sugar, margarine, syrup and salt.
Stir over medium heat until boiling.
Continue boiling without stirring for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and stir in vanilla and soda.
Pour over popcorn.
Stir to coat well.
Bake in 250° oven for 1 hour. Stir several times during baking.
Will keep several weeks, crisp, if stored in airtight container.

title: tortilla roll-ups
directions: Combine cheese, onions and chilies. Spread thinly over each tortilla. Roll up and refrigerate overnight (covered). Next day, cut in strips. Serve with salsa.

title: lemon jello salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in hot water.
Add marshmallows and stir until melted.
Cool.
When it begins to set, add pineapple and bananas. Chill until firm.
Cover with topping.

title: coleslaw and dressing
directions: Whip first 3 ingredients together with whisk.
Add remaining dressing ingredients to mixture and mix well.

title: caraway rye bread
directions: In a large bowl, dissolve yeast in 1/2 cup warm water.
Add brown sugar, caraway, oil, salt and remaining water.
Mix well. Stir in rye flour and 1 cup all-purpose flour to form a soft dough. Turn onto a floured board.
Knead until smooth and elastic, about 6 - 8 minutes.
Place in a greased bowl, turning once to grease top. Cover and let rise in a warm place until doubled, about 1 hour. Punch dough down, divide in half.
Shape each half into a ball. Place in two greased 8 inch round cake pans.
Flatten balls to a 6 inch diameter.
Cover and let rise until nearly doubled, about 30 minutes.
Bake at 375 for 25 - 30 minutes or until golden brown.

title: chili rellenos casserole
directions: Beat milk with the eggs and flour until smooth.
Split open chiles; rinse, remove seeds and pat dry with paper towels.
Mix cheeses together and set aside 1/2 cup for top of casserole. Layer chiles, cheese and egg mixture in a deep 1 1/2-quart casserole (layer optional items too if you're using them).
Pour the tomato sauce on top and cover with the cheese you set aside. Bake at 350°
for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: strawberry punch bowl cake
directions: Make Jell-O and let gel in small bowl.
Bake cake in 2 round cake pans; use milk in the recipe instead of water that the box calls for.
In a large bowl, pour jelled Jell-O in bottom.
Put layer of cake on top of it.
Use one package of glaze on top of cake.
Use half of Cool Whip on top of glaze.
Put other layer of cake on top.
Use other package of glaze.
Top with Cool Whip and strawberries.

title: banana split cake
directions: Melt 1 stick oleo and mix with graham cracker crumbs.
Spread over 9 x 13-inch pan.
Beat powdered sugar, 2 sticks oleo, eggs and vanilla for 20 minutes (no less) and spread over crumbs. Slice 4 bananas over mixture.
Over the bananas put 2 cups pineapple (you can mix strawberries with pineapple).
Next, spread Cool Whip over top and sprinkle.
Chill before serving.

title: pineapple salad
directions: Mix gelatin and water; let stand 10 minutes.
Heat pineapple, lemon and sugar.
Mix with gelatin and water; chill until partially set.
Fold in the cheese, nuts, salad dressing and condensed milk, chilled and whipped.
Chill and serve on lettuce leaves.

title: quickie rolls
directions: Combine all ingredients; mix well and drop by spoonfuls into well-greased muffin pans.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
Makes 1 dozen.

title: crisp peanut butter cookies
directions: In small bowl, stir flour, baking powder, soda and salt.
In large bowl with mixer at medium speed, beat margarine and peanut butter until smooth.
Blend sugars, eggs and vanilla.
Add flour mixture.
Beat until well blended.
Dough may need to be refrigerated to easily shape into 1-inch balls.
Place 2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Flatten with fork dipped in sugar, making crisscross patterns.
Bake in 350° oven for 12 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients until blended.
Fold in Cool Whip. Pour into a baked pie shell.
Refrigerate.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Prepare sauce as directed.
Saute onion and garlic; add to hamburger.
Do not brown onion or garlic.
Break the tortillas in half.
Layer sauce and tortillas (like lasagna).
Bake for 30 minutes.
Cover with grated cheese; bake until hot throughout.

title: cherry bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake 1 hour at 325°.
(I use 2 medium size loaf pans, 7 3/8 x 3 5/8 x 2 1/4-inch.)

title: family casserole
directions: Cook hamburger and onions together.
Drain grease off.
Add tomato soup, a little water, and green beans.
Cook macaroni until done.
Add with other ingredients, mixing well.
Put in casserole dish by layers and add cheese to the layers and on top of casserole.
Put in oven and cook until bubbling at 375°.

title: american lasagna
directions: Brown beef and garlic; drain.
Add tomato paste, tomatoes
and seasonings.
Cover and simmer 20 minutes.
Heat oven to 350°.
In oblong 9 x 13-inch baking dish, alternate layers of cooked noodles, cottage cheese, meat sauce and Mozzarella cheese.
Bake for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: rice pudding
directions: Combine rice, milk and sugar in a large pot and cook on top of stove until most liquid is absorbed.
Beat eggs in a bowl and add vanilla.
Pour rice mixture into a 9 x 13-inch dish.
Pour egg mixture over rice and mix thoroughly.
Sprinkle with cinnamon. Refrigerate 4 to 6 hours.

title: quickie peach cobbler
directions: In 2-quart saucepan, combine peaches, 1 cup of sugar, butter and cinnamon; bring to a boil over medium heat.
In mixing bowl, combine flour, salt, baking powder, 3/4 cup sugar and 1/2 cup milk.
Stir until smooth.
Pour dough mixture into greased 9 x 13-inch casserole.
Pour boiled mixture over dough; do not stir. Bake at 425° for 20 minutes or until golden brown.

title: yeast biscuits
directions: Sift first 4 ingredients; cut in shortening.
Soften yeast in 3 tablespoons lukewarm water; add to flour mixture.
Add milk to make soft dough; knead until smooth.
Roll and cut.
Let rise 20 minutes.
Bake in hot oven at 450°.

title: avocado-carrot salad
directions: Toast sunflower seeds if desired.
Mix well with avocado, carrot, green pepper and onion.
Mix remaining ingredients to make dressing.
Scoop avocado mixture onto a bed of greens.
Add dressing and garnish with parsley sprigs or lemon peel.
Serves 4.

title: almond butter crunch
directions: In a large saucepan melt butter; add sugar, corn syrup and water.
Cook stirring occasionally to hard crack state (300° on candy thermometer and watch carefully after 280°).
Quickly stir in coarsely chopped nuts; spread in ungreased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan; cool thoroughly.
Turn out on waxed paper.
Spread top with half the melted chocolate, sprinkle with 1/2 the finely chopped nuts. Cover with waxed paper and invert.
Spread the other side with remaining chocolate and sprinkle with remaining nuts.
Chill to firm; crack in pieces.
So good.

title: pineapple crinkles
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Cream the shortening and sugar in a large mixing bowl.
Add the salt, lemon rind and egg, beating until thoroughly blended.
Fold in the pineapple.
Sift together the flour, baking powder and baking soda and add to the creamed mixture.
Drop tablespoons of dough onto well-greased baking sheets, 2 inches apart.
Sprinkle cookies with sugar and nutmeg before baking.
Bake about 12 minutes until lightly browned. Store airtight.
Makes about 24.

title: beef or venison jerky
directions: Slice venison or beef into 3/8-inch strips (with the grain). In container, combine all ingredients.
Stir until all spices are dissolved.
Place meat in marinade.
Be sure all meat is covered and marinate overnight.
Rinse in fresh water.
Let all excess water drip off.
Lay meat strips over rack, dry in oven at 100° to 150° for 6 to 8 hours.
Cook longer for drier jerky.
For spicier taste, do not rinse meat.

title: million dollar pie
directions: Add all ingredients; mix well.
Pour in shells and refrigerate 2 to 3 hours.

title: jello punch
directions: Add water to make 1 gallon.
Add jello, sugar and water.
Heat until sugar dissolves.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Mix sugar, syrup and water in 2-quart saucepan.
Bring to boil. Boil until syrup spins a thread.
Add peanuts and continue to cook stirring constantly, until it turns golden brown.
Remove from heat; add butter and soda.
The mixture will honeycomb as you stir. Pour onto a chilled heavy cookie sheet 18 x 24-inch.

title: seafood bake
directions: Combine all ingredients. Put bread crumbs on top and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: baked mashed potatoes
directions: Grease casserole dish. Add potatoes and onions. Mix together water, oil, salt, sage and pepper. Drizzle over potatoes. Stir together. Bake, uncovered, at 450° until tender. Mash or beat together with mixer, adding the buttermilk.

title: celery seed dressing
directions: Blend everything but the oil, then very slowly add the oil while blending on and off.

title: cheeseburger piea delicious low-fat version of a classic dish.
directions: Combine first six ingredients.
Simmer for 6 to 8 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Add turkey and 3 oz. of cheese. Stir well until cheese melts.
Put in and 8 X 8 inch baking dish sprayed with Pam.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Bake for 30 minutes at 375° F.
Remove from oven and allow to set before serving.

title: summer chicken with peas and new potatoes
directions: Melt butter in a large skillet.
Add chicken and potatoes and brown slowly on all sides; season with salt and pepper.
(Be generous with pepper.)
Sprinkle chicken with lemon juice; reduce heat, cover pan and simmer 30 minutes.
Add green onions to butter in bottom of skillet; sprinkle peas and parsley over chicken and potatoes; cover again and simmer 10 minutes more, or until chicken and potatoes are tender.
Remove chicken and vegetables to serving platter; keep warm.
Remove skillet from heat.
Add sour cream, thyme, 1/2 teaspoon salt and 1/4 teaspoon pepper; stir to mix well and to loosen pan drippings.
Pour over chicken or pass as sauce. Garnish with additional parsley; serve immediately.
Makes 4 servings.

title: country chicken 'n biscuits
directions: In a greased 8 x 12-inch baking dish, combine the first 4 ingredients and 1 cup of cheese.
Blend soup and 3/4 cup of milk. Pour over casserole.
Bake, uncovered, at 400° for 15 minutes.

title: pea salad
directions: You will need a dish 2 to 3 inches deep.

title: green rice
directions: Combine all ingredients together.
Cover.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour (sometimes only 40 minutes).

title: creamy rice pudding
directions: Mix sugar, flour, cornstarch and salt.
Stir in cold milk and egg yolks.
Add scalded milk and rice.
Cook in a double boiler just until it starts to thicken.
Add raisins, if desired, and vanilla. Pour into a 2-quart baking pan and then set that pan in a larger pan of water.
Bake at 325° for 20 minutes.

title: orange ice cream
directions: Mix all ingredients and freeze in freezer.

title: linguine and clams
directions: Saute garlic in olive oil over low heat until soft, not brown. Add liquid from clams.
Add parsley.
Heat on low.
Just before serving, add clams to sauce, then pour over cooked linguine.

title: cheese rolls
directions: Melt together the milk, cheese and margarine. Add sugar; let cool.
Dissolve in 1/2 cup warm water the yeast.
When milk cools, add to yeast.
Add 6 to 7 cups self-rising flour and knead.
Let double.
Work down and dip in butter; let rise. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: chicken hawaiian
directions: In large skillet, heat oil and brown chicken.
Add pineapple chunks and juice, corn syrup, vinegar, catsup, soy sauce and garlic.
Bring to boil.
Reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, about 10 minutes.
Keep stirring.
Add peppers.

title: potato cheddar soup
directions: In a large pot, saute (using margarine) onions and celery.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Boil sugar and milk until it forms soft ball in water.
Remove from heat and add immediately the marshmallow, peanut butter and vanilla.
Beat until thick.
Pour in lightly buttered pan.
Cool, cut and enjoy.

title: "real" chili
directions: Put beef and pork in separate skillets and cook.
When they start to brown, cover and let cook for 45 minutes.
Add half the cumin and oregano to each skillet and stir.
Continue cooking for 30 more minutes.

title: date pecan pie
directions: Whip egg whites and add sugar gradually.
Mix crackers, dates and nuts; add to sugar and egg mixture.
Put in greased pie pan. Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: homemade chicken and noodles
directions: Cook chicken in cream of chicken soup and bouillon cubes.
Do not leave soup condensed; add water.
Remove chicken from broth and let cool.
Add wide egg noodles to broth and boil until tender. Remove chicken from bone, shred, and drop into noodles and broth. Ready to serve.

title: chicken marinade
directions: Combine all ingredients and beat well.

title: party ham and slaw sandwich
directions: Combine milk, sugar, salt and dash of black pepper.
Stir well.
Add mustard and vinegar.
Toss with cabbage.
Chill until ready to serve.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into a buttered 8 inch square pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: fruit salad(low-fat and sugar-free)
directions: Mix fruit cocktail with dry instant pudding mix.
Add pineapple, pecans and coconut.
Chill.

title: italian spaghetti sauce
directions: Cut sausage into 2-inch pieces.
Brown sausage, meat and onion in small amount of oil.
Drain off excess oil.
Add puree and 3 cans water to pot.
Add garlic powder, oregano, Italian spices, sugar and cheese.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Cook slowly for 3 hours.
Serve on cooked spaghetti.
Sprinkle with extra cheese.

title: red, white and blue dessert
directions: In a large mixing bowl, beat cream cheese, sugar and extracts until fluffy.
Fold in the whipped cream. Layer pound cake, cream cheese mixture and fruit; repeat again.
End with cream cheese mixture.
Make a "flag" on top with strawberries and blueberries.

title: fruit salad
directions: Use the saved juice and mix with pudding and Tang.
Pour over fruit.
Add fresh fruits just before serving.
Chill in refrigerator until ready to eat.

title: shrimp remoulade
directions: Add olive oil to blender.
Add chopped seasoning.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Chill about 2 hours before using.

title: baked chicken breasts
directions: Mix Worcestershire sauce, lemon juice, salt, pepper and celery salt with sour cream.
Pour over chicken and marinate overnight. Roll chicken in bread crumbs.
Put in a well greased shallow baking pan and refrigerate for 1 hour.
Brush chicken with half of butter.
Bake 30 minutes at 325°. Baste with remaining butter and bake 30 minutes.

title: pineapple pudding
directions: Mix ingredients.
Bake 45 minutes to 1 hour at 350°.
May be made the day before and refrigerated, then allow a full hour to bake.

title: banana cake(3 layers)
directions: Grease and flour 3 (8-inch) cake pans.
Sift flour, sugar, baking powder, soda and salt together in large bowl or mixer.
Mix evaporated milk with lemon juice.
Add alternately to dry ingredients with butter and bananas.
Beat at medium speed for 2 minutes.
Add eggs and beat 2 minutes.

title: pumpkin bread (roll)
directions: Combine eggs, sugar, pumpkin, and lemon juice together.
Then sift salt, flour, baking powder, cinnamon, and nutmeg over the mixture.
After stirring everything together pour into a greased jelly roll or cookie sheet pan.
Top with chopped pecans.
Bake 15 minutes at 375°.
After baking, turn onto towel and roll, starting with the shorter end.
Let cool in towel.

title: texas hash
directions: Brown onion and bell pepper in oleo, then add ground beef and brown.
Remove from fire.
Mix with tomatoes and uncooked rice. Add salt and pepper to taste.
Put in casserole and bake at 300° for about 1 hour.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix all ingredients together in large bowl until well blended. Shape into 1/2-inch balls.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes. Serves 8 to 10.

title: rice pudding
directions: Add rice to boiling water and cook until tender.
To cooked rice, add salt and vanilla.
Combine milk and cornstarch together, then add to mixture.
Add beaten egg yolks and cook until mixture thickens.
Remove from heat and cool slightly.
Beat egg whites until stiff; fold into mixture.
Sprinkle with nutmeg and cinnamon.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix sausage and Bisquick together well.
I use mild sausage and work them together with my fingers.
Then add the cup of sharp Cheddar cheese and milk.
Roll in balls and bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until browns.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello according to directions on box.
Add remaining ingredients.

title: low-fat apple cake dessert
directions: Cream applesauce.
Add Egg Beaters and beans.
Mix well.
Sift dry ingredients together and add to creamed mixture.
Add sugar, spices, apples, raisins and vanilla.
Mix well.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan that has been sprayed with Pam.
Bake at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Cut into 24 squares.
Serve with a dab of Cool Whip. Contains 92 calories and .1 gram of fat.

title: thumb cookies
directions: Mix well with mixer.
Add 1 cup of flour and 1/4 teaspoon salt.
Roll into 1-inch balls in slightly beaten egg whites.
Bake at 350° for 5 minutes.
Press center down with thumb and bake 8 minutes longer.
When cool, fill center with favorite icing.

title: cinnamon rolls
directions: Flatten biscuits into long strips.
Sprinkle sugar and cinnamon on top of strips.
Roll strips and place in pan.
Bake 12 minutes at 325°.
Melt butter into glaze. Pour lightly over cooled rolls.

title: shipwreck
directions: Brown ground beef in a Dutch oven.
Add sliced onion and continue to brown.
Add all the remaining ingredients (potatoes should be peeled and cubed).
Bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour or until potatoes are done.
Serves 6.

title: cheese logs
directions: Soften cheese.
Add ingredients.
Roll into 2 logs, then roll in chopped nuts.
Refrigerate and serve with crackers.
Will keep 2 weeks in refrigerator.

title: chocolate delight
directions: Blend all well.
Put into an 8 x 11-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Cool.

title: bucko's scalloped potatoes
directions: Peel potatoes and slice as thinly as possible.
Mix the Cheddar cheese soup and milk together.
Layer the cheese/milk mixture and potatoes in a baking dish that has been sprayed with Pam to keep the potatoes from sticking.
Also, sprinkle with salt and pepper as you are layering.
Top with the shredded Colby cheese.
Bake at 350° for an hour or until fork-tender.

title: sweet potato biscuits
directions: Wash and boil potato with peel on.
Cook potato and peel. Mash potato and be sure it is free from any lumps.
Sift together salt, flour and baking powder.
Add sweet potato and shortening. Mix into a light dough with egg and milk.
Roll thinner than regular biscuit dough.
Cut with biscuit cutter.
Bake at 450° until done.

title: cream cheese cookies
directions: Have cream cheese and oleo at room temperature.
Mix other ingredients.
Take dough by teaspoonfuls.
Roll out in balls and place on greased cookie sheets.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes or until done.

title: breakfast burritos
directions: Brown sausage in a large skillet.
Add the onion and pepper; cook until tender.
Drain off grease.
Add potatoes; cook for 6 to 8 minutes or until tender.
Add eggs; stir.
Cook until eggs are set.
Prepare tortillas by browning in hot oil in large skillet for 5 seconds on each side, or heating in microwave for 45 to 60 seconds.
Divide filling mixture between 12 tortillas, placing filling down center.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Fold bottom of tortilla up and sides toward each other.
Serve with picante sauce and sour cream on the side.
Yields 12 burritos.

title: pumpkin roll
directions: Beat the eggs, sugar and pumpkin for 5 minutes.
Add other ingredients.
Line cookie sheet with waxed paper and grease.
Pour pumpkin mixture onto greased paper; spread.
Bake for 15 minutes at 375°.
Remove; let cool for 5 minutes.
Flip onto linen towel; remove waxed paper.
Roll up in towel; cool completely.

title: apricot carrot bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray an 8 x 4 x 2-inch loaf pan with cooking spray.
In a large mixing bowl, combine flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
In a medium size bowl, combine beaten egg, sugar, applesauce, carrots and vegetable oil. Add all at once to dry ingredients.
Stir just until moistened (batter will be thick). Fold in apricots.
Pour batter into prepared loaf pan and bake 45 to 50 minutes or until an inserted toothpick comes out clean. Remove from oven and let cool. Wrap loaf and store overnight before slicing.

title: rocky road fudge
directions: Melt together first three ingredients in separate bowl.
Mix last three ingredients together.
Pour chocolate mixture over and mix well.
Pour in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Chill 2 hours.

title: peanut butter delight
directions: Put sugar, milk and cocoa in large pot. On medium heat, bring to a boil. Boil for 3 minutes. Remove from heat. Add butter, peanut butter and vanilla. Stir until blended. Add oats and stir well. Pour in greased pan and cool completely.

title: hodge podge
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Put meat in crock-pot.
Put beans on meat, minestrone soup on beans and Ro-Tel tomatoes on top of soup.
All ingredients will be layered in crock-pot.
Cook on low for 8 hours.

title: chicken dish
directions: Boil chicken and chop. Boil egg noodles and drain. Mix chicken and noodles together with milk. Add cheese and butter. Cook until cheese melts.

title: japanese fruit cake(1930 or older)
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs; mix well.
Add milk and flour; mix well.
Add nuts, coconut and raisins; mix well.
Add spices; mix well.
Pour into 9-inch cake pans.
Makes 5 thin layers.

title: cream cheese brownie pie
directions: In medium bowl, combine cream cheese, sugar, vanilla, and 1 of the eggs. Beat until smooth and set aside.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Combine potatoes, 1/2 cup butter, onion, soup, sour cream and Cheddar cheese.
Stir well and spoon into greased 2 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Crush corn flakes and stir in remaining butter. Sprinkle over potato mixture.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes or until bubbly.

title: pastie
directions: Lay out crusts.
Put ingredients in half of crusts.
Fold the other half over like a turnover.
Seal edges with fork.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: champagne punch
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large punch bowl (6 to 8-quart). Spoon in sherbet balls.
Stir and enjoy!
Should be made a half to 1 hour before company arrives.
Improves upon standing.
This punch was served at the Art Auction.

title: creative baked salmon
directions: Place salmon fillets, skin sides down, in 9 x 13 pan, sprayed with no stick cooking spray.
Mix remaining ingredients until blended; spoon over salmon.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: black midnight cake
directions: Combine cocoa and hot water.
Stir to dissolve completely.
Add to creamed shortening, sugar and eggs, alternately with dry ingredients that have been sifted.
Bake in 2 round (8-inch) layer or square cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes for layers. Bake 45 to 55 minutes for square cake pan.
Bake approximately 20 to 25 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean for 24 cupcakes in muffin paper cupcake pan.

title: pig pickin' cake
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients in the order given. Divide into 3 layers and bake in greased and floured pans at 325° until done; cool.

title: rhubarb surprise
directions: Spread 8 cups chopped rhubarb evenly in a 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Cream the butter, 1 1/2 cups of the sugar, flour, salt and baking powder alternately with 1/2 cup of the milk.
Spread mixture over rhubarb.
Combine remaining sugar (1 1/2 cups) and cornstarch.
Sprinkle evenly over batter.
Pour 1 cup boiling water evenly over all.
Bake for 1 hour at 375°.

title: company potatoes
directions: Heat 2 tablespoons oil in a large skillet.
Add potatoes and onion.
Cook until brown, turning often.
In a large bowl, mix bread, eggs and spices.
Add to potato mixture.
Cook until eggs are done, about 5 minutes.
If company arrives unexpectedly, just add more bread and eggs.
Serves 6 people.

title: jeff's quick chilli
directions: Mix together in a crock-pot for 1 hour on high.
Turn down to low for 3 more hours.
Serve hot and enjoy.

title: cod with vegetables
directions: Place cod in a large skillet and pour 1/2 cup water over. Cover and simmer for 5 minutes.
Remove fish.
In a separate skillet, heat oil and saute onions, garlic and carrots until onion is transparent.
Pour fish cooking water over; add herbs, cover and simmer for 15 minutes.
When carrots are barely tender, gently place fish on top of vegetables; heat through.
Taste and season with a little salt and tamari, as desired.
Serve with brown rice.

title: six hour stew
directions: Mix everything together raw in a roaster.
Bake at 250° to 300°.

title: tangy gooseberry pie
directions: Mix well and pour into 9-inch pie crust.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes, then at 325° about 25 minutes or until light brown.

title: turtles
directions: Heat caramels and milk until melted.
Add pecans to melted caramels.
Drop by tablespoons onto greased or buttered cookie sheets.
Freeze overnight.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients except 1 cup pecans.
Shape into a ball and chill.
Roll in remaining pecans.

title: quiche italiano
directions: Line a pie plate with pastry.
Do not prick shell.
Bake shell at 400° for 5 to 7 minutes.
In a small skillet, cook pepperoni, green pepper, onion and mushrooms in margarine until tender.
Stir in herbs.

title: hawaiian yams
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into 10-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: sweet roll dough
directions: Dough should be soft and sticky; don't add more flour.

title: icee
directions: Put water, sugar, Kool Aid and ice cubes in electric blender on high speed.

Gradually add more ice cubes and a little water until the amount reaches the top of the blender to make 5 cups. Alternate adding ice and water, pushing cubes to bottom to ensure they are getting crushed.

title: black bean salad with chili vinaigrette
directions: Mix corn, beans, onion and peppers with the Vinaigrette (can be done one day in advance).
Before serving, add chopped cilantro and decorate with tomatoes.

title: party perkies
directions: Heat oven to 250°.
Mix cereal, pretzels and nuts in oblong pan, 13 x 9 x 2-inch.
Blend butter and seasonings.
Pour over cereal mixture and mix well. Bake 30 minutes, stirring gently after 15 minutes.
Makes about 7 cups.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Butter all bread slices.
Cut bread in 1-inch cubes.
Spread in bottom of buttered pan (9 x 13-inch).
Mix remaining ingredients and pour over bread cubes.
Refrigerate overnight. Bake 1 hour at 325°.

title: baked chicken reuben
directions: In a sprayed baking dish (9 x 13), place chicken. Put sauerkraut over chicken. Top with Swiss cheese. Pour dressing evenly over cheese. Cover with foil. Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours or until done. Sprinkle with parsley. Serve hot.

title: peanut-honey cookies
directions: Cream margarine, sugar and honey with electric mixer until fluffy, then beat in egg, vanilla and cinnamon, then add flour, soda and peanuts.
Roll, then cut with cutter.
Bake at 375° until done.
Makes 16 servings.
One serving equals 3 cookies.
Three cookies equals 119 calories.

title: mom's smithville inn orange cookies
directions: Cream margarine with sugar and well beaten eggs.
Add flour with baking powder alternately with sour cream into which you have added baking soda.
Also, add ground oranges.
Drop by tablespoons (a goodly amount of dough) an bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: italian sausage and chicken legs(origin:  italian)
directions: Brown garlic and onion.
Saute meat in oil.
Add tomatoes, thyme, salt and bay leaf. Simmer 10 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer until meat is cooked, approximately 20 minutes.

title: pecan dreams
directions: Cream butter; cream in sugar, then cream in vanilla.
Add salt to flour and mix well.
Add flour mixture to butter mixture; mix slowly.
Add nuts and chill 1 hour.
Form chilled dough into "fingers" (about size of ring finger).
Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Will not be browned.
Roll in lots of powdered sugar while still warm, several times until cooled.

title: cheese puff
directions: Grease cake pan.
Butter all bread, one side, and cut in cubes.
Put half the cubes in a 9 x 12-inch pan.
Sprinkle on half the cheese.
Repeat.
Beat all other ingredients with fork and pour over bread.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for one hour.
Can add any meat.
Pre-fry bacon or bulk sausage.

title: hot rolls
directions: Mix yeast, 1 teaspoon sugar and lukewarm water in measuring cup.
Mix 1/4 cup sugar, salt, oil and boiling water in large mixing bowl.
Add 1 egg and yeast mixture.
Stir in 3 cups flour, add more if needed.
Cover bowl with plastic wrap and let rise. Make into rolls, let rise again.
Bake at 450° until brown.
Make 24 rolls or 2 loaves bread.

title: cranberry christmas salad
directions: Dissolve jello in 1 cup boiling water.
Add enough water to pineapple juice to make 1 1/2 cups.
Add to jello; set aside and let cool.
When jello starts to thicken, add crushed pineapple, orange pieces, cranberry sauce and walnuts.
Turn into mold and chill.
This will keep nicely for several weeks.

title: chicken divan
directions: Simmer chicken in salted water; cook broccoli.
Place broccoli in bottom of buttered 2-quart casserole dish.
Cut chicken into smaller pieces; place on top of broccoli.
Mix sauce with all remaining ingredients, except bread crumbs; pour on top of layered broccoli and chicken.
Top with bread crumb mixture.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes, uncovered.

title: pineapple and lime jello
directions: 1st Layer:
Mix Jell-O and hot water.
Add cold water and pineapple; put all together in 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: dip for fruit salad
directions: Blend all ingredients together and beat with an electric mixer until light and smooth.

title: mary helen's peach cobbler
directions: Put peaches in bottom of 1 1/2 or 2 qt baking dish, piling peaches higher in the middle of the dish.

title: fiesta punch
directions: Mix all ingredients in a blender.

title: potato soup
directions: Cook potatoes, celery, onion and salt in 2 cups water about 20 minutes or until potatoes are tender.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Cook until soup is hot and thickened.

title: choc. oat bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix flour, oats, brown sugar and oleo (this will be crumbly).
Save 1/2 cup of this.
Press remaining mix into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cook for 10 minutes.

title: fudgsicles
directions: Mix all ingredients except vanilla.
Stir and bring to boil. Boil 1 minute.
Let cool.
Add vanilla.
Put into tray or forms and freeze.

title: delicious nut bread
directions: Mix oatmeal, All Bran, flour, baking powder, soda, cinnamon, Sweet 'N Low and nuts in a large bowl.
In separate bowl, mix remaining ingredients.
Combine banana mixture with oatmeal mixture and mix just enough to blend together.
Batter will be thick.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan that has been lightly greased (I use Pam spray) or spoon into muffin tins.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Recipe is fat free, sugar free and cholesterol free. Great for diabetics!

title: tootie bread
directions: Place bread foil on cookie sheet.
Slice 16 slices; place triangles of cheese in slices until gone.
Cream mixture; slice bacon into tiny strips.
Place on top.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: easy catfish chowder
directions: Saute onions in butter.
Add other ingredients including enough broth to make it the right consistency.
Simmer 30 minutes.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Fry sausage until brown. Drain off fat. Separate the crescent rolls and place pieces into ungreased pizza pan, putting points toward center. Push up edges to form crust. Spoon sausage over crust. Sprinkle potatoes on top. Cover with shredded cheese. In bowl, beat together eggs, salt, pepper and milk. Pour over crust and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese. Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Combine jello with water in large bowl; stir well.
Fold in strawberries with juice, drained pineapple, bananas and nuts. Put 1/2 of mixture in a 12 x 8-inch dish.
Refrigerate until firm; spread with sour cream and pour rest of mixture on top of that. Let set until firm.

title: pecan pie
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Add well-beaten eggs and nuts last. Pour into unbaked pie crust.
Bake 10 minutes at 350°.
Turn oven to 325° and bake 35 minutes.

title: creamy fresh fruit dip
directions: Combine ingredients, mixing at medium speed on electric mixer until well blended.
Serve over fruit.
Makes about 1 1/2 cups.

title: summer salami and tomato salad(best if made day before)
directions: Cut tomato wedges, cube meat, cut pepperoncini in half and cube cheese.
Put all ingredients together in Tupperware bowl. Pour the dressing over.
Add the grated Romano cheese and black olives.
Mix everything together so dressing coats it all.
Cover and refrigerate until ready to use.

title: chili(for 25 people)
directions: Put meat and water in covered pot with chopped onions.
Let cook until tender, then add chili powder, paprika, cumin, red pepper, salt and garlic.
Let cook 5 minutes, then turn the heat down and add flour.
Let cook 5 minutes longer, then place in pan to mold.
The chili must be hard to cut in blocks.

title: spinach bake(servings:  8)
directions: After cooking spinach, drain and reserve liquid.
Melt butter; add flour, then onion.
Add evaporated milk and some liquid slowly.
Stir constantly until smooth and thick; add seasoning. Cut up cheese and melt.
After melted, add spinach; put into casserole and cover with buttered bread crumbs.
Improves taste by making a day ahead.
Can be frozen.

title: gram sieber's crumb cake
directions: Mix together.
Take out 1 cup of crumbs and set aside.
With the remaining mix, add sour milk (1 tablespoon vinegar to 1 cup milk to sour) and soda.
Bake at 350° a little longer than a 1/2 hour.

title: fettucine
directions: Cook noodles according to package directions.
Drain thoroughly.
Mix butter and cheese and cream together.
Pour over noodles and mix gently.
Serve immediately.
Serves 4.

title: broccoli bread
directions: Melt margarine or butter.
Mix the eggs into butter.
Mix well.
Add all other ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until done in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: pineapple cookies
directions: Mix shortening, sugar and egg well.
Stir in pineapple. Measure flour.
Blend flour, soda and nutmeg; stir in.
Mix in nuts.
Chill 1 hour.
Heat oven to 400°.
Drop rounded teaspoonfuls 2 inches apart onto lightly greased baking sheet. Bake 8 to 10 minutes or until no imprint remains when lightly touched.
Makes 5 dozen.

title: green tomato pickles
directions: Soak tomatoes in water and lime for 24 hours.
Wash good. Soak washed tomatoes in cold ice water 4 hours.
Tie spices in little bag and put in with sugar and vinegar and bring to a boil. Pour over drained tomatoes and let stand overnight.
Bring to boil and boil for 1 hour.
Put in hot jars and seal.

title: williamsburg candied apples
directions: Boil the last 3 ingredients in a deep pan for 5 minutes; add apples, turning often.
Lift apples from pan.
Place in baking dish; pour liquid over apples.
Let cool.
Stuff apples with cream cheese and nuts.
This is a beautiful Christmas dish!!

title: ambrosia cake
directions: Mix all in mixer. Cook in 4 layers for 15 minutes at 350°.

title: chocolate cherry cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large bowl, combine flour, sugar, oil, eggs, vanilla, soda, cinnamon and salt; mix well.
Stir in cherry pie filling, chocolate chips and nuts.
Pour into tube pan which removes from pan.
Sprinkle confectioners sugar, if desired.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Heat milk; add to bread crumbs.
Add all other ingredients. Bake at 350° in greased casserole or loaf pan 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: In a large bowl, break lettuce; top with cauliflower and layer onion in thin slices with crisp bacon pieces.
I also use chopped fresh broccoli and thawed frozen peas.
Combine mayonnaise and sugar and spread over bacon; try to seal vegetables below.
Do not stir.
Cover and refrigerate for 24 hours.
Just before serving, add Parmesan cheese and toss.
Serves 5 to 6 with the added vegetables.

title: chili rellenos
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grate cheese and mix with chilis.
Turn into buttered casserole (I use 12 x 8 x 2-inch).
Beat egg whites until stiff.
In small bowl, combine yolks, milk,
flour, salt and pepper.
Fold in egg whites.
Pour mix over cheese and "ooze" into cheese.
Bake 30 minutes.
Arrange tomato slices on top (thin slices).
Bake 30 minutes longer.
Serves 8.

title: vanilla wafer cake
directions: Grease and flour a tube or Bundt pan.
Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into pan.
Bake 2 hours at 275°.

title: sweet and sour meatballs
directions: Combine beef, egg and seasoning; mix well.
Shape into small balls and brown in skillet.
Keep warm until ready to use.

title: spinach salad
directions: Cook bacon crisp; drain and crumble.
Combine oil, vinegar, sugar, salt and catsup; mix in blender or shake in bottle. Combine bacon and remaining ingredients; toss with dressing. Yield:
12 servings.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: In a large saucepot or Dutch oven, cook the ground beef, onions and garlic until beef is brown and onions are tender (about 5 minutes). Stir frequently. Drain off excess fat.
Stir in undrained tomatoes, tomato paste, 1 tablespoon salt, basil, sugar and chili powder.
Heat to boiling.
Reduce heat to low and simmer, uncovered, 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: play dough
directions: Mix together first 4 ingredients.
Add boiling water colored with choice of food coloring.
Mix well.
Knead until smooth.

title: double chocolate cheesecake
directions: Stir together the crumbs, sugar, cocoa and butter.
Press on bottom and 1 inch up side of 9-inch spring-form pan.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Combine all ingredients in a mixing bowl, ending with flour. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
(Spoon by teaspoons onto cookie sheet.)

title: seafoam salad
directions: Drain juice from pears and heat in microwave for 2 minutes. Mix hot pear juice with lime Jell-O and mix with a mixer. Set in refrigerator to cool and thicken. Smash pears with a fork. Add pears, cream cheese, Cool Whip, cottage cheese and pecans to the lime Jell-O. Refrigerate.

title: rice and broccoli casserole
directions: Melt butter in casserole dish.
Add rest of ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix together and place strips of bacon on top.
Bake 1 1/2 to 2 hours at 350°.

title: oatmeal cookies(irene)
directions: Cream together the shortening, brown sugar and white sugar. Add eggs and vanilla; beat well.
Sift together flour, salt and soda.
Add together with oatmeal and nuts.

title: carrot cake
directions: Sift flour and next 4 ingredients and sift again.
Set aside. Combine oil and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time and beat well after each egg.
Add dry ingredients slowly.
Blend well.
Add carrots and nuts.
Blend well.
Pour into a well-greased 9 x 13-inch pan or three well-greased 8-inch cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Frost when cake has cooled.

title: shanghai party pleasers
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving juice.
In medium saucepan, combine brown sugar, cornstarch and ginger; mix well.
Add combined pineapple juice, water, 1/4 cup pineapple and margarine; mix well. Bring to a boil over medium-high heat; reduce heat.
Simmer about 1 minute, stirring frequently or until sauce is thickened and clear. Set aside.
Heat oven to 400°.

Lightly spray rack of 13 x 9-inch baking pan with vegetable oil cooking spray or oil lightly. Combine turkey, oat bran, yogurt, water chestnuts, onions, soy sauce, egg white, ginger, salt and remaining pineapple; mix well. Shape into 1-inch balls.
Place on prepared rack.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes or until golden brown.
Serve with pineapple sauce.

title: tortilla soup
directions: Combine all soups, water, corn, green beans, tomatoes, chilies and seasoning
mix in Dutch oven on medium-high heat.
Bring mixture to a boil.
Reduce heat; simmer 10 minutes.
Stir in tortilla strips and cheese.
Continue to cook until tortilla strips are softened and cheese is melted.

title: steak and dumplings
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Bake first 6 ingredients in a deep casserole dish for 2 1/2 hours.
Put dumplings on top. Bake 20 minutes more.
Makes 4 to 5 servings.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Whip cream cheese and sugar until smooth.
Add peanut butter; blend well.
Mix in Cool Whip.
Blend well then spoon all into graham cracker crust.
Chill.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Combine dry ingredients and nuts.
Beat eggs slightly.
Add sugar, oil and vanilla.
Beat until creamy.
Add zucchini and pineapple.
Combine with dry ingredients.
Bake in loaf pans at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Cool 10 minutes before removing from pans.

title: taco pie
directions: Heat oven to 400 F.
Grease 8 x 8 dish.
Cook ground beef and onion until beef is brown, drain.
Stir in seasoning mix; spoon into dish.
Beat bisquick, milk and eggs with wire whisk until smooth, about 1 minute, pour into dish.
Bake 25 minutes, top with sliced tomato and cheese, bake until cheese is melted, 2-4 minutes.

title: rose's red velvet cake(revised)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Grease and flour two 9-inch cake pans. Combine Nesquik and food color; set aside. Cream together the sugar and Crisco, then add in the food color mixture. Add eggs and beat well. Blend in the salt, vanilla, vinegar and baking soda. Beat in buttermilk and flour, alternating between the two, ending with the flour. Bake for 30 minutes or until a pick in the center comes out clean. Frost when completely cool.

title: sausage egg bake
directions: Spread croutons in buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cover with sausage and mushrooms.
Mix eggs with milk and pour into pan.
Top with cheese.
Put in refrigerator overnight.
Mix mushroom soup and milk.
Pour over mixture.
Bake at 350° for 60 minutes.

title: old fashioned pound cake
directions: Cream butter; slowly add sugar, beating well at medium speed with electric mixer.
Add eggs one at a time beating well after each addition.
Add flour to creamed mixture alternately with milk, ending with flour.
Mix until well blended.
Fold in flavoring.

title: pizza chicken
directions: Place chicken, skin side down, in baking pan and pour remaining mixed ingredients over chicken.
Turn at the end of 45 minutes.
Bake 1-1/2 hours at 350 degrees, until done.

title: grilled italian chicken
directions: In a bowl, combine salad dressing and teriyaki sauce.
Remove 1/4 cup for basting; cover and refrigerate.
Place chicken in a large resealable plastic bag; add remaining marinade.
Seal bag and turn to coat; refrigerate for 8 hours or overnight, turning occasionally.
Drain and discard marinade.
Grill chicken, covered, over medium heat for 3 minutes on each side.
Baste with reserved marinade.
Grill 3 to 4 minutes longer on each side or until juices run clear. Yield: 6 servings.

title: chicken and green bean casserole
directions: Put green beans in casserole. Add chicken.
Pour lemon juice over chicken. Add mushrooms.
Mix in bowl the soups and Miracle Whip.
Pour over all. Cover with croutons and melted butter. Top with 1/2 pound grated Cheddar cheese.
Bake 40 minutes at 350°.

title: zucchini cake
directions: Mix zucchini, sugar, oil and cinnamon.
Add eggs.
Mix all dry ingredients together, then add to zucchini mixture.
Add walnuts. Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: cod fish accras
directions: Note:
Omit one of the peppers if you want to decrease hot spice taste.

title: pesto chicken fajitas
directions: Cook chicken in oil over medium heat for 3 to 5 minutes or until tender.
Remove from skillet.
Add onions and peppers; saute 3 to 5 minutes.
Return chicken to skillet.
Stir in pesto sauce and cheese.
Cook until thoroughly heated.
Spoon onto tortillas, fold in half and serve immediately.

title: beef and rice casserole
directions: Brown meat, onions, celery and green pepper.
Scald rice in boiling water for 10 minutes; rinse in cold water.
Combine with meat mixture and add soups, water and soy sauce.
Mixture will seem watery, but will thicken as it bakes.
Bake 2 hours and 30 minutes at 350°.
Omit scalding if using Minute rice.
Yields 12 servings.

title: green punch
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Freeze part of it in an ice tray. Refrigerate the rest.
Before serving, put cubes in punch bowl and add rest of mixture.
Slice lemons and let float on top.

title: plain ole vanilla wedding cake
directions: Cream together sugar, vanilla and butter in bathtub.
Stir together flour and baking powder in a separate tub.
Find a larger container perhaps an unused grain silo.
Add cake flour to creamed mixture, alternately adding milk.
Fold in egg whites.
Pour into as many number 12 washtubs as you can find, making all layers about the same size.
Cover washtubs and place in a building that will take 28 to 30 minutes to burn down.
Remove from debris.
Frost with relatively new rowboat oars.
Serves everybody.

title: beef tips in mushroom and wine sauce
directions: Salt and pepper cubed steak and saute in butter.
Add garlic, onion and mushrooms and saute until done.
Add sherry and red wine; simmer for about 20 to 30 minutes.
Thicken with a flour paste.

title: chicken noodle casserole
directions: Cut chicken in bite size pieces and saute in butter.
Slice mushrooms and saute in butter.
Cook artichoke hearts according to directions on package; chop.
Boil noodles according to package directions and drain.
Add all ingredients.
Do not cook peas. Pour all ingredients in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle top with grated Parmesan cheese and grated Cheddar cheese.
Bake in 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes, until cheese melts.

title: dirty rice and beans
directions: Brown sausage and onion; add kidney beans and tomatoes.
Add salt and cumin.
Simmer 25 to 30 minutes.
Near the end, add celery.
For a milder taste, can add 1/2 cup rice and 3/4 cup water.
Tastes better reheated.

title: jewish coffee cake
directions: Mix ingredients with spoon. Will be slightly lumpy. Pour 1/2 of the batter in greased Bundt or angel food cake pan. Then add 1/2 topping mix (1/2 cup sugar plus 2 teaspoons cinnamon; stir until blended). Pour remaining batter over topping, then add remaining topping. Swirl with knife. Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until when knife inserted in the middle, comes out clean.

title: lemon vegetable salad
directions: Use large bowl, dissolve jello in 2 cups hot water.
Add cheese, mayonnaise and nuts.
Fold in Cool Whip; let chill to set.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together except eggs; add one egg at a time and beat well after each one.
Bake at 350 degrees for 50 minutes.

title: baked potato casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. After baked potatoes have cooled enough to remove from skins, peel and cut into 1-inch cubes. Spread half the potatoes into a 13 x 9 pan. Salt and pepper to taste. Sprinkle with bacon pieces. Spread half of sour cream over potatoes. Sprinkle half the cheese over the sour cream. Spread remaining potatoes over the first layer. Salt and pepper to taste. Sprinkle with bacon pieces. Spread remaining sour cream. Sprinkle remaining cheese on top. Bake at 350° for about 20 minutes or until heated throughout. Serve hot.

title: never fail pastry
directions: Cut the shortening into the flour until pea size.
Add the cold water, egg and vinegar.
Add more water, if necessary, for right consistency.
Makes four 1 crust or 2 double crust pies. Will freeze or will keep in refrigerator 2 to 3 weeks. Also good for sausage rolls.

title: pecan dreams (cookies)
directions: Cream butter and sugar. Add vanilla, flour and nuts. Roll into small balls. Place on ungreased cookie sheet and bake 30 to 40 minutes at 300°. Roll in powdered sugar while hot, then again when cooled.

title: mound cake
directions: Bake cake as directed.
Cool.
Slice each layer in half. Bring milk and sugar to boil.
Add coconut until thickens.
Spread between layers.
Heat a small amount of milk and Kisses.
Stir until melted. Pour over cake.

title: chicken soup
directions: Cook all together until onion and chicken are done.
Season as you like.

title: amish sugar cream pie
directions: Cook sugar, cornstarch and milk, cream or half and half until thick.
Stir in butter or oleo and vanilla.
Sprinkle with nutmeg or cinnamon.
Pour in baked pie crust.
Bake for 15 minutes at 375° or until starts to bubble.

title: sand tarts
directions: Soften margarine.
Blend all ingredients by hand.
Form into fingers.
Bake on cookie sheet at 300° for 30 to 45 minutes.
Roll in powdered sugar while still hot.

title: apple salad
directions: Mix all together.
Serves up to 10 people.

title: overnight caramel rolls
directions: Mix 2 cups flour, 1/3 cup sugar, the salt and yeast in large bowl.
Add warm milk, 1/3 cup margarine and the egg.
Beat 2 minutes, scraping bowl often.
Stir in enough flour to make dough easy to handle.
Turn dough onto floured board and knead about 5 minutes until smooth.
Place in greased bowl and turn greased side up.
Cover and let rise in warm place about 1 1/2 hours until double.

title: irish soda bread
directions: Sift dry ingredients; add currants. Mix eggs, buttermilk and melted butter, then gradually add to dry mixture. Spoon into greased bread loaf pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Toothpick test for doneness.

title: scripture cake
directions: Add ingredients as listed, one at a time.
Mix well as each ingredient is added.

title: cheesecake cookies
directions: Cream butter and brown sugar until light and fluffy.
Add flour and nuts; blend until mixture resembles crumbs.
Set aside 1 cup. Press remaining mixture into 10 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Combine sugar and cheese and beat until smooth. Add eggs, milk, lemon juice and vanilla; beat well.
Spread over baked crust.
Sprinkle reserved crumbs over top.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Cool and cut into bars.
Chill.

title: honey mousse
directions: Separate the white from the yolk of the eggs.
Then mix yolks with liquid honey.
(If honey is set and thick, stand jar on piece of wood in warm or hot water, until it liquifies).
Cook on very low heat, stirring constantly, or preferably in a double boiler, until the mixture thickens like a custard.
Remove from stove and cool.
Whisk egg whites until stiff and fold into the mixture. Pour into either individual dishes or one dish and chill.
It should be left for several hours before serving.

title: texas gravy
directions: Heat oil in skillet.
Add flour, stirring until smooth and tan in color.
Add milk.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Season to taste.

title: vodka slush
directions: Mix and freeze 24 hours.
Serve 1 or 2 ice cream scoops in a glass and fill with 7-Up.
Makes 1 gallon.

title: summer sausage
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Refrigerate in a covered bowl.
Mix once a day for 3 days.
On the 4th day, mix and form in rolls.
Place on rack or broiler pan and bake at 175° for 8 hours.
Turn once.

title: taco casserole
directions: In baking dish, start with Doritos; cover with 1/2 pound hamburger, 1/2 of onion, 1/2 cheese.
Pour 1/2 sauce mixture and layer again.
Bake at 350° to 375° for 45 minutes.

title: cheesecake
directions: Melt butter, add graham crackers crumbs and sugar.
Mix well. Press into bottom of 9-inch spring dish.
Combine and beat all other ingredients in large mixing bowl.
Pour into crumb lined pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Cool for 1 hour in oven with door open. Serve with strawberries or cherries.
Serves 10.

title: my favorite dessert
directions: Put apricots on bottom of an 8 x 8 glass pan.
Pour dry cake mix over fruit.
Pour melted margarine over all.
Bake 350° for 35 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: chicken chow bake
directions: Combine chicken, soup, pineapple, soy sauce, celery and onion. Mix well. Gently fold in noodles (reserve 1 1/2 cups).
Turn into casserole dish and top with remaining noodles.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until heated through and hot.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.
tags: cream of chicken soup or mushroom soup

title: apricot bread
directions: Mix all together and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: baked wild turkey
directions: Pat turkey dry with paper towel.
Salt and pepper inside the body and neck cavities.
Mix croutettes, onions, celery and butter as listed on package.
Saute onions and celery in butter.
Add mushrooms and heat.
Add to croutettes in a large bowl.
Toss until coated.
Add boiling water; mix.
Add enough to make it stick. Pack into body and neck cavities.
Use bread ends to hold stuffing in.
Place turkey in lightly greased roasting pan, breast up. Cover tightly with aluminum foil.
Put on lid.
Bake at 350° about 30 minutes or until juices run clear.
Don't overbake (1 hour for small or 2 1/2 hours for large).

title: mile high meringue
directions: Combine egg whites, sugar and cream of tartar in a large bowl. Add boiling water and beat at once until very thick and fluffy. Add vanilla.
Bake just until brown at 350°.

title: no flour peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix sugar and egg.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well. Roll into balls and flatten with fork.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes on ungreased cookie sheet.
Makes approximately 3 dozen.

title: margarita pie
directions: Combine butter, pretzels and sugar.
Press mixture into pie pan and freeze until firm.
Beat together milk, lime juice, tequila and Triple Sec.
Add thawed strawberries and fold into whipping cream.
Mound mixture into pie shell and freeze for 2 hours.
Remove and wrap airtight and freeze overnight.
Put in refrigerator 30 minutes before serving.

title: strawberry ice cream
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Pour into electric ice cream freezer.

title: pecan candy cake
directions: Heat oven to 250°.
Chop all fruit.
Add fruit to large bowl. Sprinkle flour; toss to coat well.
Add pecans and coconut.
Toss to mix.
Add sweetened milk; stir to mix well.
(I use my hands.) Spoon evenly into greased tube pan.
Bake in slow oven 1 1/2 hours.
Wrap tightly in foil.
Refrigerate.

title: mexican cheese meat dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
If needed, thicken with cornstarch and water.
Serve over Doritos or Tostitos.

title: ten minute pie
directions: Arrange fruit on cake:
row of bananas (overlapping) down center, overlapping berries on each side of bananas, whole grapes on each side of berries and berries on each side of grapes.

title: creamy basil tortellini
directions: In skillet, saute garlic in margarine until tender.
Stir in soup mix (dry) and cream.
Heat to boiling.
Simmer uncovered 10 minutes.
Stir in basil, parsley, cheese and cooked tortellini. Heat through.

title: yogurt pie
directions: Mix yogurt
and Cool Whip.
Stir in dry jello.	Pour in pie shell and chill.

title: leah's cauliflower soup
directions: Cook cauliflower in boiling, salted water until tender; drain and reserve liquid.
Melt butter and cook with onions until soft; add flour.
Add broth and cook, stirring constantly until mixture boils.
Stir in 1 cup reserved liquid, milk, Worcestershire and salt.
Add cauliflower.
Heat to boiling.
Stir in cheese and sprinkle with parsley.

title: grandmother whitley's sweet cucumber pickles
directions: Mix 2 gallons water and 2 cups lime.
Add sliced cucumbers. Soak 12 to 14 hours.
(Stir occasionally.)
Drain.
Rinse.
Soak in salt water 4 hours (2 cups salt).
Drain.
Rinse.
Soak in clear water 2 hours.
Drain.

title: lime-jello salad
directions: Chill Carnation milk before starting recipe.
Mix lime jello with 5 cups boiling water.
Chill jello for a while until soft set.
Add pineapple, cottage cheese and mayonnaise and mix well. Whip the Carnation milk and add.
Mix well and chill.

title: velvety cocoa cream pie
directions: Prepare pie shell; set aside.
Combine cocoa, sugar, cornstarch and salt in medium saucepan.
Gradually blend milk into dry ingredients, stirring until smooth.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until mixture boils.
Boil and stir 3 minutes. Remove from heat.
Blend in butter and vanilla.
Pour into prepared crust.
Carefully press plastic wrap directly onto pie filling.
Chill 3 to 4 hours.

title: easy fruit cobbler
directions: Beat together flour, sugar and milk.
Melt margarine in casserole dish.
Pour batter into margarine and put fruit on top. Do not stir.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: mound cake
directions: Cook milk, margarine and sugar 10 minutes or until becomes syrupy.
Remove from heat.
Add marshmallows and beat until smooth; add coconut and vanilla.
Pour over bottom half of cake. Place other half of cake on top.

title: apple loaf
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Blend in beaten eggs and apples. Stir in dry ingredients.
Blend in nuts.
Bake 55 to 60 minutes at 300°.

title: yummy butterfinger cake
directions: Follow the directions for a yellow cake mix and bake.
While the cake is still warm, take a wooden handle spoon and poke holes in the top of the cake.
Mix the caramel topping and condensed milk.
Pour the mixture over the cake while it is warm.
Crunch 3 large Butterfingers over the top of the caramel mixture.
Spread 16 ounces Cool Whip on top.
Crunch 3 more Butterfinger candy bars on top of Cool Whip.
Refrigerate for at least 1 hour before serving. Easy...easy!

title: turkey chili
directions: In a 6-quart pot, brown turkey and onion in oil over medium-high heat.
Drain off any excess fat.
Peel and crush garlic; add to turkey mixture with chili powder, salt, chiles, crushed tomatoes and juice and beans.
Stir well.
Heat to boiling stirring often.
Reduce to low heat and simmer, stirring occasionally, about 30 minutes.
Serve topped with sour cream, Cheddar cheese and guacamole, if desired.

title: low-fat cheesecake
directions: Put the ingredients into blender.
Put the lemon juice in last. Bake for 50 minutes in a 350° oven.
Use a graham cracker crust; don't overbake.

title: slow cooker beef stew
directions: Coat stew meat with flour, salt and pepper.
Brown in oil. Add remaining ingredients; slow cook on high 5 to 6 hours, or until meat is tender and vegetables are soft.

title: olive jean's coahoma marinated carrots
directions: Mix vinegar, sugar and salad oil.
Bring to a boil.
Remove from heat and cool.
Place carrots in shallow dish.
Sprinkle with chopped vegetables.
Pour cooled vinegar mixture over all. Refrigerate several hours before serving.
These will keep for weeks in the refrigerator.
Serves 12.

title: pink fluff salad
directions: Bring pineapple to a boil.
Stir jello with hot pineapple. Let cool.
Add cottage cheese and Cool Whip.
Mix well and chill.

title: meat and potatoes with gravy(one pot dinner)
directions: Combine mushroom soup and milk in medium pot and blend together. Brown steaks in skillet on both sides.
Don't overcook meat. Add to mushroom soup and milk mixture. Put potatoes on top of meat. Salt and pepper to taste.
Cover and cook 25 minutes or until potatoes are done (low heat).

title: cheese rolls
directions: Cream together cream cheese and Cheddar cheese; add garlic powder and roll in chili powder.
Makes 4 to 6 rolls.
Serve with crackers.

title: spanish rice
directions: In large skillet, fry bacon until crisp.
Add onion and green pepper.
Cook until onion is yellow.
Drain most of fat.
Add remaining ingredients and bacon.
Cook over low heat, uncovered, about 15 minutes.

title: potatoes with cheese
directions: Cook potatoes with skins.
Drain, peel and whip with a pinch of salt.
Blend remaining ingredients mixture.
Should be moist. Pile into baking dish and bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: make-ahead cabbage salad
directions: Combine vegetables and mix well.
In small bowl mix mayonnaise with milk and salt until smooth.
Pour over vegetables and toss. Chill before serving.

title: extra special spinach dip
directions: Blend the Lipton soup mix, sour cream, mayonnaise and lemon juice.
Stir in the spinach and water chestnuts.
Chill 2 to 3 hours before serving.

title: corn chowder
directions: Cook bacon; reserve 3 tablespoons bacon drippings.
Lightly brown.
Add diced potatoes and water; cook over medium heat until potatoes are tender, 10 to 15 minutes.
Add corn, milk, salt and dash of pepper.
Cook until heated through.
Pour into warmed bowls.
Top with crumbled bacon and a pat of butter.
Serve with crackers.
Makes 4 to 5 servings.

title: pineapple sheet cake
directions: Mix and pour into greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: mickey's hawaiian ribs
directions: Fry ribs until browned and well done.
Mix all other ingredients and pour over cooked ribs into a large, heavy pan. Simmer several hours.
Stir occasionally.
More barbecue sauce may be added according to taste.
Serve over steamed rice.

title: pepperoni-vegetable rolls
directions: Combine all ingredients, except bread, in a small bowl; stir well and set aside.
Cut a thick slice from top of bread. Carefully remove soft bread from inside top and bottom of loaf, leaving about 1/4-inch shells.

title: fried apple pies
directions: Soak apples overnight. Drain well. Cover apples with water and cook about 1 hour until soft.

Drain. Add remaining ingredients. Mash and combine. Roll out pastry on waxed paper, 1/3 at a time. Cut out pastry in circles, using a 5-inch saucer as a measure. Place about 3 tablespoons of apple mixture on each pastry circle. To seal pies, dip fingers in cold water and moisten edges of circle. Fold in half, making sure edges are even.
Using a floured fork, press edges of pastry firmly together.
Cook pies until brown in 1-inch heated oil. Turn only once. Drain on paper towel. Eat!

title: rice pilaf
directions: Brown until golden the orzo in margarine.
Add rice, broth and water.
Bring to a boil and lower to simmer for 25 to 30 minutes or until all liquid is absorbed into rice.

title: cheese sauce for broccoli
directions: Melt margarine in saucepan.
Add next four ingredients.
Add cheese; heat until cheese melts.
Drain broccoli and pour sauce over it.

title: hot fruit
directions: Drain fruit, reserving the juice from pineapple chunks.
Layer fruit in an oblong baking dish.

title: corn and tomato soup
directions: Bring corn and tomatoes to boil and simmer about 5 minutes. Add okra and cook about 15 minutes or until okra is tender.
Fry bacon and use bacon grease to season the soup.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into two bread pans and bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or in a 13 x 9-inch pan for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: pickle bunny bites(preparation time: 15 minutes plus marinating)
directions: Prepare salad dressing mix as directed on package. Place salad dressing and carrot halves in zipper-style plastic bag. Refrigerate 2 hours or overnight to marinate. Drain. Reserve salad dressing. Wrap 1 ham strip around 1 pickle half and 1 carrot half. Secure with toothpick. Serve with reserved salad dressing for dipping.

title: monkey cake(pick-apart-cake)
directions: Mix 1 cup of sugar and 2 tablespoons of cinnamon together with roll quarters.
Mix margarine, 1 tablespoon of cinnamon and 1 cup of sugar well and boil a few minutes to make syrup.
Put half of roll pieces in ungreased tube pan and pour half of the syrup into it.
Put rest of rolls in and pour in rest of syrup.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
You can use raisins or nuts, but they go in the pan first.
As soon as it is done, turn upside down on a plate. Best served warm, but good cold, too.
Just pick it apart piece by piece.

title: potato salad
directions: Dice and cook potatoes until soft (not mushy).
Dice boiled eggs.
Mix potatoes and eggs with 2 to 3 tablespoons mustard and 1 pint mayonnaise.
Mix in 2/3 of a 16 oz. jar of pickle relish. Salt to taste.

title: coconut macaroons
directions: Beat egg whites with vanilla and salt until soft peaks form. Gradually add sugar, beating until stiff, but not dry.
Fold in coconut.
Drop rounded teaspoonfuls on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 325° for about 20 minutes.
Immediately remove cookies to rack. Makes 18.

title: if its
directions: Open door to refrigerator and announce, "If you can find it, you can eat it."
Make sure when using this for smaller children, the Father is there to supervise to supervise.

title: stuffed zucchini squash
directions: Wash zucchini, cut off ends, don't pare.
Cook in boiling, salted water 5 minutes.
Halve lengthwise, remove pulp with spoon; combine with bread crumbs, cheese, onion, salt and pepper and eggs.
Fill zucchini shells, dot with butter and sprinkle with more cheese.
Bake in moderate oven (350°) for 30 minutes.

title: zelma's red hot pears
directions: Peel, core pears and cut in halves or fourths.
Place pears in boiling syrup made with above ingredients.
Bring to a boil. Place in jars and seal.

title: chicken divan
directions: Boil, debone and cut chicken into chunks.
Layer chicken and broccoli in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cover with slices of Velveeta. Spread soup and mayonnaise mixture and sprinkle with Durkee onions.
Bake, uncovered, for 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: alberta toomey's corn bread
directions: Mix ingredients together and cook until thick.
Put in baking dish.
Bake at 350° for approximately 1 hour.

title: vegetable juice
directions: Mix vegetables in large kettle; cook 30 minutes.
Put through a sieve, then add seasonings.
Chill and serve, or heat and can in sterilized jars.
Makes 6 quarts.

title: fudge cakes
directions: Bake in greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan for approximately 20 minutes at 325°.
Take out while still soft on top.
Cut in squares while still warm and roll in powdered sugar.

title: blue cheese dressing
directions: Blend together and store in an airtight container in refrigerator.

title: baked corn
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Place in a 2-quart baking dish. Bake 1 hour and 15 minutes at 350°.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Melt butter.
Add flour and seasonings.
Blend; add milk. Cook slow until thick and smooth; add cheese and stir until melted.

title: peanut butter pie(frozen dessert)
directions: Cream the cream cheese, peanut butter, milk and powdered sugar until smooth.
Add Cool Whip and mix well.
Pour into crust. Freeze until firm.

title: walking taco salad
directions: Mix beans, taco mix and meat; place in bottom of 9 x 13-inch dish.
Cover with cheese.
Mix dip, sour cream and lemon juice. Place on top of cheese.
Cover with more cheese.
Continue layering the rest of ingredients alternating and topping with cheese.
Store in refrigerator until ready to serve with tortilla chips.

title: kolbasi with vegetables
directions: Melt shortening in skillet.
