Brown kolbasi pieces; add green peppers and saute until soft.
Add rest of the vegetables and seasonings and simmer for 3/4 of an hour.
Add flour and cook slowly for 10 minutes, stir or it will scorch.
Serve with potatoes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: baked eggplant
directions: Pare and dice eggplant; soak in cold water and cook until tender.
Drain and mash.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake in buttered baking dish until brown.
Makes 4 servings.

title: pork chops
directions: Spread yogurt on both sides of chops to make crumbs stick. Place in a casserole dish and cook in oven at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cheesecake
directions: Save 1 cup dry cake mix; set aside.
Combine remaining cake mix, 1 egg and oil.
In small bowl, mix until crumbly.
Press on bottom and halfway up sides of 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
In large bowl, blend cream cheese, sugar, lemon juice and vanilla.
Add 3 eggs and rest of cake mix.
Beat 1 minute and add milk.
Beat until smooth.
Pour onto crust.
Bake at 300° for 45 to 50 minutes until center is firm.
Cool and put pie filling on top.

title: baked chicken oriental
directions: Cut chicken in pieces; dredge with mixture of flour, seasoning salt and pepper.
Place in a greased 2-quart shallow baking dish. Combine remaining ingredients; pour over chicken.
Cover and bake in a 375° oven for 1 hour.
Remove cover and bake 30 minutes longer, basting several times.
Serves 4.

title: roll-ups
directions: Cut salami in strips.
Spread with mixture.
Roll with cut pickle in middle.
Use a toothpick to hold.

title: poor man's cake
directions: Boil raisins in water 5 minutes.
Let cool slightly.
Add sugar and shortening; stir together flour, baking soda, cloves, nutmeg, cinnamon and salt.
Mix all together.
Bake in a greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish at 350° for 35 minutes or until cake tests done.
If using a Bundt pan, bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: jo's texas sheet cake
directions: In a bowl, add sugar and flour. Set aside. In a 2-quart saucepan, add next 4 ingredients and bring to a boil, then add to the flour and sugar mixture. Add next 5 ingredients to the batter mixture. Place in a greased 13 x 15-inch cookie sheet and bake 20 minutes at 400°.

title: sam's pound cake with apricot brandy
directions: Cream the butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Combine dry ingredients; add to creamed mixture.
Combine sour cream with flavorings and brandy; add to cake batter and mix well.
Bake in a large, well-greased and floured tube pan at 325° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.
Let cool in pan before removing.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Mix all ingredients well in a large bowl.
Chill and serve.

title: mama's oatmeal cake
directions: Pour water over oatmeal. Let set 20 minutes. Cream together brown sugar, butter and sugar. Add oatmeal, then add remaining ingredients. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes in 9 x 13 pan.

title: stromboli sandwich
directions: Cut lengthwise slice off top of bread.
Scoop out center to form a shell.
Place half the cheese on bottom of shell.
Fill with meat and spaghetti sauce mixture.
Cover with remaining cheese, then replace top slice of bread.

title: tangerine marmalade
directions: Wash tangerines and lemon.
Quarter.
Remove seeds.
Put through food chopper.
Measure the ground citrus.
Add 4 cups water to 2 cups of pulp.
Bring to a boil and cook on low heat 1 hour or until volume is about half that it was in the beginning. Stand overnight.
This extracts pectin from the lemon.
Measure out 3 cups of stock.
Add 3 cups sugar.
Cook until candy or jelly thermometer reads 222°.
Let cool to 190°.
Pour in clean jars. Close with self-sealing lids at once.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Blend first four ingredients together; fold in Cool Whip and pour into desired type of crust.
Freeze.
Set out of freezer a short time before serving.

title: peanut butter sticks
directions: Take the sandwich bread and cut off the crusts. Cut each slice into 5 strips.
Bake crusts and strips in a 225° oven for 1 hour. Turn oven off and leave sticks in oven until cool.
Crush the dried crusts with a rolling pin.
Mix the peanut butter with the oil.
Mix until smooth.
Dip sticks into peanut butter mix until covered. Roll in the crusts.
Put on paper towels to set. When set, if any are left, pack in Ziploc bags.

title: chili sauce
directions: Cook tomatoes with salt until tender.
Skim off 2 cups liquid (for shorter cooking time).
Add other ingredients and cook until thick, stirring occasionally.
Pour into hot, sterilized jars and seal.
Makes about 4 quarts.

title: baked chicken
directions: Butter skillet; salt and pepper chicken.
Place in skillet. Dot with butter.
Put chopped onions, celery and carrots on top of chicken.
Cover and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Uncover and bake 30 more minutes.
Good with rice.

title: fantastic frozen peanut butter pie
directions: Beat the cream cheese until fluffy.
Gradually add sugar.
Add peanut butter, mixing well.
Gradually stir in the milk.
Add vanilla.
Gradually fold in the whipped cream with a rubber spatula.
Freeze at least 4 hours or overnight.
Bring out 20 minutes before serving.

title: fresh apple pecan cake
directions: Combine in large bowl the first 5 ingredients.
In separate bowl, combine the next 3 ingredients.
Mix bowls together well. Add vanilla.
Grease and flour a tube pan.
Place cake in cold oven to bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Grind cranberries and let set in 1 cup sugar for 8 hours. Dissolve Jell-O in 1 to 1 1/2 cups water; let begin to gel.
Mix all other ingredients together and blend into partially gelled Jell-O.
Let gel fully.
Serves 10 to 12 (at least).
Great for large family gatherings and keeps well in refrigerator.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Heat oil in skillet; add onion, pepper, celery and garlic and cook about 10 minutes until soft, stirring frequently.
Add tomatoes, tomato paste, seasonings and parsley; mix well.
Simmer over low heat, uncovered, for
one hour or until thickened; pour over cooked spaghetti.

title: fruit salad
directions: In a large bowl, mix together all the ingredients.
Set aside.

title: barbecue green beans
directions: Fry bacon and onion. Drain and crumble bacon.
Mix all ingredients together and place in casserole. Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours, covered part of the time.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: chicken poppy cosh
directions: Saute chicken and onion in olive oil.
While sauteing, sprinkle paprika over chicken.
After chicken is lightly cooked, add water to cover chicken.
Add cream of chicken soup by tablespoons into the water (do not stir then).
Cover and cook for 1 hour or until chicken is tender.
Debone chicken; put meat back in liquid in the pot.
Cook noodles according to the box; drain noodles.
Put some noodles in a bowl; add some meat and juice over noodles.

title: candied sweet potatoes
directions: Parboil potatoes for 15 minutes. Place in a buttered baking dish. Combine sugar, salt, butter and water in a saucepan. Boil for 3 minutes. Pour sauce over sweet potatoes. Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Baste occasionally.

title: squash and apple bake
directions: Cut
each
squash in half.
Remove seeds.
Pare squash. Cut into
1/2-inch
slices.
Stir
the
remaining ingredients together except for apple slices.
Arrange squash in ungreased baking dish 11
x 7 x 1-inch or a 9 x 13-inch.
Top with apple slices. Sprinkle
sugar
mixture
over top.
Cover with foil. Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes or until squash is tender.

title: stir fried green beans
directions: In a large skillet, heat oil over medium heat.
Add beans. Stir-fry about 3 minutes or until barely tender.
Add sugar, salt and chicken stock.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer 10 minutes.
Mix cornstarch and water until smooth.
Add to skillet.
Stir until beans are glazed.
Makes about 4 servings.

title: italian meatballs
directions: Mix all ingredients together and form small meatballs and brown in oil.
Then cook in 1 jar prepared spaghetti sauce for 30 minutes.

title: sea island gumbo
directions: Add okra, onion, garlic, salt and pepper.
Add water, tomato sauce, tomatoes and bay leaves.
Add Tabasco and cooked, peeled shrimp.
Cook mixture on medium heat about 5 minutes.
Place 1/2 cup of cooked rice in bottom of each bowl and ladle gumbo over rice.

title: chicken and rice pilaf
directions: In a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish, combine all ingredients, except chicken and seasonings.
Brush chicken with melted butter and seasonings.
Cover and bake at 375° for 1 hour and 15 minutes. Cook, uncovered, the last 10 or 15 minutes.

title: special "k" bars
directions: Stir Karo syrup and sugar together in a saucepan and bring to a boil.
Take off the stove, add the peanut butter and stir well. Stir in the cereal.
Place in a 9 x 13-inch buttered pan.
Put the Hershey bars on top and place under the broiler until chocolate is soft; spread the chocolate.

title: beef tenderloin
directions: Line pan with aluminum foil. Make a paste with ingredients. Use half of mixture on top of roast. Broil 7 minutes. Turn roast. Use remaining 1/2 paste and broil 7
minutes more. Seal with foil. Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Slice thinly and serve with horseradish sauce and thinly sliced bread.

title: vanishing oatmeal raisin cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350.
Beat together butter & sugars until creamy. Add eggs & vanilla.
Beat well.
Add combined flour, baking soda & salt.
Mix well.
Stir in oats & raisins or chips; mix well.
Drop by rounded tablespoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 10-12 minutes or until golden brown; remove to wire rack.
Bar cookies: Bake 30-35 minutes in ungreased 13x9 inch baking pan.

title: fresh apple muffins
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put in slightly greased muffin tins or in 2 small loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes. Makes 36 muffins.

title: rhubarb custard pie
directions: Mix sugar, cornstarch, salt and soda together. Add milk, mix well. Fold in rhubarb. Beat egg yolks and add to rhubarb mixture. Cook in double boiler until thick. Pour into 9 inch baked pie shell. Cover with meringue and bake until brown at 350°.

title: finger jello
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in a large bowl.
Mix in 2 1/2 cups boiling water, stirring all the time, until clear and smooth. Add 1/2 teaspoon vanilla.
Pour into 8 x 8-inch pan.
Chill in refrigerator.
Cut into cubes.
Will not melt at room temperature.

title: vanilla cream pie(recipe from university of tennessee, 1940)
directions: Mix sugar, flour,
cornstarch and salt in top of double boiler.
Add
milk
slowly;
stir and cook over the fire until boiling
point
is
reached.
Place over hot water and cook 20 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add well beaten egg yolks and butter; stir for 2 minutes.
Remove from fire and add vanilla. Cool
and turn into a cooked pastry shell.
Spread with margarine and bake 15 minutes in slow oven at 300°.

title: italian chicken cutlets
directions: Place chicken breast, bone side up, between 2 pieces of waxed paper.
Working from center, gently pound chicken until about 1/4-inch thick.
Repeat with 3 remaining pieces.

title: spinach balls
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Form into balls 1 1/2 to 2 inches.
Cook at 325° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: baked pork chops
directions: Roll pork chops in flour, salt and pepper.
Put in pan and cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Remove foil and brown.

title: corny corn bread
directions: In a large mixing bowl, combine first 4 ingredients; mix well. Fold in corn. Pour batter into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 30-35 minutes. Makes 10 servings.

title: lemon delite
directions: Mix ingredients together and press into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Cool.

title: grandpa's maple syrup
directions: Bring water to a boil.
Pour in sugar and stir until completely dissolved. Continue simmering for 4 minutes.
Remove from heat and add maple flavoring.
For added richness, add 4 ounces commercially prepared maple syrup.
Serve on pancakes, waffles, biscuits or Britches Patches.

title: pineapple zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar and oil, then stir in flour and pudding mix, then pineapple, zucchini, raisins and nuts.
Blend well. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
This makes 2 large or 3 small loaves.

title: polly's christmas cookies
directions: Mix shortening, sugar and eggs; stir in milk.
Sift together flour, soda and salt; stir this into sugar and milk mixture. (Save back just a little flour to toss with fruit mixture to keep from sticking together.)
Toss fruit mixture first (with flour), then stir everything together and chill at least 1 hour before baking.
Bake 10 minutes at 375°.

title: mandarin orange salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Add sherbet; cool until partially set.
Fold in oranges and pineapple; turn into mold or deep dish.
Refrigerate until set before serving.

title: tuna and rice croquettes
directions: Combine slightly beaten egg yolk with flaked tuna.
Add rice and seasonings; chill.
Fold in beaten egg white.
Shape into 10 patties.
Roll in bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Serve hot with tomato or cheese slice.
Serves 10.

title: carrot-coconut-cherry bread
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Combine eggs, oil and milk. Add to flour mixture.
Add last 5 ingredients.
Turn into four well-greased and floured 16 ounce fruit or vegetable cans, from which top lid has been removed.
(Or you can use any small type loaf pan.)
Bake in 350° oven for 45 to 50 minutes.
Cool on rack. Wrap in foil and store in refrigerator.
Makes 4 loaves.

title: applesauce nut bread
directions: Blend sugar, applesauce, oil, egg whites and milk and then sift remaining ingredients. Combine all until well blended. Fold in 1/2 cup chopped walnuts. Spread in oiled and floured 9 x 5-inch loaf pan. Bake at 350° for 60 to 70 minutes.

title: cheese straws
directions: Cream the cream cheese and margarine together.
Squeeze through a cookie press onto an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Makes 6 dozen.

title: hot sausage cheese balls
directions: Combine all ingredients well.
Shape into small balls and bake on an ungreased cookie sheet about 15 minutes in a 400° oven.

title: crostini with olives and cheese
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Slice bread on the diagonal, about 3/8-inch thick.
Place slices on baking sheet and brush lightly with olive oil. Bake 8 to 10 minutes until crisp and browned around edges.
Remove rind from cheese and spread on toast.
Top with sliced olives.
Return to oven and bake 3 to 5 minutes, until cheese is melted and bubbly.
Place crostini on a serving board or platter.
Makes 30 pieces, about 15 servings. Bread can be toasted a day ahead of serving.

title: buttermilk salad
directions: Mix and heat pineapple and jello until jello dissolves.
Cool slightly.
Add buttermilk, pecans and Cool Whip.
Let set 2 hours or overnight.

title: go-carts
directions: You will need toothpicks.

title: tacorita
directions: Fix taco seasoning and meat according to package directions. Mix remaining ingredients. Simmer 20 minutes. Pour 1/3 soup mixture into meat. Roll into 12 small flour tortillas. Place into 13 x 9 pan. Pour remaining soup mixture over tacoritas. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes. Top with grated Cheddar cheese and bake for 5 minutes or until melted.

title: fresh mushroom soup
directions: Melt butter in soup pot.
Add sliced mushrooms and onions to pot.
Cook 5 minutes.
Add soup, undiluted.
Add salt, pepper and garlic.
Bring to boil, reduce to simmer and cook 25 minutes.

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: Combine sugar, water, cornstarch and salt.
Cook until clear. Remove from heat; add red food coloring.
Add jello.
Stir well. Let cool.
Put strawberries in baked pie shell.
Pour sauce over the berries.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix graham cracker crumbs, 6 Tbsp. melted butter, 6 Tbsp. powdered sugar, and pecans. Press into bottom of greased 9x13 inch pyrex dish. Mix beaten egg whites, 2 cups powdered sugar, and 1/2 cup melted butter. Pour over first layer. Slice bananas and sprinkle with lemon juice to keep them from turning brown. Add to previous layers. Drain pineapple well and pour over bananas. Cover with whipped topping. Refrigerate. Slice strawberries, sprinkle with sugar, and refrigerate. add to top of other layers just before serving.

title: chili con carne
directions: Saute onion and bell pepper in melted butter; when tender, add meat.
Cook until slightly brown.
Add other ingredients.
Simmer 30 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: ugly duckling cake
directions: Combine cake mix, fruit cocktail with syrup, 1 cup of coconut and eggs.
Blend, then beat at medium speed 2 minutes.
Pour into greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Sprinkle with brown sugar.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.
Bring butter, sugar and milk to a boil; boil 2 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Stir in remaining coconut; spoon over hot cake in pan.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat well together the eggs, sugar, syrup, flour, salt and vanilla.
Add pecans.
Mix well and turn into 2 unbaked pie crusts.
Bake in oven for about 10 minutes at 350°.
Turn oven temperature to 300° and bake until set, about 40 minutes.

title: swiss cheese bread
directions: Melt together butter, mustard, lemon juice, poppy seed, Beau Monde and onion.
Cut bread in crisscross pattern.
Drizzle butter between slices.
Then, place sliced Swiss cheese between slices. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: mint tea
directions: Boil all for 5 minutes.
Toss out mint.
Mix into pitcher of iced tea to taste.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Brown beef; drain.
Add salt, pizza sauce, tomato sauce, paste and ketchup.
Combine with cooked macaroni.
In large greased casserole dish, put half of mixture.
Sprinkle with cheeses; cover with remaining mixture.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: apple raisin coffee cake
directions: Mix together thoroughly the sugar, shortening and egg.
Stir in milk.
Sift together and stir in the flour, baking powder, salt and raisins.
Spread in 9-inch pan (greased).
Slice 2 apples and line on top of batter.
Mix cinnamon and sugar together and sprinkle on top of apples.
Bake 45 minutes in 350° oven.

title: date balls
directions: Mix eggs, sugar and dates in bowl.
Melt butter; add to eggs, sugar and dates.
Cook in electric skillet at 300° for 6 minutes, stirring continuously.
Pour over Rice Krispies.
Add coconut, vanilla and nuts.
Make in balls and roll in coconut.

title: dark chocolate cake
directions: Chocolate Mixture:
Place the half-cup of sugar, oil and cocoa in blender.
Gradually add and thoroughly blend in the hot milk. Set aside.

title: southwest burgers(good for low-fat diets.)
directions: Mash beans lightly (there will be whole beans and chunks). Mix all ingredients together well.
Makes 6 to 8 burgers. Grilling is the cooking method.

title: round steak
directions: Salt and pepper steak.
Put in foiled pan.
Pour mushroom soup over steak.
Sprinkle onion soup mix on top.
Cover with foil.
Bake in 325° for 1 1/2 hours.
Serve with white rice.

title: vegetable burritos
directions: Coat a Dutch oven with cooking oil spray, place on medium-high heat until hot.
Add onion, mushroom and garlic.
Saute until they are tender.
Add remaining vegetables and peppers.
Saute, stirring constantly until they are tender-crisp, about 10 minutes.
Drain; add green chilies and next 4 ingredients; stir well.
Spoon 1/3 cup mixture onto tortilla; sprinkle on cheese.
Fold over.
Serve.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa, milk and margarine together in large saucepan. Boil for 5 minutes. Remove from heat. Add vanilla, peanut butter and oats. Stir together. Use large spoon to scoop onto waxed paper. Let sit until cool and set.

title: "joggin' in a bottle"
directions: Mix well and chill.
Personally, I don't care for the stuff, but my daddy drinks it.

title: sweet potato salad
directions: In a large bowl, combine potatoes, pineapple, nuts, dates, celery and onion. Add 3/4 cup coconut and salt.
In a small bowl, mix sour cream, mayonnaise and curry powder until well blended. Add 1/2 of mixture to potatoes.
Toss lightly. Top with remaining dressing and rest of coconut.

title: american beauty cake
directions: Stir together first two ingredients and set aside.
Cream Crisco, sugar and eggs together.
Add food coloring and Nestle Quik.

title: mrs. sharman's date-nut bread
directions: Combine water, baking soda and dates in a small bowl and let stand until cool.
Mix sugar, salt and butter until light.
Beat in eggs.
Add date mixture.
Combine flour and baking powder and gradually add to the batter.
Fold in nuts.
Pour batter into a loaf pan that has been well buttered.
Let stand 20 minutes before baking.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Bake 1 1/4 hours.
Loosen loaf from the pan and invert on a cooling rack.
Pour 2 ounces or more rum or bourbon evenly over the bread before wrapping in plastic wrap for storage.
Makes one loaf.

title: cheesy potatoes
directions: Boil potatoes; cool, peel and grate.
Melt margarine and cheese in microwave.
Mix all ingredients in casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: southern sweet potato pecan bread
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease bottom of a loaf pan.
Mix flour, baking powder, salt and spices in mixing bowl, stirring with a spoon. Stir in sugar, eggs, oil and milk; stir to blend. Stir in remaining sweet potatoes, pecans and raisins.
Pour batter into prepared pan and bake 1 hour and 10 minutes or until a toothpick comes out clean.
Cool in pan 15 minutes, then remove from pan.

title: greek meatballs(keftethakia)
directions: Brown onions in a little butter and place in mixing bowl.
Add meat, breadcrumbs, eggs and seasoning and blend well.
Shape into tiny, bite-size balls.
Roll in flour and fry in hot oil.
Drain well.
Serve warm or cold.

title: amazing raisin cake
directions: On low speed, beat first 10 ingredients two minutes; stir in apples, raisins and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes or until done.
Use tube pan.

title: stuffed bell peppers
directions: Boil peppers until tender (5 minutes), then core.
Mix ingredients and stuff peppers.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: cheese grits casserole
directions: Add grits to boiling water
and salt.
Let cool.
Beat eggs with milk; stir into grits mixture with the sausage, Jiffy mix and butter.
Put in 13 x 9-inch casserole.
Cover all with cheese. Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: camarones con venduras(shrimp with vegetables)
directions: Cooking time:
9 minutes.
Be sure the shrimp is peeled and veined.
Servings:
4 to 5.

title: cheese herb bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease an 8-inch round cake pan (or a giant foil salad container).
Combine all dry ingredients in a food processor.
Cut in the butter until mixture resembles coarse crumbs, using the food processor blade.
In another bowl beat the eggs, honey, milk and cheese with a fork just until blended.
Stir liquid into dry ingredients just until mixed.
Pour into pan. Bake 45 to 55 minutes or until top springs back when touched lightly.
Cool in the pan.
Cut into 12 wedges or into strips.

title: islander chicken
directions: Pour smoke over chicken parts.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.
Serve over rice of choice.

title: butterscotch pie
directions: Put part of milk in double boiler; add a little extra white sugar and part of brown sugar to milk.
Add flour and rest of sugar together; stir in remaining milk and beat in egg yolks, then add with butter into hot mixture.
Cool until thickened and add to pie crust.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into a buttered 9 x 13-inch casserole and refrigerate overnight.
Cook at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.
Sprinkle with more shredded Cheddar, if desired, and serve warm.
Wonderful for weekends!!!

title: fresh strawberry cake
directions: Combine cake mix, strawberry gelatin, vegetable oil, eggs, flour and 1/2 of strawberry mixture.
Beat at medium high speed on electric mixer 3 minutes.
Fold in remainder of berries and nuts.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Cook onion in fat until clear; add Worcestershire sauce, green pepper, celery and chili powder.
Cook this for 10 to 15 minutes or until tender.
Then add tomatoes and tomato paste and then mushroom soup.
Cook hen until tender.
Cool and remove from bones.
Cut up and add to other mixture.
Cook 1 pound spaghetti until tender and add to mixture and cook until well done.

title: gingersnap brisket
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Sprinkle salt, pepper, garlic salt and of brisket.
Empty onion soup mix on bottom of pan.
Add water and brisket.
Add the gingersnaps to the juice around brisket.
Spread chili sauce on top of brisket.
Add the potatoes, carrots and onions; bake for 1 1/2 hours at 350°. Remove brisket and slice on a cutting board.
Put the sliced brisket back in gravy until tender, about 1/2 to 1 hour.

title: applesauce jam cake
directions: Cream together shortening and sugar.
Add beaten eggs, jam, raisins and nuts.
Sift together flour, soda, salt and spices. Add alternately with applesauce.
Makes 4 layers.
Cook at 325° for 30 minutes.
Ice with Caramel Icing.

title: tortilla soup (spicy)
directions: Saute first five ingredients.
Add the rest and simmer 50 minutes.
Serve over corn chip strips.
Sprinkle cheese on top.

title: peg's broccoli casserole
directions: Saute the celery and onion in the margarine in a large electric skillet.
Add all the other ingredients and blend well. Pour into 9 x 13 x 2-inch greased baking dish.
Top with seasoned crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes, adding French fried onions on top for last 10 minutes.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all the ingredients together except the nuts.
Form them into a ball.
Top with the chopped nuts.

title: blueberry muffins(light)
directions: Sift together the flour, baking powder, sugar and salt.
(If self-rising flour, omit baking powder and salt.)
Beat the egg, add milk to egg then shortening.
Pour liquid mixture into the dry ingredients and combine quickly.
Add blabbers and spoon into greased and lightly floured muffin pan.
Bake 20 minutes at 400°. Serve hot or cold.

title: pimento soup
directions: Place pimento in blender, reserving a few strips for garnish. Add onion and cream and blend on high about 30 seconds.
Remove from blender and chill.
Chill consomme separately.
Ten minutes before serving, add consomme to pimento mix and stir well.
Leave a few lumps of consomme to add texture.
Garnish each serving with 1 or 2 strips pimento.

title: lasagna
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes with tinfoil.
Remove foil and bake for 10 minutes, uncovered.

title: no bake fruit cake
directions: Put milk in double boiler and scald.
Add marshmallows, stirring constantly and cook until smooth.
Remove from heat. Place graham crackers in paper bag and crush.
Mix crumbs, raisins, fruits and nuts and pour warm marshmallow mixture over, mixing well.
Place in tube pan, pressing down firmly so it takes shape of pan.
Place in refrigerator and when cold will come out of pan.

title: potato cakes
directions: Mix all together.
You
might
want to add more milk or less, just enough to make
the
mixture into patties to fry in oil or Pam spray.
Umm good!

title: raisin puffs
directions: Boil raisins in water until all water is gone.
Set aside and cool.
Cream shortening and sugar until creamy.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Beat until light.
Sift flour, salt and baking soda. Add flour and raisins and mix until well blended.

title: pecan pie
directions: Cream together butter and sugar.
Beat in 3 eggs one at a time.
Add 1 cup white corn syrup.
Beat together well; add 1 teaspoon vanilla and 1 cup chopped pecans.
Pour into pie shell and bake at 300° until center is firm, about 1 hour.

title: pecan log
directions: Crush vanilla wafers in a food processor.
Mix pecans, wafers and condensed milk in a large mixing bowl.
Shape into logs with wax paper.
Cover logs with aluminum foil.
Place in refrigerator for 2 days.

title: chicken breasts in cream
directions: Rinse chicken and pat dry.
Brown in margarine in skillet. Arrange in single layer in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Add onion and garlic to drippings in skillet.
Saute until tender.
Add half and half, Worcestershire sauce and pepper, stirring to deglaze.
Pour over chicken.
Bake, tightly covered, at 325° for 2 hours or until tender.
Serve over rice.
Yield: 8 servings.

title: pistachio salad
directions: Mix well and pour into dish desired.
Place sliced maraschino cherries on top.
Chill.
Keep refrigerated.

title: fresh fruit cobbler
directions: Put first 4 ingredients in 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish or pan. Cream margarine; add egg, sugar and vanilla and beat thoroughly. Add sifted dry ingredients with milk.
Mix gently to form a smooth batter.
Spread on fruit.
Sprinkle with a mixture of 2 tablespoons sugar and 1 teaspoon cinnamon.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes until crust is brown.
Serve warm or cold with whipped cream.

title: cinnamon roll good
directions: Bring to a boil, cool slightly.
Pour in baking pan.
Add nuts, if desired.
Place rolls, cut side down.
Let rise and bake.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Combine pie filling mix with milk in saucepan.
Add peanut butter; cook and stir over medium heat until mixture comes to a full boil.
Cool pudding 5 minutes, stirring twice.
Pour into pie shell and chill 3 hours.

title: fried apple pies
directions: Prepare pastry by mixing flour and salt; cut shortening into flour until size of small peas.
Sprinkle 1 tablespoon water and toss with fork and push aside until all dough is mixed.
Roll to 1/8-inch thick and cut into 6-inch circles.
Place 2 tablespoons apples (cooked about 45 minutes to an hour in 3 cups water; 1/2 cup sugar added after cooking).
Fry in heavy skillet in shortening at 375° about 1/8 to 1/4-inch deep.
Fry 3 to 4 minutes on each side.
Drain on paper towel.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar, if desired.	Makes 12.

title: stew meat stroganoff
directions: Brown meat in a little oil.
Throw in a crock-pot; stir in soup, water and onion soup mix.
Cook on high from 9:00 to 3:00 p.m., then turn down to low.
Stir in sour cream 15 minutes before serving.
Serve over rice or noodles.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash in boiling water or steam, then drain. Mix with rest of ingredients. Put in casserole dish and top with buttered bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: o'henry bars
directions: Boil sugar and corn syrup to a rolling boil.
Take off burner and add peanut butter.
Pour over corn flakes, mix real well. Put in a 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Melt chocolate chips and put that over the top.
Let set.
Do not refrigerate.
This is better if made the day before served.

title: cornbread
directions: Combine
all	ingredients,
blending
well.	Preheat greased 8-inch
iron skillet or muffin tins.
Fill with batter and bake at 450° approximately 20 minutes or until brown.

title: spiced pickled beets
directions: Cook beets until tender.
Cut in pieces if too large.
Bring sugar, vinegar, spices and 1 1/2 cups of water to a boil and then simmer for 15 minutes.
Pack beets in hot sterilized jars.
Remove cinnamon sticks and pour the boiling liquid over the peeled beets in jar.
Seal at once.

title: lemon squares
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Blend flavoring, margarine and confectioners sugar thoroughly.
Press evenly into square 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Bake 2 minutes.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put in well-greased, 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake at 375° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: cherry-lemon icebox pie
directions: Combine milk, lemon juice and extracts; stir until thickened, about 2 minutes.
Beat cream until stiff, fold into milk mixture. Pour into pastry shell.
Refrigerate for 10 minutes.
Top with pie filling.
Chill for at least 2 hours or overnight, if desired.

title: bow ties with sausage and sweet peppers
directions: Cook pasta.
Meanwhile, cut sausage into 1-inch pieces and cook with red peppers until sausage is brown.
Drain off fat.
Add broth and black pepper.
Simmer, uncovered, 5 minutes.
Toss pasta with sausage mixture and parsley.

title: ice cream salad
directions: Melt the margarine.
Add the sugar and 3 crackers and mix until crumbly.
Press into a 9 x 9-inch pan.
Add the boiling water to the jello mix and the ice cream.
Beat with mixer.
Pour over crackers.
Top with fresh fruit and whipping cream, if desired.

title: ice cream sandwich(low-fat)
directions: Mix vanilla ice cream and peanut butter together.
Make 2 sandwiches; break crackers.
Put mixture in crackers.
Put in freezer; wrapped in foil.
Serve after frozen.

title: lasagne
directions: Bake at 375°
in 9 x 12-inch baking pan for 1 hour.
Let sit for 10 minutes.
Cut and serve.

title: vegetable salad
directions: Mix all this together for several hours at least.
It is better to sit overnight.

title: crawfish pie
directions: Saute onions and celery in butter and roux until partially clear (approximately 4 minutes).
Add bell pepper and garlic; cook until all moisture has evaporated from vegetables (4 to 5 minutes).
Add cornstarch; simmer until thickened.
Remove from heat.
Add parsley and onion tops; cool.
Blend in egg.
Spoon mixture in pie crust; sprinkle cheese on top.
Next, add top pie crust.
Leave vent in center.
Bake at 350° until golden brown, approximately 50 minutes.

title: spinach-strawberry salad
directions: Tear spinach into bite size pieces in a large bowl.
In separate bowl, whisk vinegars, mustard, honey, salt and pepper all together.
Add to salad and toss.
Add strawberries, sesame seed and onion slices.
Serves 6 people.
Looks very attractive in glass salad bowl.

title: spinach pesto appetizer
directions: Blend all ingredients in processor.
Pour into a 9-inch oiled spring-form pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Serve with crackers or French bread toast.

title: nacho dip
directions: Brown hamburger; drain and put in crock-pot.
Add soup and salsa.
Heat until warm.
Can leave on low all day.
Serve with nacho chips.

title: upstate minestrone soup
directions: Slice sausage crosswise about 1/2-inch thick; brown in oil in deep saucepan or Dutch oven.
Add onion, garlic, carrots and basil; cook for 5 minutes.
Add zucchini, tomatoes with liquid, bouillon, cabbage, salt and pepper.
Bring soup to a boil; reduce heat and simmer, covered for 1 hour.
Add beans with liquid; cook another 20 minutes.
Garnish with parsley.

title: crab chowder
directions: Cook onions and garlic in butter with cayenne pepper until tender.
Blend in soup, softened cream cheese and milk.
Add crabmeat and undrained corn.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer ten minutes.
Stir in sugar after this.
Serves eight, reheats well.

title: diet vegetable dip
directions: Blend ingredients in blender until smooth.
Return mixture to container and chill overnight.
Serve as a dip with vegetables for dieters.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix all together.
Place into buttered casserole; sprinkle with more crumbled Ritz crackers and paprika.
Bake at 350° for about 40 minutes.

title: gingersnaps
directions: Cream shortening and sugar together; add molasses and egg. Combine flour, soda and spices that have been mixed together. Roll into small balls; dip in sugar.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet for 15 to 18 minutes at 350°.

title: briselchecks (swedish christmas cookies)
directions: Cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add flour and baking powder; mix until mixture forms a firm ball that does not stick to your bowl.
Divide ball in half.
By hand, form each ball into a log shape about 10 inches long and 1 1/2 inches in height. Wrap in wax paper and refrigerate 1 hour or longer.
Remove from refrigerator and roll each log in nonpareils.
Slice logs into cookies.
Place on cookie baking sheets.
Bake at 350° for 9 to 10 minutes.
Cookies should still look white, but underside should be a golden brown.

title: cucumber salad
directions: Cut apart the cauliflower carefully, keeping the flowerets fairly large.
Drop into boiling, salted water.
Boil 4 to 5 minutes, until just slightly tender.
Pour into a colander and cool in running cold water.
Drain well and reassemble by arranging top-side-down in a bowl (one about the same shape on the bottom as the cauliflower).
Combine the oil, vinegar, capers, parsley, pimiento, onion, salt, mustard and pepper; spoon over the cauliflower.
Cover bowl and refrigerate for at least 2 hours or overnight.

title: chicken and spaghetti
directions: In skillet, saute onion and green pepper.
When done, add cubed tomato and simmer until tender.
Add soup and boiled cubed chicken.
Pour over cooked spaghetti and bake at 350°, long enough to get real hot.
Grated cheese may be added on top before baking.

title: cabbage beef soup
directions: Steam cabbage. Cook ground beef and drain excess fat. Mix all ingredients in large pot and add 1 tablespoon Wesson oil. Bring to a boil. Cover and reduce heat. Simmer 1 hour.

title: easy pot roast
directions: Place roast in heavy-duty aluminum foil.
Pour mushroom soup on top of roast (undiluted).
Sprinkle with onion soup.
Place carrots on top.
Pot potatoes around roast.
Fasten foil tightly.
Place in uncovered roasting pan.
Roast 4 hours at 225° to 250°.

title: pineapple-lime snow
directions: Drain pineapple well, reserving syrup.
Combine reserved syrup and enough water to measure 1 cup in saucepan.
Heat to a boil. Add lime gelatin.
Reduce heat and cook, stirring, until gelatin is thoroughly dissolved.
Remove from heat.
Add 1 cup cold water. Set aside and refrigerate until gelatin is consistency of egg whites.

title: cheese krispies
directions: Mix butter and cheese together.
Add remaining ingredients. Shape mixture into balls the size of a quarter.
Place on a greased cookie sheet.
Flatten balls with floured fork tongs, crossways. Bake at 325° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Yields 6 to 8 dozen.

title: hodge podge stew
directions: Cook beef, onion and garlic until beef is brown and onion is tender. Stir in remaining ingredients and simmer 15 to 20 minutes.

title: easy dump cake
directions: Spread peaches on bottom of oblong or square pan.
Pour dry cake mix on top, then cut up butter on top.
Sprinkle with cinnamon and nutmeg.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serve with ice cream or whipped cream.

title: christmas fruit cake
directions: Cream shortening; add sugar.
Mix well; add salt and beaten eggs.
Add fruit and nuts which have been cut in small pieces and mixed with 1/2 cup flour.
Add sifted dry ingredients and fruit juice.
Mix well.
Bake in paper lined loaf tins at 275° for 3 hours.
Makes 9 pounds of cake.

title: four layer chocolate dessert
directions: Mix flour, softened butter and nuts.
Press into a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Let cool.
Mix softened cream cheese and sugar with 1 cup Cool Whip.
Spread over crust.
Mix chocolate pudding with milk (use mixer).
Spread on top of the cream cheese layer.
Top with Cool Whip and chill.

title: g??? d??? stew
directions: You may use all duck or all goose. Venison, beef or chicken can be used.

title: hot shrimp dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Heat in saucepan.
Serve in small fondue pot with melba rounds.

title: oatmeal coffee bread
directions: Mix and pour into individual loaf pan which has been treated with nonstick spray.
Bake for 20 minutes at 350° to 375°.
Recipe makes only 1 loaf.

title: icicle pickles
directions: Peel and remove seeds from large cucumbers.
Cut in strips, 1/2-inch wide.
Cover with ice water.
Let stand overnight.
Drain and pack upright in sterilized pint jars.
For each 3 or 4 jars, boil together for 3 minutes all the ingredients.
Pour over the cucumbers to fill the jars.
Let stand 6 weeks before using.

title: creamy baked fish fillets
directions: Place fillets in a lightly greased 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish. Sprinkle with pepper.
Dot with butter.
Spoon soup over fillets. Sprinkle with cheese and paprika.
Bake, uncovered, in preheated oven for 20 minutes or until fish flakes easily with a fork. Makes 3 to 4 servings.

title: yam cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour one Bundt pan.
Cream together sugar, vanilla and margarine until fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time until well blended.
Add yams and beat well.
Add flour, baking soda, cinnamon and allspice.
Blend well.
Fold in pineapple, pecans and raisins.
Pour into prepared pan and bake 60 to 70 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean after cake is completely cooled.
Melt frosting in a saucepan and drizzle over cake.

title: morning (or anytime) mix-up
directions: In large skillet, saute potatoes and ham or Spam in oil for 10 minutes or until tender.
In a small bowl, beat eggs, salt and pepper.
Add to skillet.
Cook, stirring occasionally, until eggs are set.
Remove from heat and gently stir in cheese.
Spoon onto serving platter and sprinkle with chives or other toppings.
Makes 4 servings.

title: apple raisin popcorn
directions: Stir together the apples, raisins and cinnamon.
Add to the popcorn and mix thoroughly.
Low calorie.

title: creme de menthe cake
directions: Prepare cake mix according to package directions, adding 2 tablespoons creme de menthe syrup.
Bake.
After cake has cooled, spread on fudge topping.
Add 2 tablespoons creme de menthe syrup to Cool Whip; spread on top of fudge topping.
Refrigerate.
Will make a 9 x 13-inch pan, plus 6 cupcakes or triple layer cake using round pans.

title: apple cheese casserole
directions: Put the sliced and peeled apples into greased casserole.
Mix flour and sugars.
Cut oleo into mixture.
Combine the water and lemon juice and pour over apples in dish.
Pour sugar topping over the apples.
Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes. Sprinkle the cheese on top and bake until cheese melts.

title: cheese bars
directions: Beat with spoon the melted butter and egg.
Add cake mix and mix until gooey.
Put into 9 x 13-inch cake pan.

title: pumpkin pie - no crust!
directions: Grease a pie tin generously with butter and dust generously with flour.
Don't shake the pan too hard, but don't leave too much flour.
Beat eggs and mix in remaining ingredients.
Pour into pie tin.
Bake at 375° (hot oven) for 45 minutes or until knife in center comes out clean.
Makes a large pie!

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Slice peppers in half; remove seeds.
In microwavable container with lid, cook peppers, covered in water, for 4 minutes on High. Or steam peppers.
Remove peppers and turn upside down to drain.

title: reese's peanut butter squares
directions: Cream together ingredients and press into 13 x 9-inch pan. Top with 1 small package butterscotch chips, 1 small package chocolate chips and 4 tablespoons butter, melted together.
Spread over filling and refrigerate.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Cream butter, Crisco and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time. Sift dry ingredients together and add alternately with milk and vanilla.
Grease and flour tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: pina colada cake
directions: Mix all together except the cream of coconut and Cool Whip. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Remove from oven and punch holes all over with fork. Pour cream of coconut over the cake. After cake cools, cover with Cool Whip and sprinkle with coconut.

title: sweet and sour cabbage
directions: Boil cabbage in salt water.
When done, pour off all but one cup of water.
Add remaining ingredients to make a thickening. Serve hot; also good reheated.

title: autumn chicken
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into casserole dish.
Bake in 350°
oven for 30 minutes or until bubbly.
Serves 8 people.

title: fall fresh fruit dip
directions: Beat cheese until smooth; add sugar and vanilla.
Mix until smooth.
Great with apple wedges.

title: corn spoon bread
directions: In a deep casserole (2-quart), mix everything, but cheese. When well mixed, top with cheese.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°. Remove from oven.
Cover and let stand 10 minutes.

title: charlie's cafe special wild rice
directions: Rinse wild rice thoroughly. Combine with water, salt and onion.
Cover and simmer until tender, 40 to 45 minutes.
Remove onion; drain rice in colander.
Dice bacon; fry until crisp.
Add green onions and mushrooms; cook just until tender.
Add drained rice; season with salt and pepper.
Heat through.
Makes 6 servings.

title: gingersnaps
directions: Cream the shortening and sugar. Add molasses and egg.
Mix well and drop on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° until done.

title: linda's caramel corn
directions: Boil sugar and oleo 1 minute. Add soda and stir.
Pour over popcorn and mix until coated.

title: hardee's biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Mix all dry ingredients well. Add oil and buttermilk.
Add yeast to mixture.
Mix well.
Bake as many as needed at 425°.
Keep excess dough in refrigerator, well covered.
Will keep for 2 weeks.

title: apple loaf(one large loaf or 3 mini loaves)
directions: In bowl of electric mixer, beat sugar and butter until fluffy. Add the eggs, one by one, beating well after each.
Combine the flour, baking powder and salt.
Add half of the flour mixture to the batter.
Beat (not too much).
Beat in milk and vanilla, then remaining flour mixture.
Fold in apples with rubber spatula. Spoon batter into 9 x 5-inch loaf pan or 3 mini loaf pans, smoothing top.
Sprinkle generously with cinnamon sugar.

title: diet raisin cookies
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients, boil 3 minutes.
Cool.
Add eggs, artificial sweetener, soda and water.
Blend well.
Add dry ingredients.
Drop on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 7 minutes.

title: whiskey slush
directions: Set boiling water with tea bags aside.
Combine tea with rest of ingredients.
Freeze.
Use 1/2 glass slush to 1/2 glass 7-Up.

title: chicken broccoli
directions: Stew chicken breasts.
Cook broccoli until tender.
Place broccoli in greased dish, then chicken.
Cover with cream of chicken soup and mayonnaise or salad dressing.
Sprinkle with cheese and bread crumbs.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: pineapple cranberry upside down cake
directions: Melt butter in a 13 X 9 pan in 350 degree oven.
Sprinkle with sugar, nuts, cranberries, and pineapple.
Add water to reserved juice to equal amount of liquid specified on the cake mix package. Prepare as directed and spread over fruit.
Bake 350 degrees for 35 to 40 minutes or until cake tests done.
Cool 5 minutes.
Invert onto a large serving dish.

title: mac's stuffed meat loaf
directions: Part 1:
Mix thawed and drained ground beef thoroughly with all Part 1 ingredients, except for 1/4 cup onion or tomato soup. Mixture should be firm enough to shape into loaf by hand (if soggy, add
more oatmeal).
Place in a 2 pound capacity loaf pan and pour 1/4 cup soup over loaf.
Place in oven and slow cook at 350° for 40 minutes.
Occasionally baste and marinate in natural juices.

title: mom's maple syrup
directions: Combine sugars and water in saucepan.
Bring to boil; boil for 2 minutes.
Add vanilla and maple flavoring.
Cover saucepan for a few minutes.

title: mexican meat loaf
directions: Brown beef; add remaining ingredients, except tortillas and cheese.
Bring to boil, then place half of mixture in casserole. Add tortillas, then remaining meat mixture.
Top with cheese and cover.
Bake at 260° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: mock crabmeat ball
directions: Mix crabmeat with cream cheese, lemon juice and garlic salt. Mix ketchup with horseradish for topping.
Form into a ball and chill with topping.
Serve with crackers.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff.
Add 1/4 teaspoon salt to egg whites; set aside.
Add soda to flour; set aside.
Cream butter and sugar well; add egg yolks.
Add flour alternately with sour cream.
Mix well.
Add egg whites; mix well.
Add vanilla. Bake at 300° for 1 hour and 15 minutes in Bundt pan.

title: yeast bread
directions: Mix 2 cups water, sugar, eggs and sugar (honey) in a blender. Add other 2 cups water and flour to make batter.
Let set 30 minutes.
Add oil or fat and salt.
Knead until smooth.
Place in a greased bowl and let rise until double.
Punch down.
Let rise again.
Make into loaves.
Makes 4 medium loaves.
When doubled, bake in a 350° oven about 40 minutes.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix all together and let sit overnight.

title: banana salad
directions: Put a layer of sliced bananas in a bowl and cover with mayonnaise diluted with a little water, sugar and lemon juice. Cover with crushed peanuts.
Keep adding the three layers on top of each other until the size bowl you need is filled.
Garnish with red cherries.

title: fruit salad in pudding
directions: Drain oranges and pineapple; set aside in large bowl.
Cook pudding in juice of oranges and pineapple only.
Pour pudding over fruit and blend well.
Recipe can be doubled.

title: peanut butter candy
directions: Cook to boil.
Add peanut butter and vanilla.
Pour into greased pan and cool.

title: squash casserole
directions: Boil squash until tender.
Drain water.
Put margarine in baking dish.
Put in oven at 350°; mix all other ingredients with squash.
Be sure bread is in crumbs.
(You can use a food processor.)
Place in your margarine and cook in oven for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: cranberry jello salad
directions: Grind cranberries; mix with sugar and refrigerate.
Mix Jell-O with hot water and boil 3 minutes.
Add all other ingredients and chill.

title: blender jam
directions: Chop green tomatoes in blender.
Add sugar.
Boil together 15 minutes.
Skim.
Dump in Jell-O.
Stir and put in hot jars with lids or paraffin.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix all together and chill overnight.
May be served with chips, crackers, Hawaiian bread or raw vegetables.

title: sweet and sour green beans
directions: Bring to boil.
Fry bacon and put grease and bacon in beans. Pour in hot vinegar and sugar mixture.
Add chopped onions.
Stir and bake 20 minutes.

title: vegetable marinade with tangy dressing
directions: Heat together vinegar, pepper, salt, sugar, and oil until dissolved; set aside to cool.
Place vegetables in large container and pour dressing over vegetables.
Mix and refrigerate.
Serves 6 to 8.
Add more vegetables to existing marinade when supply gets low.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix well.
I use hand beater to make salad smooth.
Put in flat bowl and chill overnight.

title: sweet and sour sauce
directions: Heat until it thickens.
I always needed more cornstarch.
If it's too strong for you, just add water to it.

title: fish tacos(- a san diego favorite!  yield:  10 tacos)
directions: 1. Cut cod into 1/2 x 3-inch strips.

title: japanese fruit pie
directions: Beat the eggs.
Add margarine and sugar; stir well.
Add vinegar, water and vanilla, then add pecans, coconut and raisins. Bake in an 8-inch pie pan at 350° until brown and set.

title: asparagus peking-style
directions: Heat pan; add oil, stock, water, sherry, soy sauce and cornstarch.
Stir constantly until it boils.
Add asparagus; heat thoroughly.
Makes 4 to 5 servings.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: You will need a 9 x 12-inch baking pan.

title: boiled custard
directions: Place all the milk except a cup in double boiler.
Get real hot.
Beat eggs thoroughly.
Mix sugar and flour.
Add sugar mixture and 1 cup milk.
Add eggs.
Mix good.
Add to heated milk, stirring constantly until it thickens.
Add vanilla.
If lumpy, strain.
Place in refrigerator.

title: calf's liver with bacon
directions: Dredge liver in flour, shaking off excess.
Saute in hot butter for 2 to 3 minutes or until half done.
Meanwhile, gently cook bacon until half done.
Place bacon over the liver and bake in 325° oven for 10 minutes.

title: quick hamburger dish
directions: Brown ground beef with the onion.
Put into baking dish.
Pour tomato sauce over hamburger, then cover with grated cheese.
Over this put 1 can of biscuits.
Brown biscuits in 350° to 400° oven. Good with salad.

title: extra easy german's sweet chocolate cake
directions: Blend all ingredients in large mixer bowl; beat 4 minutes at medium speed.
Pour into 3 greased and floured 9-inch pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until cake springs back when lightly pressed.
(Do not underbake.)
Cool in pans for 15 minutes; remove and cool on racks.
Fill with Easy Coconut-Pecan Filling.

title: chocolate cheese fudge
directions: Melt cheese and butter until smooth. Remove from heat. Add vanilla and nuts. Mix. In large bowl, sift sugar and cocoa, then pour cheese mixture over sugar. Stir well. Pour into ungreased pan. Use a paper towel to blot the extra butter off top. Place in fridge for 30 minutes. Then cut in squares.

title: hearty winter soup
directions: Bring water or broth, potatoes, carrots and celery to a boil; reduce heat.
Simmer 10 minutes or until vegetables are tender. Add
remaining ingredients; cover.	Microwave on High 3 minutes or	until
cheese
is melted and soup is thoroughly heated.

title: "milk and egg free" potato salad
directions: Wash potatoes; heat 1-inch salted water (1 1/2 teaspoons salt to cup of water).
Add unpared potatoes.
Cover tightly; heat to boiling and cook 30 to 35 minutes.
Drain, cool and peel.
Cut potatoes into slices.
Combine oil, onion, vinegar, mustard, salt and pepper.
Pour over potatoes; toss gently.
Cover; refrigerate at least 2 hours.
Just before serving, add bacon chips and celery seed.
Toss until potatoes are well coated.
Can also garnish with bacon chips and pimentos.

title: old fashioned molasses pudding
directions: Mix and bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: squash relish
directions: Grind squash, onions and peppers with salt.
Let stand one hour.
Boil together sugar, vinegar, turmeric and celery seed. Drain squash mixture.
Put all ingredients in pot and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and let simmer 5 minutes.
Pour into hot jars and seal.
Makes 5 pints.

title: bacon cheese log
directions: Fry bacon crisp and crumble.
Mix all ingredients and shape into two rolls, about 1-inch in diameter.
Sprinkle 1 tablespoon chili powder and 1 tablespoon paprika on wax paper and roll logs in mixture to coat evenly.
Wrap tightly in wax paper.
Chill. Serve with your favorite crackers.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Spray a 2 1/2-quart casserole with Pam and layer hash browns, onion and Cheddar cheese.
Mix cream of chicken soup and sour cream and spread over potatoes.
Spread crushed corn flakes over top of casserole.
Melt butter and drizzle over top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: bradshaw's potatoes
directions: Tear off large amount of heavy-duty aluminum foil.
Butter foil except for about 1-inch around edges.
Scrub and slice potatoes (skins and all), about 1/4-inch thick onto one side of foil. (Make whatever amount you desire.)
Sprinkle potatoes with good amount of seasoned salt.
Sprinkle with some pepper.
Top with sliced onion (your desired amount) and chunks of butter all over. Fold foil over potatoes and fold edges several times real tight. Cook on barbecue 15 to 20 minutes on each side.

title: broccoli cheese soup
directions: Cook together water and all the vegetables, except the parsley.
In another pan, cook over very low heat the milk, cheese and parsley.
When vegetables are done, pour melted cheese mixture over the vegetables.
Do not drain any water off vegetables.
Mix well and serve.
Serves 6 to 9 people easily.

title: sweet and sour sauce
directions: Mix according to taste. This is a very inexpensive and quick sauce for meatballs, chicken fingers, etc.

title: double chocolate pudding pie
directions: Pour 3/4 cup milk in bowl. Add dark chocolate pudding mix. Beat with wire whisk 1 minute. Mixture will be thick. Gently stir in 1/2 of the Cool Whip. Spoon evenly into pie crust. Pour remaining milk in another bowl. Add white chocolate pudding. Beat with wire whisk one minute. Mixture will be thick. Gently stir in remaining Cool Whip. Spread over pudding layer in crust. Refrigerate 4 hours or until set.

title: bonbon candies
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients; form into balls and refrigerate. Melt chips and paraffin over low heat in a pan of water.
Dip balls in chocolate.
Place on waxed paper.
Yields 3 1/2 dozen.

title: japanese fruit pie
directions: Beat eggs and sugar; mix in other ingredients.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake 25 minutes at 350°.

title: aunt shirley's hamburg casserole
directions: Brown hamburg; drain off fat.
Pour cans of soup over hamburg and mix.
Season with salt and pepper.
Layer hamburg, carrots, onions and potatoes in a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Repeat.
Top with hamburg mixture.
Pour milk over and add little water.
Bake at 350° for 2 hours.
Absolutely delicious!

title: sweet and sour dip
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Serve with crackers, vegetables and/or fruit.

title: skillet barbecued pork chops
directions: Brown chops in oil in large frying pan; drain excess fat. Sprinkle with salt.
Top with barbecue sauce.
Simmer, covered, for 25 to 30 minutes until chops are tender.
Place lemon slices on top of chops and simmer, uncovered, 5 minutes.

title: sweet potato salad
directions: In a large bowl, stir together first 7 ingredients.
Add sweet potatoes, celery and peas.
Toss to coat with dressing.
Cover and refrigerate at least 2 hours or overnight.
Bring to room temperature before serving.
Serves 6.

title: lattice top chicken
directions: Combine soup, milk and salt.
Add chicken, vegetables, 1/2 cheese and 1/2 onions.
Bake, covered, at 375° for 20 minutes. Unwrap rolls; pinch together, twist and place on top.
Bake 15 minutes longer.
Add remaining cheese and onions on top and bake 2 to 3 minutes longer.

title: danish apple squares
directions: Cut shortening into flour and salt.
Add milk to egg yolk to make 2/3 cup.
Add to flour mixture.
Divide dough in half.
Roll half to put in jelly roll pan or 13 x 9-inch pan.
Put apples and spices in middle.
Put other half of dough on top.
Pinch edges together.
Beat egg white until stiff and brush over top.

title: orange roughy
directions: Put fish in microwave-proof baking dish.
On top of fish put paprika.
Combine tomato, onion, green pepper, celery and parsley. Spoon over fish fillets; set aside.
Put butter in cup and cook on High for 1/2 minute.
Add lime juice to butter.
Put over fish. Cover with waxed paper.
Cook on High for 3 minutes.
Rotate dish and cook on High for 2 minutes.
Makes 2 servings.

title: zucchini cookies
directions: Mix sugar, flour, cinnamon, salt, soda and cloves.
Mix oleo and egg together.
Mix wet and dry ingredients together.
Add zucchini, nuts and raisins.
Chill dough for 2 hours.
Drop on greased cookie sheet.
Bake 12 minutes at 350°.

title: no-fail vanilla ice cream
directions: Mix first four ingredients well and pour into ice cream freezer.
Then fill freezer within 2 inches from the top with additional milk.
Freeze according to your freezer instructions and enjoy!

title: sausage kabobs(makes 4 servings)
directions: Place sausage, onions, mushrooms and zucchini in 2-quart bowl. Mix remaining ingredients; pour over sausage and vegetables.
Cover and refrigerate, stirring occasionally, at least 1 hour, but no longer than 24 hours.
About 20 minutes before serving, drain sausage and vegetables, reserving marinade.
Alternate sausage and vegetables on 4 metal skewers.
Set oven to broil (550°).
Place kabobs on rack in broiler pan.
Brush with reserved marinade. Broil 6 minutes with tops 4 inches from heat; turn.
Brush with marinade.
Broil until sausage is hot and zucchini is crisp-tender, 6 to 8 minutes.
Brush with marinade before serving.

title: peanut butter sheet cake
directions: Boil first four ingredients together.
Take off heat and add remaining ingredients.
This will be a very thin batter.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch jelly roll pan or large cookie sheet.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 375°.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Place pineapple in a well-greased rectangular glass pan.
Mix flour, sugar and cheese in a separate bowl.
Sprinkle mixture on top of pineapple.
Crumble Ritz crackers on top of everything. Pour melted butter on top of that.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes, until golden brown.

title: chicken & broccoli casserole
directions: Boil chicken and debone. Cook broccoli. In double boiler combine milk, cream cheese, salt, garlic powder and half of parmesan cheese. Bring to a boil, stirring constantly until mixture is creamy, the remove from heat. Layer in casserole dish chicken, broccoli then sauce. Sprinkle remaining parmesan cheese on top of casserole. Place in oven and bake for 30 minutes at 350°. Note: Preheat oven at 350°.

title: creamy pralines
directions: Check your barometric pressure, must be 30 in. or above. Combine sugar, cream of tartar, salt and milk.
Stir over low heat until sugar dissolves.
Wipe crystals from side of pan with cloth or rubber spatula.
Cook to 236° to 238°.
Cool to 220°.

title: skillet cabbage
directions: Spray Dutch oven with cooking spray.
Add the cabbage and the rest of the ingredients.
Bring this to a boil; cover and reduce heat, and simmer for about 20 minutes or until tender-crisp. Stir occasionally.

title: spaghetti bake
directions: Mix together.
Mix with 1/2 box of cooked spaghetti.
Layer in casserole dish: spaghetti mixture, cottage cheese, Mozzarella cheese and sauce.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: loksa(also known as langashe)
directions: Blend flour into mashed potatoes, add more flour if needed, but not too much.
Dough should not be sticky or crumbly.
Divide dough into four portions and roll out each portion on floured board to 1/8 inch thickness in 8 inch circles.
Prick surface with fork to prevent puffing. Bake in preheated oven 400°.
Bake on bottom surface of oven (I use cookie sheets) for about 7 minutes on each side.
After Loksa is baked, brush each brush each side with browned butter and either with or without sugar.
Stack on platter and either roll or cut into wedges.
Loksa is good with any meatless soup.

title: banana split bars
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Beat margarine and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, banana and vanilla; mix well.
Mix in flour, baking powder and salt.
Stir in nuts.
Pour into greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake for 20 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Sprinkle with marshmallows, chips and cherries.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes longer or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean. Cool in pan; cut into bars.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix
all
ingredients as listed. Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: neiman-marcus cake
directions: Mix together cake mix, oleo, 1 egg and pecans.
Press in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan. Cream together the cream cheese, 3 eggs and powdered sugar.
Pour over batter.
Bake in oven at 350° for 35 minutes. Do not overbake.

title: cheese polenta
directions: In a 1 1/2-quart saucepan, combine cornmeal and cold water. Add boiling water and cook over high heat, stirring constantly until mixture comes to a boil and thickens.
Reduce heat to low; cook, stirring occasionally until mixture is smooth, 25 to 30 minutes.

title: megan's mouth-watering pretzels
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients together.
Break pretzels into small pieces.
Put on a cookie sheet.
Brush mixture on pretzels.
Bake at 350° for 7 minutes.
Take out and mix, then bake 7 more minutes.

title: corn fritters
directions: Combine flour, salt and baking powder.
Beat eggs with milk. Add 1 tablespoon melted Crisco and corn.
Combine the two mixtures lightly.
Drop from a teaspoon into hot Crisco.
Fry until brown and cooked in center.
Drain.

title: coconut pie
directions: Mix together margarine and cornstarch.
Add eggs and beat. Add vanilla and stir in milk and coconut.
Bake in unbaked pie shell for 35 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken quesadillas
directions: Boil chicken breasts in water seasoned with salt and pepper to taste until done; skin and debone. Chip up meat.

Melt butter; brush each tortilla with butter. Layer each tortilla with chicken, chili powder, cheese and green chilies. Fold over and brush with butter. Bake in 350° oven about 3 or 5 minutes or until light brown. Serve with picante sauce, sour cream or guacamole.

title: pineapple-cottage cheese jello salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O with 1 cup of hot water.
Stir in the milk, small curd cottage cheese, pineapple, salad dressing and chopped nuts.
Chill in a large pan.
Serve on lettuce.
Top with maraschino cherries, if desired.

title: super burgers
directions: Brown hamburger and chopped onion.
Drain grease.
Add soup, 1/4 cup water, ketchup to taste, mustard, salt and pepper.
Serve on toasted, buttered buns.

title: lemon sponge pudding
directions: Add lemon rind and juice to egg yolks which have been beaten thick.
Mix the flour with sugar and stir smoothly into egg mixture.
Add the milk gradually.
Beat egg whites stiff, but not dry and fold into pudding mixture.
Pour into shallow 1-quart baking dish.
Set in pan of cold water and bake 45 minutes in moderately slow oven (325°).
Cakelike top with custard on bottom. Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: sweet onion pie
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Saute the onions in butter.
Arrange in the bottom of the pie shell.
Combine milk, sour cream, flour and salt.
Add to beaten eggs and mix well.
Pour over onions and bake 30 minutes.
Sprinkle with bacon and parsley.
Let set 10 minutes before cutting into 6 to 8 wedges.

title: everyday cupcakes
directions: Place shortening in mixing bowl.
Sift in dry ingredients. Add egg and half the milk.
Mix until flour is moistened.
Beat 2 minutes at low speed on electric mixer.
Add remaining milk and vanilla.
Beat 1 minute longer.
Fill paper bake cups in muffin pans half full.
Bake at 375° for 18 to 20 minutes or until done. Cool.
Frost with jelly frosting.
Makes 1 1/2 dozen cupcakes.

title: ground beef stew
directions: Brown ground beef; drain excess fat.
Add soup.
Add Veg-All, water, salt and pepper.
Simmer for 10 to 15 minutes.
Serve over cooked noodles.

title: mom's silver champion cake
directions: Beat butter and sugar until very light and creamy.
Add milk alternately with flour with which baking powder has been sifted with last cup of flour.
Then add beaten egg whites and fold. Bake in three 9-inch round pans about 40 minutes at 350°.

title: one bowl brownies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Microwave chocolate and margarine in large microwavable bowl on High 2 minutes or until margarine is melted. Stir until chocolate is completely melted.
Stir sugar into chocolate.
Mix eggs and vanilla until well blended.
Stir in flour and walnuts.
Spread in greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out with fudgy crumbs.
Cool in pan.
Cut into squares.
Makes 24 fudgy brownies.

title: baked beans
directions: Brown hamburger and drain.
In a 9 x 13-inch pan, mix all other ingredients.
Mix in browned hamburger.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: date nut pudding
directions: Pour hot water over the first 4 ingredients;
let cool.
Beat and add egg, sugar, flour and vanilla.
Bake at 350° in a 7 1/2 x 11 1/2-inch glass dish.

title: pineapple salad
directions: Mix sugar and cornstarch.
Add egg and water; mix well.
Cook until thick, stirring constantly.
Add crushed pineapple and cheese.
Cook until cheese melts.
Add marshmallows.
Cook until marshmallows are soft and begin to melt.
Pour into bowl, cool, then refrigerate until well chilled.

title: drop sugar cookies
directions: Cream shortening.
Add sugar and eggs.
Mix soda and sour cream and add alternately with dry ingredients.
Drop on cookie sheets.
Sprinkle sugar over the top and bake in a 350° oven.

title: raw potato cakes
directions: Grate potatoes; add remaining ingredients.
Mix; fry in shortening.
(Applesauce goes good with these.)

title: ham and cheese casserole
directions: Cook noodles as directed on package.
Drain and put in 2-quart casserole dish.
Drain ham.
Mix with soup, water and cheese. Microwave until cheese is melted.
Pour over noodles.
Cook at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: corn beef sandwiches
directions: Heat oven to 350 degrees.
Crumble up corn beef.
Mix all of the above.
Add cheese in cubes.
Add to buns.
Wrap in aluminum foil.
Heat for 20 minutes.

title: snert (dutch pea soup)
directions: Soak peas overnight.
Drain.
Combine all ingredients.
Cook for 30 minutes over medium heat, then simmer for 2 1/2 hours or until peas are tender.

title: beef, cheese, noodle casserole
directions: Cook oil, chopped onion and hamburger until hamburger loses red color; boil noodles with salt.
Add spaghetti sauce to hamburger mixture and heat.
Layer 1/2 of noodles in greased baking dish; add layer of cheese and layer of sauce; repeat.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: banana cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Mix all ingredients.
Drop dough by rounded teaspoonfuls about 2-inches apart onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake until light brown, 12 to 15 minutes.
Immediately remove from cookie sheet.
Makes about 3 dozen cookies.

title: pecan pie
directions: Cream together the syrup and sugar.
Add oleo and salt.
Mix well and add eggs; beat for 150 strokes.
Add pecans and mix well. Pour into pie shell and bake in moderate oven
(325°) for 40 minutes or until done.

title: alta loma h.s. baked turkey salad
directions: Combine all ingredients except bread.
Put in a greased 1 1/3-quart casserole.
Sprinkle bread crumbs on top.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Serves 6.

title: coleslaw
directions: Add the shredded cabbage and dash of salt in a large salad bowl.
In a small jar, mix the milk, lemon juice, sugar and mayonnaise.
Stir until well blended.
Add to the shredded cabbage.
Refrigerate for 1 hour.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: maple pecan strawberry bread
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease and flour a 5 x 9-inch loaf pan. In a large mixing bowl, stir together eggs, maple syrup and honey.
Add oil or melted butter, strawberries, milk and vanilla and mix well.

title: beer butt chicken
directions: Take one whole chicken and rub barbecue poultry seasoning inside and out. Open can of beer; drink approximately half of the beer. Set the can of beer on the grill of your barbecue pit. Hold open the large end of the chicken and stand it up on the grill with the beer can inside the chicken. Slow smoke over your favorite wood for 3 to 4 hours or until done for the most tender juicy chicken ever made. Enjoy.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Blend together sugar and Crisco.
Then mix rest of ingredients together.
Bake 1 hour at 325° in a greased and floured loaf pan.

title: squash dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 350° approximately 30 minutes.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Mix all ingredients except peanut butter and cook 5 minutes. Add peanut butter and beat well.
Pour into buttered dish or pan and let cool.
Cut into squares.

title: chinese peas
directions: Brown pork in oil.
Add onion.
Cook a few minutes.
Add soy sauce, flour and water.
Add salt, pepper and can peas.
Cook until thickened.

title: chocolate chip cake
directions: Mix cake mix and puddings.
Add eggs, oil and water.
Mix for 2 minutes.
Add chocolate chips.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch greased and floured cake pan.
Bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Place vegetables in casserole dish.
Pour soup over all. Sprinkle with grated cheese.
Add croutons or bread crumbs.
Bake in 400° oven for 30 minutes.

title: vegetable-cheese dip
directions: Combine chopped vegetables and salad dressing mix.
Fold into cottage cheese.
Store in container with screw-top; chill well. Serve with assorted crackers, chips or raw vegetables.

title: fruit cup
directions: To prepare dressing, mix yogurt and reserved pineapple juice. Cover and refrigerate.
In 6 dessert dishes, alternately layer pineapple chunks and strawberry slices, placing cottage cheese between each layer.
Refrigerate 1 1/2 to 2 hours or until well chilled.
Just before serving, top with yogurt dressing.
Makes 6 servings.

title: peanut butter and cracker cookies
directions: Combine milk and sugar in large saucepan.
Bring to boil for exactly 3 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add the vanilla, cracker crumbs, peanut butter and nuts.
Mix well and drop by spoonfuls on wax paper.

title: sweet and sour green beans
directions: If using canned beans, drain them.
Put beans in a 1 1/2-quart greased casserole dish.
Lay onion rings over beans.
Fry bacon; save drippings.
Crumble bacon; sprinkle it and almonds over beans.
Add sugar and vinegar to bacon drippings; heat to a simmer.
Pour over beans; marinate several hours or overnight. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: chocolate zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs, oil, sugar and vanilla. Stir in remaining ingredients after sifting dry ingredients together. Bake in 2 greased ring molds or loaf pans at 350° for 1 hour until tests done.

title: mock pizza
directions: Lightly brown ground beef; drain off excess fat.
Mix ground beef with all remaining ingredients, except bread and cheese. Slice French bread in half lengthwise.
Spread with ground beef mixture.
Broil 10 minutes.
Add cheese.
Broil until done.

title: french bread monterey
directions: Spread cut loaf with butter.
Put in a 350 degree oven for 8 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Mix remaining ingredients together and spread on bread.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Place under broiler until it's puffy and light brown.

title: marshmallow fruit dip
directions: Mix the cream cheese with the Marshmallow Creme.
Beat with electric mixer until smooth.
Red food coloring may be added. Chill and serve with fresh fruit.

title: old fashioned lemon pie
directions: Beat eggs; add remaining ingredients.
Pour into unbaked pie crust.
Bake 45 minutes in 325° oven.

title: mary's upside-down chocolate cake
directions: In small saucepan, heat 1/4 cup water and 1/4 cup butter. Stir in sugar, nuts and coconut.
Pour into greased 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: my favorite apple salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: pumpkin tea loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Bake in 9 x 5-inch loaf pan in a 350° oven for 60 to 70 minutes.
Yield:
1 loaf.

title: anniversary pound cake
directions: Grease and flour a 10-inch tube pan. Cream together butter, shortening and sugar. Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each. Sift together flour, salt, baking powder and cocoa. Add to creamed mixture alternately with milk and vanilla, beating after each. Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 30 minutes or 1 hour and 40 minutes. Cool in pan 5 minutes. Turn out and cool on rack. Frost if desired.

title: buckeyes
directions: Mix together 1 stick oleo, peanut butter, vanilla flavoring, graham crackers and confectioners sugar. Roll into small balls. It
is best to refrigerate for about 30 minutes.

title: better 'n chicken and dumplings
directions: Layer chicken in casserole dish and pour melted oleo over chicken.
Mix flour with milk and pour over chicken.
Mix soup with broth (liquid where chicken was cooked) and pour over top of casserole.
Gently stir across top to smooth out.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: sour cream raisin pie
directions: Cook raisins in water until plump, drain.
Mix dry ingredients, set aside.
In boiler beat egg yolks and add sour cream and stir together well.
Add dry ingredients.
Cook over medium heat until thick stirring constantly.
Pour filling into a cooked crust.
Top with meringue.

title: crab meat dip
directions: Have cream cheese at room temperature.
Combine all ingredients, except almonds.
Blend over low heat until warm or bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Sprinkle almonds on top.
This can be made ahead and refrigerated.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients; press into loaf pan and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Steam broccoli (chop if you have spears).
Mix soup, cheese, egg, onion and mayonnaise together.
In a separate bowl mix butter and stuffing.
Place broccoli mixture in a baking dish and top with stuffing.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: cherry chocolate cake
directions: In large bowl, combine cake mix, cherry pie filling, eggs and extract.
Stir by hand until well mixed.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: cheese spread
directions: Mix the Wispride and cream cheese together well.
Chop the vegetables up very small and add them to the base.
Add in sauces. Fold in the cottage cheese and Bleu cheese.

title: chicken vermicelli
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Boil chicken (reserve broth) and chop in bite size pieces. Boil vermicelli according to directions. Drain.

title: lemon marinated chuck roast
directions: Score fat edges of roast.
Place meat in shallow baking dish. Combine lemon peel and juice, cooking oil, green onion, sugar, salt, Worcestershire, mustard and pepper.
Pour over roast. Cover; let stand 3 hours at room temperature or overnight in the refrigerator, turning roast several times.

title: reuben casserole
directions: Mix sauerkraut, sour cream, onion and garlic.
Place mixture in bottom of 13 x 9 x 2-inch buttered pan.
Top with corned beef. Sprinkle Swiss cheese over beef.
Top with rye crumbs.
Bake at 350° until hot and cheese melts (20 to 30 minutes).
Serves 4.

title: sausage jelly
directions: Cook sausage and drain.
Add jelly and mustard.
Cook until jelly is dissolved and mix with the mustard.

title: taco shells - tacos(international cuisine)
directions: Put sizable amount of cooking oil in frying pan (large enough to hold tortilla); heat until almost scalding (don't boil).
Place tortilla in open-faced until just slightly brown on bottom, then turn and fold in half (you have to hold slightly open with fork to shape like a taco shell).
Brown one side, then flip it over and brown other side; take out and place on paper towel to absorb oil. Stuff with meat and toppings.

title: hurry up dinner rolls
directions: Combine 1 cup flour, sugar, yeast and salt in bowl.
Stir water, egg and oil.
Beat until smooth.
Cover; let rise in warm place for 15 minutes.
Stir in enough flour to make soft, sticky dough.
Turn dough onto a floured board; continue to work in flour until dough can be kneaded.
Knead until smooth and elastic (about 3 minutes).

title: hustie
directions: Combine ingredients; roll into paper thin circles.
Cut into triangle shape wedges.
Slice an opening into every other wedge. Insert an unslit wedge into slit wedge and deep fry in hot fat. After cooked, shake with confectioners sugar.

title: bill's famous jerky
directions: Trim and discard all fat from meat.
Cut meat into 1/8 to 1/4-inch slices.

title: banana split pudding
directions: In a bowl, whisk milk with pudding for 2 minutes.
Add banana, strawberries and pineapple.
Place in serving bowls.
Top with Cool Whip.
Drizzle with syrup and top with nuts.

title: pepper jack meat loaf
directions: In large bowl, combine egg, bread crumbs, onion, salt and pepper. Crumble beef over mixture and mix well. Press half of the beef mixture into the bottom and halfway up the sides of a greased 8 x 4 x 2-inch loaf pan. Sprinkle 3/4 cup cheese over the meat to within 1/2-inch of the sides. Pat remaining beef mixture over cheese. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes or until meat is no longer pink and meat thermometer reads 160°. Sprinkle with remaining cheese and bake 5 minutes longer or until cheese is melted. Let stand 10 minutes before slicing.

title: peach cream pie
directions: Peel peaches and cut in halves.
Arrange on unbaked pie crust with cut side down.
Mix rest of ingredients and pour over peaches.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes.
Reduce oven to 350° and bake for an additional 30 minutes.

title: ritz cracker chicken casserole
directions: Put cut up chicken in bottom of casserole dish (9 x 13-inch). Combine soup and sour cream; cover chicken.
