Crush crackers, mix with poppy seed and sprinkle over soup mixture. Drizzle with melted butter (oleo).
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Watch very closely as Ritz crackers may burn.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: oatmeal bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.

Grease pan. Beat butter and sugar. Stir in syrup and oats. Butter fingers and pat into the pan. Bake at 350° for 15 to 16 minutes in 9 x 13-inch pan. DO NOT OVERBAKE. Cool in pan. Spread with glaze while warm.

title: yellow squash casserole
directions: Cook squash and onion until tender. Drain. Mix eggs, cheese, milk, butter and sugar with squash. Put in a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish. Cover with buttered croutons or bread crumbs. Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: california blend vegetables
directions: Spray 9 1/2 x 13 pan with Pam. Add Cheddar cheese on top last.

title: chocolate chip kiss cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Remove wrappers from chocolate pieces. In large mixing bowl, beat butter, sugar, brown sugar and vanilla until well blended.
Add flour, blend until smooth.
Stir in small chocolate chips.
Mold scant tablespoon dough around each chocolate piece, covering completely.
Shape into balls.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes or until set.
Cool slightly, remove from cookie sheet to wire rack; cool completely. Makes 4 dozen.

title: heartland baked beans
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
In skillet brown ground beef and drain. In large bowl combine all ingredients, pour into 2-quart casserole.
Bake, uncovered 30 to 35 minutes or until thoroughly heated.

title: tomato gelatin jam
directions: Combine tomatoes and sugar.
Boil 15 minutes.
Add the gelatin and stir until completely dissolved.
Put in jars and refrigerate or freeze.

title: mandarin orange salad
directions: Mix together pineapple and pudding and pie filling.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Drain oranges.
Mix oranges with pineapple, pudding and Cool Whip mixture.
Save a few of the oranges to garnish the top of the salad.
Refrigerate.

title: martha washington candy
directions: Mix sugar, pecans, coconut, vanilla, butter and milk with hands.
Roll into balls the size of marbles.
Melt chocolate and paraffin in double boiler.
Dip balls in mixture (use skewer) and place on wax paper to cool.

title: chicken and dressing casserole
directions: Stew chicken breasts until well done.
Reserve chicken broth. Cube chicken into small cubes.
Put in bottom of casserole dish. Mix celery soup and mushroom soup with sour cream until smooth. Spread over top of chicken.
Cover this with Stove Top stuffing (after mixing package).
Pour 1 1/2 cups chicken broth over top evenly.
Bake, covered, in 325° oven about 40 minutes.

title: teriyaki sauce for steak
directions: Stir until sugar dissolves.
Add steak.
Let marinate 2 to 4 hours before cooking.

title: lucy's tortilla pinwheels
directions: Mix all of the filling ingredients together thoroughly. Divide filling and spread evenly over tortillas.
Roll up tortillas, cover tightly, with plastic wrap, twisting ends. Refrigerate for several hours.
Unwrap, cut in slices 1/2 to 1/4-inch thick.
Arrange on plate, serve with salsa, makes about 50 pinwheels.

title: pork chop-bean bake
directions: In ovenproof skillet, brown chops on both sides.
Remove chops from pan and pour off drippings.
Blend in soup and thyme.
Stir in beans.
Arrange chops on top.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper. Cover and bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until tender.
Uncover and cook until sauce is of desired consistency, 5 to 8 minutes.

title: corn bread-old fashion
directions: Bring the water and margarine to a rolling boil.
In a mixing bowl, combine meal, sugar and salt.
Pour water mixture into dry ingredients and mix well with electric mixer.
Add eggs and mix well.
Pour in milk, mix well.
Grease a 13 inch x 8 inch oblong baking dish.
Bake at 350 degrees for approximately one hour or until a toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together and place in a casserole dish. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: tomato basil soup
directions: Place in sauce pan and warm slowly, until heated thoroughly.

title: "quick" green bean casserole
directions: Mix together.
Put in 1-quart casserole dish.
Sprinkle with Chinese noodles or rice noodles or top with your favorite sliced cheese.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Cook ground meat until done; drain well on paper towels.
Add onion and peppers.
Cook until tender.
Grease a large iron skillet and sprinkle with meal.
Bake in oven until brown.
Mix first 7 ingredients together.
Pour about 1/2 corn mixture in pan, then put layer of cheese, hamburger mixture and rest of cheese.
Then top with rest of batter.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: yummy bars
directions: Whip with spoon and spread over first layer.

title: microwave mint chocolate bars
directions: Grease round baking dish.
Microwave unsweetened chocolate in a large batter bowl on High until melted, about 2 to 2 1/2 minutes.
Add shortening; microwave on High for 30 seconds.
Beat in sugar, eggs and vanilla until smooth.
Stir in flour, baking powder and salt.
Spread in baking dish.
Microwave on High for 2 minutes.
Rotate dish 1/4 turn and continue to microwave 1 to 3 minutes longer or until no longer doughy, but not dry.
Place chocolate mint patties on top and microwave on High until filling melts out around chocolate coating, about 1 1/2 to 2 minutes. Spread mint patties over chocolate bars.
Cut after cooling for 5 minutes.

title: light fudge cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Coat a 9 x 13-inch baking pan with cooking spray.
Sift flour, cocoa, salt and baking soda in mixing bowl.
Mix in brown sugar.
Add vinegar, oil, vanilla and water. Stir until completely mixed.
Pour batter into baking pan and bake 45 to 50 minutes.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Cook carrots; slice onion and bell pepper.
Bring to boil soup, sugar, vinegar, oil and Worcestershire sauce.
After ingredients boil, pour over onions, pepper and carrots.
Marinate overnight.

title: sweet pie
directions: Mix flour and butter in a food processor until crumbly (or mix by hand).
Add egg, sugar and white wine.
Mix together in processor.
Chill for 1 hour.
Roll out and put in spring-form pan to be filled with Sweet Pie Recipe.

title: prune cake(gooooood!)
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Combine oil, prune pulp, buttermilk and
eggs.
Add dry ingredients; mix well.
Add nuts and vanilla. Pour
into
tube
pan.
May
or
may not grease pan. Bake
at 325° or 350° for 1 hour or 10 minutes more.
Makes a large
cake. I
put
on
a
glaze while it is still warm.
Be prepared for compliments!

title: country ham-baked
directions: Trim ham.
Layer in a casserole dish.
Put a lid on the dish and bake approximately 30 to 45 minutes at 350°.
This is an easy way to have ham quickly.
Ham is softer than fried and works great for ham and biscuits.

title: potato casserole
directions: Cook potatoes until done.
Mix soups together.
Layer potatoes, cheese and soup twice.
Dot with butter, salt and pepper to taste.
Cook at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pancit(oriental noodles)
directions: Heat oil in a skillet.
Saute garlic and onions.
Add shrimp, pork or chicken.
Add soy sauce and pepper and cook until dry. Add water or chicken broth and cook until meat is tender.
Add noodles and mix.
Cook on low fire.
Add vegetables until cooked or half-cooked.
Add salt to taste.
Serve hot.
Sprinkle with chopped green onions over the top.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Place peanut butter in mixing bowl and add syrup slowly. Blend eggs, sugar, vanilla and salt.
Stir until mixture is smooth and creamy.
Fold in pecans and pour into pie crust.
Bake at 425° for 20 minutes; reduce to 350° and bake for 25 to 30 minutes more or until custard forms.
Serve with whipped cream when cooled.

title: blushing champagne punch
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in a large container, stirring well. Cover and chill.
Pour mixture into a large punch bowl; add champagne, stirring gently.
Add ice cubes or an ice ring, if desired.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix
all
together
and pour in hot greased skillet and bake at 400° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: stained glass window cookies
directions: In a large bowl, beat butter with hand mixer until soft. Then add the sugar and beat until fluffy. Add milk and vanilla and blend, gradually beat in flour. Form dough into a disc, wrap and chill one hour. Roll the chilled dough out on lightly floured surface. Use lightly floured cookie cutter to cut shapes and a small round cookie cutter to cut holes. Place the shapes on a foil lined cookie sheet and add
about a half a teaspoon of crushed candy to the holes. Bake 375° for 8 minutes, cool 10 minutes.

title: brandied cranberries
directions: Wash cranberries and discard any unacceptable cranberries. Combine cranberries and sugar in a 13 X 9 inch Pyrex dish. Cover with foil and bake at 350 degrees for 45 to 50 minutes or until cranberries take on a "candied" appearance. Allow to cool. Add brandy to baked cranberries and stir. Store in a sealed container in refrigerator. Great as a relish or use as a topping on a dessert.

title: herbed spinach bake
directions: Cook and drain spinach.
Mix with the rice and all other ingredients.
Put into 10 x 6 x 1 1/2-inch baking dish in 350° oven for 20 to 25 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: orange delight
directions: Make Jell-O as directed on box.
Mix in orange sherbet while still hot.
Place orange slices in bottom of dessert dish.
Pour Jell-O mixture over orange slices and cool.
This will have a layered look when cool.

title: gazpacho
directions: Combine ingredients in a stainless steel or glass bowl. Cover; chill at least 4 hours.
Serve in chilled cups.
Pass crisp croutons.
Makes 6 servings.

title: blueberry bread
directions: Beat shortening at medium speed until creamy; gradually add sugar, beating well.
Add pineapple, eggs, milk and lemon juice; beat well.
Combine flour and next 3 ingredients; add to shortening mixture, beating until blended.
Stir in blueberries, pecans and coconut.
Spoon batter into 2 greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pans. Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes or until a wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool bread in pans on wire racks 10 minutes.
Remove bread from pans and let cool completely on wire racks.

title: forgotten cookies
directions: Turn oven to 350°.
Beat until stiff the egg whites and sugar. Add chocolate bits, pecans and vanilla.
Drop by teaspoon on lightly greased cookie sheet.
Put in oven and turn oven off. Leave in oven for at least 45 minutes.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat all ingredients together well.
Pour into unbaked pie crust and bake very slowly at 350° about 1 hour.

title: ham and vegetable soup
directions: Soak the beans overnight; drain and cook in the ham broth with the bone until tender.
Add the other vegetables and cook them until they are soft.
Remove the bone; add parsley and pieces of leftover ham.
Simmer for a few minutes, then serve.
It will be thick and delicious.

title: cookie salad
directions: Mix together the yogurt and pudding.
Add the Cool Whip.
Mix and add the oranges and pineapple.
Add the cookies and mix all together.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Drain and reserve liquid from salmon.
Remove bones from salmon.
Use liquid to moisten bread.
Add remaining ingredients. Mix well.
Pour into loaf dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Can be microwaved at High (100%) until center is set, 7 to 11 minutes.
If you don't have a carousel, rotate loaf dish 1/2 turn after 1/2 cooking time.

title: pecan delight
directions: Melt
almond bark and chocolate chips in double boiler. Add nuts and stir well.
Spoon out on wax paper.

title: party meatballs
directions: Heat and serve.
I served these at Chris' wedding.
They were easy and delicious.

title: corn bread
directions: Cream shortening and sugar; add egg.
Beat and add milk.
Add flour and corn meal, stirring only to mix.
No need to sift flour or corn meal unless you prefer.
Pour in greased baking pan or dish.
Bake in hot oven, 425°, for 25 minutes or until brown on top.

title: shrimp casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients except stuffing and butter.
Spoon mixture into 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Stir dressing in melted butter and sprinkle over casserole.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 minutes.
Remove from oven and cover casserole dish for a few minutes before serving.
Serves four.

title: avocado salad
directions: Slice avocado in strips.
In large bowl, toss avocado, salad greens, cheese and olives with the vinaigrette until well coated. Makes 4 servings.

title: golden chocolate treasure cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In small bowl, combine flour, baking soda and salt; set aside.
In large mixing bowl, beat butter, sugar and brown sugar until creamy, 3 to 5 minutes.
Beat in vanilla and egg.
Gradually blend in flour mixture.
Stir in semi-sweet chocolate morsels and nuts.
Drop by rounded measuring tablespoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes.
Let stand 2 minutes before removing from cookie sheets; cool completely.
Makes about 18 cookies.

title: yum-yum salad
directions: Drain pineapple and cherries. Cook juice with flour and sugar until thick.
Beat egg yolks into mixture and let cool.
Fold in beaten egg whites. Add fruit mixture and whipped cream.
Makes a large bowl.

title: pasta primavera
directions: Cook sliced sausage in frypan with onion, mushrooms, garlic and olive oil.
Fry meat until cooked.
Add broccoli and zucchini; cook until soft.
Drain off excess grease.
Cook thin spaghetti as directed on package.
Drain.
Add meat mix to vegetable mix with spaghetti and mix well.
Add salt, pepper and more cheese to top off.

title: easy peanut butter fudge
directions: Melt chocolate and peanut butter in top of a double boiler. Remove from heat and stir in milk.
Pour in 8 x 8-inch pan lined with waxed paper.
Refrigerate to chill.
Cut into 1-inch pieces. Yields 1 1/2 pounds.
Enjoy!

title: crab tidbits
directions: Mix all ingredients, except crabmeat and muffins.
Add crabmeat.
Spread on muffins; cut in wedges.
Can freeze.
Broil until golden, 4 to 8 minutes.

title: paella casserole(chicken, shrimp, sausage and rice)
directions: Preheat oven to 350° (176°C).
In a Dutch oven, lightly saute garlic in oil over moderate heat.
Remove garlic.
Brown chicken in same oil.
When brown, set chicken aside.
Add rice to oil; stir until browned.
Dissolve saffron in chicken stock (hot), then add all ingredients together, except shrimp and clams.
Bake for 30 minutes.
Arrange shrimp and clams on top; bake for an extra 10 minutes.

title: sausage and gravy
directions: Cook sausage.
Crumble and set aside.
(Leave enough fat to cover bottom of pan.)
Turn pan to high and add 3 tablespoons flour to fat.
Brown the flour to medium brown, stirring at all times. Pour in 1 cup hot water and constantly stir to keep it from lumping.
Turn heat to medium and stir in 1 cup milk.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: honey ham tortilla rolls
directions: With electric mixer, beat ham and cream cheese together until smooth.
Stir in green onion, pineapple and honey.
Spread 1/4 cup ham mixture on each flour tortilla to within 1/2-inch of edges. Roll up each tortilla, starting from one edge; wrap in plastic wrap and refrigerate 2 to 8 hours before serving.
To serve, cut each tortilla, roll into 1/2-inch slices and arrange on platter. Makes appetizer servings for 8.

title: pork 'n' potatoes
directions: Brown pork chops in 1 tablespoon oil in large skillet.
Remove and drain fat.
Cut up onions and potatoes and brown in 1 tablespoon oil.
Add pork chops to potatoes and onions.
Mix mushroom soup with 1/2 cup water and pour over chips.
Allow to simmer on medium-low for about 1 hour to 1 1/2 hours.
Stir occasionally.
Salt to taste.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream the shortening and sugar. Add eggs, then mashed bananas, flour, baking powder, soda and lastly water. Bake at 300° for 1 hour.

title: country kitchen casserole
directions: Mix all together or put meat on top and bake in shallow dish at 400° for 25 minutes.

title: strawberry pizza
directions: Blend flour and margarine, then blend in all confectioners sugar.
Press into pizza pan or 9 x 13-inch pan or casserole dish. Bake 15 minutes at 350°.
Cool to room temperature.

title: dirt
directions: You will need a plastic flower pot, digging trowel and flower.

title: twinkie cake
directions: Mix sour cream and pudding.
Layer in this order:
Twinkies, filling, sour cream and pudding and Cool Whip.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into well-greased skillet or muffin tins.
Bake at 375° for 40 minutes.
Makes 12 muffins.

title: fruit salad
directions: Cook pudding with juice from fruit (not milk); cool.
Fold in fruit (don't stir).

title: never fail custard pie
directions: Beat 4 eggs, 1 tsp. vanilla, 1 tsp. salt.
Add milk and sugar to egg mixture.
Pour in pie shell and sprinkle with nutmeg.
Bake at 400 degrees for 20 - 25 minutes.

title: baked lima beans
directions: Cook dried limas until done.
(You can use canned limas if you prefer.)
When done, drain about half of liquid off (and save) and put in baking dish.
Cook 4 slices of bacon and drain on paper towel.
Cook 1/2 cup onion and 1 tablespoon of the bacon grease. Add onion to beans and the following:
Worcestershire sauce, mustard, brown sugar and catsup.
Mix all together with crumpled bacon.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 325°.
(If it is not thick enough, cook another 1/2 hour.)

title: estonian sauerkraut(mulgi kapsad)
directions: Rinse sauerkraut to take away excess sourness.
Press out water and put into a heavy pot, pan, skillet or Dutch oven.
Soak pork overnight in salted water.

Put rinsed sauerkraut in pot. Take pork from water and add to pot along with the barley. Bring to a boil over slow flame. Do not let stick, so stir often with a wooden spoon. When boiling, remove from burner, cover and place in a 350° preheated oven.
Let simmer for 3 hours.

title: chicken bundles
directions: Mix cheese, milk, salt, pepper and dill weed until smooth. Stir in chicken, celery and onions.
Unroll crescent dough and separate into 12 rectangles.
Place on baking sheet.
Press perforated edges together.
Place 1/3 cup chicken mixture into the center of each rectangle.
Bring up to the center and pinch edges to seal.
Brush with butter.
Sprinkle with bread crumbs. Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes or until golden brown.

title: corned beef and cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients together and form into ball.
Sprinkle with paprika and serve with crackers.

title: pumpkin pie cake
directions: Mix and bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Spread mixture on cooled crust.
Chop raw vegetables very fine and place on top of mixture.
Top with very finely shredded Cheddar cheese.

title: tostitos
directions: Mix all ingredients and spread each chip with cheese mixture. Place 10 to 12 Tostitos on serving plate.
Microwave at 50% power for 1 minute or until cheese is melted. Serve warm. Give dish 1/4 turn during cooking.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Combine broccoli, celery and onion; cook until tender-crisp, according to directions on broccoli box.
Drain.
Melt margarine in a large casserole.
Combine all ingredients, except onion rings, in casserole and mix well.
Bake in a 350° oven for 45 minutes, covered.
During last 5 minutes, put onion rings on top and bake, uncovered.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: cabbage rolls
directions: Mix together sausage, egg, rice and finely chopped onion. Place the head of cabbage in boiling water to loosen and remove outer leaves.
Cut core part of leaves down to thin areas.
Place small amount of meat mixture in each leaf and roll up.
Push ends in.
Place in large pot; pour tomatoes over and simmer until rice is tender.
Serve hot with bread.

title: choose a cake mix cookies
directions: Mix together cake mix, butter and eggs.
Add water and chocolate chips.
Bake in a 350° oven for 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes 7 dozen cookies.

title: better than sex cake
directions: Bake cake according to directions, using a 9 x 13-inch pan. Let cool.
In saucepan, combine pineapple with juice and sugar. Bring to a boil, stirring until the sugar dissolves.
Poke holes in cooled cake and then spread pineapple mixture over cake.

title: shrimp and green bean bake
directions: Rinse shrimp.
Cook beans as directed.
Drain thoroughly. Place beans in a shallow 1-quart baking dish.
Cover with shrimp. Combine soup, parsley, lemon juice and lemon peel.
Pour over shrimp and beans.
Cover and bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Uncover and top with cheese.
Sprinkle with paprika and bake 10 minutes more or until cheese is melted.
Makes 4 to 5 servings.

title: carrot cheese soup
directions: Place carrots, onions and broth in 4-quart saucepan.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and cook until carrots are tender.
Remove 1 cup and chop fine.
Blend with cheese; return to saucepan.
Season to taste.
May be pureed all together, if preferred.

title: bean salad
directions: In a saucepan, bring sugar, oil, vinegar, salt and pepper to a boil.
Cook until sugar dissolves.
Cool, then pour over beans that have been rinsed and drained.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: patriotic salad
directions: Dissolve 2 boxes Jell-O in 4 cups boiling water.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan and chill until firm.

title: chocolate cherry oatmeal cluster
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa, milk and butter in saucepan.
Cook, stirring constantly, until the ingredients begin to boil.
Boil 1 minute. Remove from heat and blend in peanut butter and oats.
If you want other ingredients, add to mix at this time.
Drop by teaspoon onto wax paper to cool.
Makes about 4 dozen cookies.

title: perfect pie crust
directions: Sift together flour, sugar and salt.
Add shortening and mix until crumbly.
In small bowl beat together the ice water, vinegar and egg.
Add to flour mixture and stir ingredients until moist. Divide dough into five balls.
Wrap each in plastic bag and refrigerate about 30 minutes before rolling.
Pastry will keep in refrigerator 3 days or can be stored in freezer.
Makes 2 double and 1 single crusts.

title: chocolate zucchini bread
directions: Cream eggs, oil and sugar.
Add vanilla.
Mix dry ingredients together.
Add zucchini to creamed mixture.
Mix with dry ingredients. Fold in nuts, if desired.
Bake at 350 degrees for 80 minutes.

title: yellow squash pickles
directions: Slice squash, add onion.
Add salt; cover with cracked ice. Mix thoroughly; let stand 3 hours.

title: poppy seed pound cake
directions: Cream Crisco with sugar.
Add egg yolks and poppy seed in milk, mixing well.
Add 1 cup buttermilk, butter, lemon and almond flavorings.
Measure out flour, soda and salt; fold into first mixture.
Beat egg whites until stiff and fold into mixture.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes in a greased and floured tube or Bundt pan.

title: french fried mushrooms
directions: Thoroughly mix flour, salt, baking powder and pepper.
Beat egg yolk and milk together.
Blend in dry ingredients.
Beat egg white until foamy; add sugar.
Beat until stiff, but not dry. Fold in milk mixture.
Dip mushrooms in batter.
Roll in Chex crumbs.
Drop, a few at a time, in deep, hot fat.
Fry until brown (1 to 2 minutes).
Turn once.

title: crackling cornbread
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Add egg, sour milk and oil; blend well.
Add 1 cup cracklings, stir and pour into a greased 8-inch square pan.
Bake at 425° for 30 minutes or until done.
Cut in squares and serve.

title: baked fillets
directions: Cut frozen fillets into serving size.
Place in a single layer, skin side down, in a well-greased baking dish.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour over fish.
Bake in moderate oven at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until fish flakes when tested.

title: dump cake
directions: In an oblong cake pan, dump the pineapple.
To this, add the pie filling.
Mix together.
Spread on top of dry cake mix.
Melt the margarine and drizzle over the top.
Add 1 cup chopped pecans. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: golfer's chicken
directions: Wash the chicken and pat dry.
Overlap slightly in baking dish. Mix the Lipton onion soup mix, Russian dressing and apricot jam. Stir until mixed well and not lumpy.
Put 1 tablespoon of mixture on each piece of chicken.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour or at 225° for 4 to 5 hours (while playing golf).

title: cocktail meatballs
directions: Mix ground beef with all ingredients except chili sauce and grape jelly.
Shape into 1-inch meatballs.
Brown meatballs in heavy skillet with 1/4 cup shortening or place meatballs on broiler pan and bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Heat chili sauce and grape jelly.
Stir to melt.
Add meatballs and simmer, uncovered, for about 30 minutes.
Makes from 3 to 5 dozen, depending on the size.

title: lima bean ham chowder
directions: Combine beans and water; bring to boil and let simmer 2 minutes.
Remove from heat; let stand 1 hour.
Add ham hock; cover and simmer 1 hour or until meat is tender.
Add 1 teaspoon salt; simmer 30 minutes.
Saute onion and green pepper in butter until tender; add to lima beans along with ham, corn and milk.
Heat thoroughly, but do not boil.
Season to taste with salt and pepper.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix all together including the cheese (except crackers).
Top with crushed crackers.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: venison sausage
directions: Grind all meat fine.
Mix all ingredients.
Put into casings or fry as country sausage.

title: wild rice chowder
directions: Partially cook wild rice (about 20 minutes), following basic method.
Add vegetable broth and flour.
Heat to boiling; stir constantly.
Boil 1 minute.
Stir in half and half.
Simmer for 10 minutes.
Season with salt and pepper.
Clams can be added if you like.

title: cheese squares(appetizers)
directions: Grate the 2 cheeses together.
Grease a 9 x 9-inch pan.
Layer cheese, green chilies, cheese and green chilies.
Dribble egg, milk and flour mixture over the top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until done.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Cream softened margarine and cream cheese.
Cream in sugar then eggs, adding egg one at a time.
Add salt, baking powder, vanilla and almond extract; mix well.
Add flour, a little at a time, then mix all for at least 5 minutes.
Bake at 275° for 1 1/2 hours or until top splits, sides loosen from sides of pan and toothpick comes out clean.
Bake in a large tube pan sprayed liberally with Pam spray.

title: walleye fillets en noble
directions: Dip fillets in melted butter and place in shallow baking dish; sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Mix soup, cream and sherry.
Cover fish with this, then sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
(Any white fleshed fish can be used.)
Good with pasta or rice.

title: quick custard pie
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Beat well and pour into 9-inch pie plate.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Sprinkle top with cinnamon.

title: calico beans
directions: Mix all the ingredients together and bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Stir twice while baking.

title: cassie's date bars
directions: Slowly add sugar to eggs; beat well.
Add dry ingredients, beat.
Add dates, vanilla and nuts.
Pour into 9 inch x 13 inch pan lined with wax paper.
Bake at 350° about 30 minutes.
While warm, cut into 1 inch x 4 inch bars.
Roll in powdered sugar.

title: old fashioned corn bread
directions: Sift, then measure the flour. Sift again with the baking soda, salt and cornmeal. Combine well beaten eggs, buttermilk and melted shortening. Add the liquid ingredients, stirring only until smooth. Turn into a well-greased 8 x 8-inch pan. Bake in preheated 425° oven for 25 to 30 minutes. This is a moist, golden bread.

title: wacky cake
directions: Into an ungreased cake pan, sift the first 6 ingredients. Make 3 depressions in the dry ingredients.
Put vanilla in first, vinegar in second and shortening in third.
Pour over all the water.
Stir until a thin well mixed batter is formed.
It should be stirred until smooth.
Bake 30 minutes in a 350° oven.
Leave in pan and frost.

title: avocado salad
directions: Stuff avocado halves with mixture.
Put halves together.
Wrap in wax paper. Chill for 30 minutes.

title: canned tomato juice
directions: Wash tomatoes; remove core and cut in fourths.
Put in large pot; cook until soupy.
Strain in a strainer to remove seed and peeling.
Put strained juice in another pot; boil.
Have hot jars ready with 1 teaspoon salt in each.
Pour hot juice in jar; seal with can flat and ring.
(More or less tomatoes can be prepared at a time.)
